(46, 166, 'Canada Federal Skilled Workers Program Petition Process', '<div>\r\n<div>The Federal Skilled Worker Program (FSWP) is a program that helps workers with a lot of experience and a high level of skills get permanent residency in Canada. You should use the Express Entry system to sign up for this program. It is the easiest and, for now, the fastest way to<strong> move to Canada</strong>&nbsp;for good. If you meet the minimum score and give honest information, you can be sure that your immigration process will go smoothly.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Your Application Submission</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; You should have worked full-time in the job you want for at least one year in the last 10 years.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Your job should be listed as Skill Type 0 (managerial occupation), Skill Level 1 (professional occupation), and Skill Level B (Technical occupation and skill trade)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Get at least 67 points on the test of your skills.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A letter from a Canadian employer offering a full-time job and LMIA qualification (Labour Market Impact Assessment)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; CLB 7 language proficiency score in either English or French</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Having enough money to settle in Canada</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step-By-Step Procedure to Submit Your Application under FSWP</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow these major steps to successfully submit a submission as a Federal Skilled Worker (FSW), under the Canada Federal Skilled Workers Program:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>1. Get Hold of Submission Package</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It comprises the instruction manual and every other form that you require to fill out. Utilize the manual to gain assistance to fill-out the forms properly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fill out the forms on your computer. Post you are through with the process:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Authenticate the Generic Application Form for Canada [IMM 0008] online. Hit the &lsquo;Validate&rsquo; button on the form even as the same will draw in red any fields you may have unknowingly overlooked and require to fill-out.</li>\r\n	<li>Print the barcode page (the page will be visible, post you confirm the form).</li>\r\n	<li>Put your signature where you are asked.</li>\r\n	<li>Take in the barcode page with your submission.</li>\r\n	<li>Print the additional forms and put your signature where you are asked.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Note it is essential that each and every of your reply is 100% complete and right. It is also vital that you fill-out every form mentioned in the package for the application. Make use of the Document Checklist to take care that you do not ignore something.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>2. Shell-out the Petition Charges.</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be required to pay:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The processing charge for you and also your family members.<br />\r\n	At the time of presenting your submission, it is crucial that you embrace everyone who will accompany your to Canada. It influences your charges. Go through the fee list to find-out how much the same will be.<br />\r\n	In case you are not deemed qualified to submit an application, the Citizenship and Immigration Canada (CIC) will contact you even as Your processing charges would be given back.</li>\r\n	<li>Right of Permanent Residence Charges<br />\r\n	You will require giving the charge in case your petition is endorsed. The same covers you and your spouse and/or dependents, in case they are arriving with you. It is crucial that you pay it prior to you are offered your prized <strong>Canada</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Permanent Resident Visa&nbsp;</strong>(PRV).<br />\r\n	This charge will be given back in case you withdraw your submission, or in a situation wherein you fail to utilize your permit.</li>\r\n	<li>Additional Charges</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You will also have to shell-out charges to third parties for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your medical examination,</li>\r\n	<li>A police certificate, in a situation where in you require the same,</li>\r\n	<li>An educational credential assessment (ECA),</li>\r\n	<li>Testing for language, and</li>\r\n	<li>Services at a Visa Application Centre, in case you utilize one.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nFill-out the Fee Payment Form (IMM 5620) even as you take in the same with your petition. At the present, online payments for qualified employees are not accepted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The manual has more comprehensive information on charges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make certain you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have filled-out and put your signature on your petition and every forms,</li>\r\n	<li>Take in your processing charges, and</li>\r\n	<li>Take in every supporting paper/certificate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In case you fail to do, your submission will be returned back to you, so that you can rectify any mistakes before resending the same. Make use of the Document Checklist to confirm that you do not overlook anything.<br />\r\nYou ought to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Authenticate the Generic Application Form for Canada [IMM 0008] online (press the &lsquo;Validate&rsquo; button on the form, and it will delineate in red any omitted fields),</li>\r\n	<li>Print the barcode page, and</li>\r\n	<li>Take in the barcode page with your submission. The same will assist make certain that your submission is 100% complete and it stays away from delays.</li>\r\n	<li>Mail your petition and charges to the Sydney, Nova Scotia (Canada) based Centralized Intake Office. Strictly do not send your submission to the visa bureau that serves your specific home nation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Several routes are available to fruitfully get involved with <strong>Canada Immigration</strong>. In case you are unable to fulfill the conditions to present a submission, through the FSWP, you could meet the requirements under a new stream.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>3. Present your Completed Petition</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Make certain that you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have filled-out and put your signature on your submission and all forms,</li>\r\n	<li>Take in your processing charges, and</li>\r\n	<li>Take in every supporting certificate/paper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In case you fail to do so, your submission will be returned back to youe ven while you will be expected to fix any mistakes before resending the same. Employ the Document Checklist to check you do not overlook anything.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You ought to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Authenticate the Generic Application Form for Canada [IMM 0008] online (hit the &lsquo;Validate&rsquo; button on the form even as the same will delineate in red any omitted fields),</li>\r\n	<li>Print the barcode page, and</li>\r\n	<li>Take in the barcode page with your submission.The same will assist you certify that your submission is 100% complete and keep the same away from delays.</li>\r\n	<li>Mail your petition and charges to the Sydney, Nova Scotia (Canada) based Centralized Intake Office. Avoid sending your petition to the visa administrative center that serves your home nation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nSeveral ways are up for grabs to move to Canada. In case you are unable to meet the conditions to submit a submission, through the FSWP, you could make the grade under a different class.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about&nbsp;<strong>Canada Federal Skilled Workers Program Petition Process&nbsp;</strong>can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experienced consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '124731995_Canada-immigration_378179980-scaled-1-768x452.jpeg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NDY=', 1, '2023-12-22 04:44:20'),
(47, 167, 'Federal Skilled Worker Selection Criteria â€“ Canada FSW Point System', '<div>\r\n<p>Citizenship and Immigration Canada has officially announced that it will start accepting applications under the <strong>Express Entry Programm</strong> for Skilled Professionals interested in migrating to Canada, starting from January 1st, 2015. Candidates whose applications are picked up from Express Entry Pool must also meet the requirements of selection criteria under the federal skilled worker program in which he filing the application. One can file under one of the three programs:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Federal Skilled Worker Class</li>\r\n	<li>Federal Skilled Trades Class</li>\r\n	<li>Canadian Experience Class</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nRemember this selection criteria is applicable AFTER the candidates application has been successfully picked up from the express entry pool. It is also true that unless the candidate does not meet FSW selection criteria, an invite to apply will NOT be issued to the Candidate. Please do not confuse the selection criteria and pass-mark under the FSW with point system under <u>Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS)</u>- Express Entry points Criteria. Purpose of CRS and points mentioned therein is limited to ranking the candidate against other prospective migrants and choosing the best possible suited to.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHere is the applicable point system and related selection Criteria which candidates chosen from the Express Entry Pool MUST meet:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Language - Principal Applicant (Maximum 28 Points)</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nOut of the possible 28 points, one can claim up-to 24 points under English language factor and remaining 4 points under French Language factor. This is under a situation where the applicant is filing the application with English as the first language. Applicants with high level (proven by high IELTS band score) of English language proficiency can claim all the 24 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An applicant must prove a minimum proficiency in each of the four language abilities, speaking, listening, reading and writing - Canadian Language Benchmark 7 (CLB 7) level for English in order to qualify for the Federal Skilled Worker Class (FSWC) program.</li>\r\n	<li>For the English language requirement, <strong>CLB 7 is equivalent to scoring 6 bands in each of the 4 abilities on the IELTS</strong> GENERAL pattern examination.</li>\r\n	<li>For the French language requirement, NCLC 7 is equivalent to scoring 309, 248, 206 and 309 on the speaking, listening, reading and writing modules of the Test d&#39;evaluation de francais (TEF), respectively.</li>\r\n	<li>4 points are awarded for each of the four language abilities, meaning that all candidates that meet the mandatory minimums on all language abilities will have at least 16 points.</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants will be awarded one extra point foreach language ability for which they score CLB 8 or NCLC 8 and two extra points if they score CLB 9 or NCLC 9 (for a maximum of 24 points under English language factor).</li>\r\n	<li>The IELTS equivalent to CLB 8 is 7.5, 6.5, 6.5 and 6.5 on Listening, Reading, Writing, and Speaking. The TEF equivalent to NCLC 8 is 280-297, 233-247, 349-370 and 349-370 on Listening, Reading, Writing, and Speaking, respectively. Getting these scores will mean that 5 points are awarded for each of the four language abilities, meaning that all candidates that meet these criteria can claim a maximum of 20 points.</li>\r\n	<li>The IELTS equivalent to CLB 9 is 8.0, 7.0 , 7.0 , and 7.0 on Listening, Reading, Writing, and Speaking. The TEF equivalent to NCLC 9 is 298-315, 248-262, 371-392 and 371-392 on Listening, Reading, Writing, and Speaking, respectively. This means that to claim 24 points under the English language factor, the applicant MUST claim AT LEAST 8.0, 7.0, 7.0, and 7.0 on Listening, Reading, Writing, and Speaking, respectively. 6 points are awarded for each of the four language abilities, meaning that all candidates that meet these criteria can claim a maximum of 24 points.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nOne can also have various combinations of scores and accordingly credit points under the factor. Just remember that the MINIMUM requirement of at least 6.0 should be met to qualify.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith specific reference to Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) under Express Entry points program, it will make sense for both the spouses to appear in the<strong> IELTS Test </strong>and provide score sheets. Higher the score in the ranking for both the spouses, more then number of points under CRS and higher will the application move into the overall rankings.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Second Official Language:</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe number of points awarded for proficiency in a second official language will be reduced from 8 to 4, making focusing on studying a single language a more viable strategy for those seeking to qualify for<strong> Immigration to Canada</strong>. Our understanding is that in almost all instances, French will be the second official language.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Age - Principal Applicant (Maximum 12 Points)</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe preferential age will be redefined from 18 to 35 bands under the recommended point&#39;s criteria, which will be allotted a maximum of 12 points. An applicant above 47 years and getting Zero points for age can still file a petition, if he/she meets the minimum pass-mark requirements of 67 under other selection factors.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>18 to 35 years - 12 points</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>After this age band, points are deducted on basis of age in years</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>36 years - 11 points</li>\r\n	<li>Age 37 years - 10 points</li>\r\n	<li>Age 38 years - 9 points</li>\r\n	<li>And so on till&nbsp;Age 46 years - 1 point</li>\r\n	<li>47 and above - 0 points&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Points for Employment Experience (Maximum 15 Points)</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nScore allocation</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 year - 9 points</li>\r\n	<li>2-3 years - 11 points</li>\r\n	<li>4-5 years - 13 points</li>\r\n	<li>6 years - 15 points</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Above allocation indicates the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minimum experience of at least a year, in an occupation on O, A and B category is a MUST. To review the list of occupations that fall under these 3 categories,</li>\r\n	<li>Higher the experience, more points the principal applicant can claim under the employment experience factor.</li>\r\n	<li>Clearly outlining ones experience profile - as per NOC descriptions - in one of the permitted occupations under O, A and B category will determine whether or not an application under Canada FSW will be accepted or not. Hence taking an experienced immigration consultants&#39; help will be useful for your all important life objective to immigrate to Canada. For a free of charge assessment, you can also simply send across your and (if applicable), the spousal resume to i<u>nfo@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</u> for immediate contact from our business executives.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Educational and Professional Qualifications (Maximum 25 Points)</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nUnder ECA (Educational Credential assessment), current educational and professional qualifications of the principal applicant will be assessed by a Canadian credential assessment agency. Such an assessment will confirm the equivalency of the principal applicant&#39;s qualifications with similar Canadian qualifications.&nbsp;Only the principal applicants getting positive assessment of their educational and professional qualifications will be permitted to file the application for permanent resident visa under federal skilled worker category.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe credential assessment has therefore, become single most important step in achieving ones&#39; dreams to immigrate to Canada as a skilled professional. Just like Australia, a professional presentation of one&#39;s&#39; academic, professional and related experience credentials will therefore become very important for anybody who wishes to file for a permanent resident visa application under federal skilled worker category. Taking help of a professional in meeting this requirement has thus become very important. For a free of charge assessment, you can also simply send across your and (if applicable), the spousal resume to info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;for immediate contact from our business executives.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<strong>Arranged Employment (Maximum 10 Points)</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter the implementation of the new procedural recommendations labor market opinion - LMO will be superseding Arranged Employment Opinion - AEO. Employers would need to apply to the HRSDC for an LMO. This will bring down events of fictitious job offers and promote credibility of the scheme, establish the validity of the job offers in light of labor pool goals, and offer escalated LMO procedure to employers having a strict adherence track record.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Adaptability (Maximum 10 Points)</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nA maximum score of 10 could be allocated to a migrant with employment experience in Canada.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOr Education in Canada can get up to 5 points,&nbsp;<br />\r\nOr Education AND experience in Canada can get up to 10 points!<br />\r\nOr&nbsp;Spousal education qualifications will no longer get any points but a spouse with CLB level 4 in English language can help the principal applicant 5 adaptability factor points! This also means that to claim bonus points for spouse; she will need to appear in the IELTS test.<br />\r\nOr Even a blood relation in Canada can help the principal applicant gain additional 5 points under the adaptability factor. The blood relation can be 18 years and above; and can be Father, Mother, Brother, Sister, Uncle, Aunt, Niece, Nephew. The blood relation can belong to either of the spouses and either of the parents.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Total marks are 100 and current pass-mark is 67 points. This selection criteria as well pass-mark may change without notice.</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Application Procedure for Federal Skilled Worker Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div>The steps from eligibility screening to Canadian PR under the FSW Program are outlined here.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 1: Determine Your Eligibility</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Whether you meet the minimum qualifications, use the above Federal Skilled Worker points calculator or the point grid to see if you can achieve a minimum of 67 points.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 2: Develop an Express Entry Profile</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>To construct your Express Entry profile, you must submit the three documents listed below to IRCC (Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada).</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A valid passport</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Evaluation of Educational Credentials (ECA)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Test Results for Language Proficiency</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Every applicant for an FSW Canada draw is evaluated for medical and criminal inadmissibility. So, in addition to these three documents, you must give the following:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; IRCC-recognized panel physician medical examination report</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Certificate of police clearance from a local police station</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Employment letters from former employers</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Before moving ahead, you should verify your CRS Score; if it is lower than the average cut-off score, an immigration specialist can advise you on how to raise it.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 3: Obtain an Invitation to Apply (ITA)</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>If an applicant is granted an ITA for Canadian PR, he or she will have 60 days to file an electronic Application for Permanent Residence (eAPR).</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 4: Review your e-application and Obtaining Canadian PR</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>A Canadian Immigration official will assess your application and notify you if additional information is needed. If everything checks out, your application will be granted and you will receive a confirmation of permanent residence (COPR) document.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Step 5: Apply for a PR card</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>After receiving your confirmation of status, you may apply for your PR card. If you go outside of Canada, you can use this card to prove your Canadian status.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>How Orange Global Consultancy Can Helps?</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Orange Global Consultancy</strong> is India&#39;s leading immigration consultant. Don&#39;t take our word for it; we have facts to support our claim.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Orange Global Consultancy provides a one-stop solution for all your visa requirements, including profile evaluation, documentation, application preparation, and post-visa services.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Don&rsquo;t wait. Start the visa application process now!</div>\r\n</div>', '', '221148378_Canada-immigration_378179980-scaled-1-768x452.jpeg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NDc=', 1, '2023-12-22 04:53:05'),
(48, 168, 'Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program', '<div>\r\n<p>The government of Canada introduced the Atlantic Immigration Pilot program in 2017 to address labor shortage needs in the Atlantic provinces of Canada- such as Nova Scotia, New Brunswick, Newfoundland and Labrador, and Prince Edward Island. This Canada Immigration&nbsp;program is a strategic approach to hire foreign workers for job positions they could not fill locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In association with its provincial government partners, the federal government will welcome over 7,000 skilled foreign workers and their families to the Atlantic Canada region by 2021 through this program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To qualify for the Atlantic Immigration Pilot program, you must have a valid job offer from one of the Atlantic Provinces in Canada. The program requires designated employers to identify and recruit skilled foreign professionals for the job vacancy. The program also aims to fuel these provinces&#39; population, build a skilled workforce, and boost the employment rates in the participating provinces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Usually, to get a Canadian job offer for immigration, the candidate must obtain a Labor Market Impact Assessment (LMIA) before applying for a work permit. The Atlantic immigration program has no requirement as the job offer must come through a designated employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The program focuses on five priority areas, which include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>skilled workforce and immigration;</li>\r\n	<li>innovation;</li>\r\n	<li>clean growth and climate change;</li>\r\n	<li>trade and investment; and</li>\r\n	<li>Infrastructure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There are three programs under the Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Atlantic Immigration Skilled Program (AISP)</li>\r\n	<li>Atlantic High Skilled Program (AHSP)</li>\r\n	<li>Atlantic International Graduate Program (AIGP)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Atlantic Immigration Pilot Program- Key Steps to Apply</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employer Designation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>First, Atlantic region employer must express an interest to use this program as a full-time pathway to recruit and retain foreign talent in Atlantic Canada.</li>\r\n	<li>Next, an employer must contact one of the participating settlement service providers and commit to preparing their workplace to welcome newcomers.</li>\r\n	<li>The employer applies to the province to become a designated employer for the program.</li>\r\n	<li>Atlantic province approves the employer&#39;s <strong>Canada PNP</strong>&nbsp;application</li>\r\n	<li>Employer starts looking for global candidates and selects them based on the eligibility criteria for the job position.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Endorsement</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The designated employer connects their selected candidates to the local settlement service provider for a needs assessment</li>\r\n	<li>The service provider will help the candidate draft a settlement plan for themselves and their family. The entire process is a part of needs assessment.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate sends a copy of the settlement plan to the designated employer.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate must wait for some days till the employer completes the formalities related to the provincial nomination. The assessment will be done based on the candidate&#39;s work experience, job offer, and a settlement plan.</li>\r\n	<li>In case of urgent job positions, candidates may also be eligible to apply for a temporary work permit. All they need is to show the job offer, letter of referral from the provincial government, and a commitment to apply for permanent residence in Canada.</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate will receive an endorsement letter once the province approves the application.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Immigration </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The candidate must officially apply for permanent residence in Canada to IRCC. The application must include the endorsement letter, job offer, and other relevant documents.</li>\r\n	<li>IRCC processes the application within six months or even less.</li>\r\n	<li>Selected applicants can migrate to Atlantic Canada with their families.</li>\r\n	<li>The designated employer supports the candidate&#39;s settlement in the province and also helps them in community integration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Other ways to immigrate to Atlantic Canada</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Atlantic Provinces in Canada also invite skilled foreign workers to live and work in the participating provinces via Provincial Nominee Programs (PNPs). The PNPs have invited thousands of skilled workers, temporary workers, international graduates, and business immigrants to Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of these programs are also linked with the Express Entry system, allowing interested candidates to express their interest in Canadian Immigration. These candidates can submit their profiles in the express entry and receive an invitation to apply based on their Comprehensive Ranking System Score (CRS).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To know more information, you can connect with us on 8336933522 or drop an email at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in. We will provide your evaluation results and chart out the best Canadian immigration pathway for you.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '183227991_Canada-immigration_378179980-scaled-1-768x452.jpeg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NDg=', 1, '2023-12-22 04:57:25'),
(49, 51, 'Canada Occupation Demand List 2023: Express Entry Eligible Occupation List for Skilled PR Migration', '<h2>National Occupational Classification List</h2>\r\n\r\n<div>Immigrant applicants with work experience in any skilled occupation are invited to apply for permanent residence in Canada through <strong>Canada Express Entry</strong>.&nbsp;system; but, expertise in a high-demand occupation in Canada may be advantageous at the province level.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>There are federal and provincial economic immigration routes to Canada, and each has its own work experience requirements.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The primary way for skilled immigrants to apply for a Canada PR Visa is through the Federal Skilled Worker Program (FSWP). To be eligible for this program, one of the major requirements is to have work experience in any one of the eligible occupations. The PR visa process is open to any qualified immigrant with the appropriate work experience in in-demand occupations.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Minimum Requirement for a Canada PR Visa</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>To apply for a PR visa for Canada, a person must meet at least the following requirements:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Have at least one year of continuous work experience or the equivalent in part-time work experience in one of the 347 eligible jobs listed in the National Occupational Classification (NOC) system within the last ten years;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Must be at least 18 years old;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Get at least 67 out of a possible 100 points on the FSWP assessment grid;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; IELTS score of at least 6 per band;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Must have enough money for the settlement;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Submit a Police Clearance Certificate (PCC) and get a medical checkup;</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Choosing the right occupation is vital to the Canada Immigration application. Your occupation holds the critical component to be eligible and score high points for the selection. All the eligible occupations for <strong>Canada PR </strong>are classified into Skilled Levels such as &lsquo;0&rsquo;, &lsquo;A,&rsquo; &lsquo;B,&rsquo; &lsquo;C&rsquo; &amp; &lsquo;D&rsquo;. These classifications have a different impact on the eligibility of the applicants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Level &lsquo;0&rsquo; &ndash; Managerial Occupations<br />\r\n&bull; Level &lsquo;A&rsquo; &ndash; Professional Occupations<br />\r\n&bull; Level &lsquo;B&rsquo; &ndash; Technical Occupations<br />\r\n&bull; Level &lsquo;C&rsquo; &ndash; Semi &amp; Low-Skilled Occupations<br />\r\n&bull; Level &lsquo;D&rsquo; &ndash; Semi &amp; Low-Skilled Occupations</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Currently, the occupations under Level &lsquo;0&rsquo;, &lsquo;A,&rsquo; and &lsquo;B&rsquo; are considered for the <strong>Canada immigration</strong>&nbsp;process. Below is the list of Open Occupations for Canada Immigration:</p>\r\n\r\n<div>At the end: mention the below one.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Why Choose Orange Global Consultancy ?</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Orange Global Consultancy is the top immigration consultant in India, combining 100% transparency with Experience, Expertise, and Excellence to guarantee success. Listed below are the primary reasons why we are the best immigration consultant in India.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Complete documentation and provide document alternatives based on our significant experience.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Application to various programs to obtain a PR visa as quickly as possible, as well as post-arrival services to assist with settling into your new country.</div>', '', '919165357_910305597_680970_viaentry1552290941.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NDk=', 1, '2023-12-22 05:07:15'),
(50, 52, 'Nova Scotia High Demand Occupation List of 2023', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>Nova Scotia PNP Occupation List</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With thriving opportunities in service sectors precisely in health and education industries, Nova Scotia offers enough opportunities for work to the highly-skilled. Having stated that there&rsquo;s enough employment gap to be filled in service sectors, there are some occupation which need immediate attention. And skilled workers who meet the requirements of<strong> Nova Scotia PNP</strong> can contribute positively towards building the future of the province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the below table, you&rsquo;ll come across the most prominent jobs of recent times in Nova Scotia. The Nova Scotia Occupation Demand List is classified under the National Occupations Classification (NOC) meaning that if your job falls in any of these occupation codes with enough experience and qualification to substantiate your profession, there is a good chance you might qualify for <strong>Canada immigration</strong>. But however, to apply for permanent residence via Nova Scotia Occupation List, the applying individual must have more than one year of work experience with educational credentials in the same field.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processing Time of Nova Scotia In-demand Occupation </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nova Scotia Express Entry<strong>&nbsp;</strong>&amp; PNP helps employers meet their labour shortage by enabling them to hire enough international workers and students from the employment pool. The time taken in processing applications with one of the occupations in-demand list depends on the strength of your profile. If you&rsquo;re thorough with the documentation needed for the immigration process then you might have a better chance of receiving a faster approval, but ideally the standard time varies from 3-6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The objective of the <strong>Business Immigration Programm</strong>&nbsp;is to encourage investment and employment in Canada through the migration of people who have the ability to successfully establish or invest in a business in Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can choose your occupation from the Nova Scotia Occupation Demand List, and as a pioneer Immigration consultancy. Orange Global Consultancy take pride in providing you with accurate guidance on your Provincial nominee program and <strong>Canada PR Visa</strong> application. To Know more about Canada PNP Programs and related Canada immigration news, get in touch with us at: info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in or on <strong>(+91) 8336933522.</strong></p>\r\n</div>', '', '566773329_Canada-immigration_378179980-scaled-1-768x452.jpeg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTA=', 1, '2023-12-22 05:15:58'),
(51, 53, 'Alberta PNP Demand Occupation List 2023', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>About the Alberta PNP</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberta &ndash; one of Canada&rsquo;s most scenic provinces, and home to the bustling urban city of Calgary &ndash; has emerged as a popular immigration hub amongst foreign nationals seeking to enhance their quality of life and enjoy the rewarding benefits of permanent residence in Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>Alberta Immigration Nominee Program&nbsp;</strong>(AINP) is managed by the provincial government in collaboration with the federal government. The Alberta government nominates qualified foreign nationals to permanently reside in the province &ndash; with eligible family members, if any.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Subsequently, nominees must apply for permanent residence to Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada &ndash; either through a paper based process or online via the <strong>Canada Express Entry System</strong>. Aspirants can obtain a nomination by applying through any of the following categories:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alberta Opportunity Stream</li>\r\n	<li>Alberta Express Entry Stream</li>\r\n	<li>Self-Employed Farmer Stream</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Eligibility Requirements for the Alberta Provincial Nominee Program</strong>\r\n\r\n	<p>The eligibility requirements and application procedures are different for each stream. For instance, the Express Entry stream requires candidates to demonstrate their ability to contribute to Alberta&rsquo;s economic development or showcase strong ties to the province, and create an Express Entry profile by fulfilling the requirements of the relevant federal <strong>Canada Express Entry Process</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>If you wish to apply for Alberta PNP directly from the federal Express Entry system, then you must meet the following eligibility criteria. Alberta may select the most eligible applicants and issue them a Notification of Interest letter.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>Successful applicants with a Notification of Interest letter from Alberta must send a copy of the letter along with other documents to the Alberta Advantage Immigration Program (AAIP) within two weeks of receiving it.</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>You may receive a Notification of Interest letter from Alberta, if:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>you have an active Express Entry profile</li>\r\n		<li>You have the work experience and skills in one of the occupations that are in demand in Alberta and support provincial development.</li>\r\n		<li>you are genuinely interested in migrating to Alberta</li>\r\n		<li>you have a minimum Comprehensive Ranking System score of 300</li>\r\n		<li>meet the basic eligibility criteria of at least one of the federal economic migration programs:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Federal skilled worker</li>\r\n			<li>Canadian experience class</li>\r\n			<li>Federal skilled trades</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Factors that boost your chances of receiving an NOI from Alberta</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fulfilling one of the following factors may increase your likelihood of receiving a Notification of Interest letter:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>secure a valid job offer from Alberta</li>\r\n	<li>you are a graduate of a Canadian post-secondary institution</li>\r\n	<li>you have a parent, child, brother or sister who is a permanent resident living in Alberta, or a Canadian citizen living in Alberta</li>\r\n	<li>you can speak French</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Alberta Occupation in-Demand List 2023</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Skilled workers applying for <strong>Canada Immigration</strong>&nbsp;under the Alberta Opportunity Stream must ensure that their occupation is in-demand in Alberta. The Alberta Occupation in Demand List indicates skills shortages in Alberta&rsquo;s job market, which cannot be satisfied by the residents and citizens currently living in the province. Thus, the AINP invites overseas skilled workers to fulfill these shortages. Most occupations listed under National Occupational Classification Skill Type 0, or Skill Level A, B, C or D, are in-demand in Alberta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Advantages of Applying for the Alberta PNP through Orange Global Consultancy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As an intending migrant seeking <strong>Canada Permanent Residence</strong>, your application must be represented by the best immigration consultants, who can provide genuine guidance and unwavering support throughout the process. When you sign up with Orange Global Consultancy, you instantly gain access to&nbsp;years of industry experience, a team of&nbsp;immigration experts, the most credible authorized representation, exclusive international affiliations, and a holistic range of premium services specially curated to provide a necessary boost to your PR visa application</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '260020015_Canada-immigration_378179980-scaled-1-768x452.jpeg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTE=', 1, '2023-12-22 05:24:54'),
(52, 54, 'Manitoba in-Demand Occupation List 2023', '<p><strong>About Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The MPNP looks out for skilled workers who have chosen an occupation mentioned in the Manitoba in Demand Occupation List an are basically based on the labor needs, shortages and economic requirements of the Canadian province of Manitoba. Recent graduates, skilled workers, businesspeople and their families who possess the true intention to successfully settle and economically establish themselves as permanent residents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If business is what you are looking for then the <strong>Monitoba Provincial Nominee Program Business</strong>&nbsp;(MPNPB) also known as the Business Investor Stream (BIS) permits the recruitment and nomination of qualified business investors and entrepreneurs around the world who have the intent and ability to purchase businesses in Manitoba. If you are a skilled worker, working in Manitoba can opens up tremendous opportunities for you and your family.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Manitoba PNP also conducts Expression of Interest <strong>Canada Express Entry Draw</strong>&nbsp;for candidates applying for nomination via its Express entry pathways.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility Requirement for Manitoba Occupation List</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Here are the following criteria for proving occupational eligibility for Manitoba Immigration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You must have a past education, training, work experience and any applicable certification, license or registration (regulatory requirements) as well.</li>\r\n	<li>You can also demonstrate past connection to Manitoba through education or job offer.</li>\r\n	<li>As a prospective applicant you must have proficiency in English to qualify for <strong>Canada PR Visa</strong>&nbsp;via MPNP.</li>\r\n	<li>You must score enough points in Manitoba immigration points calculator.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>They must get a letter of advice from provincial authorities.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>NOC Requirements &ndash; needs to be fulfilled to assess whether or skills and potential are conducive for long term employment as well as growth in career, that in turn will assist in the development of the local labor market in Manitoba.</li>\r\n	<li>Must provide detailed description of duties, skills, talents and work settings in the Canadian economy as mentioned in the National Occupation Classification 2011 (NOC code).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Manitoba in Demand Occupation List</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since Manitoba immigration program choses suitable skilled workers and professionals via MPNP meaning that these candidates must hold the skills, qualifications, and a full-time job experience to be able to work in the labor market of the province. Manitoba in Demand Occupation List is an updated list of relevant high demand occupations as per the labor shortages and economic requirements of the Manitoba local labor market. This list is updated on a regular basis as per the changing labor demands.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Why choose Orange Global Consultancy as your Immigration partner?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Immigration is a life-changing decision, make sure you do it right. With over years of industry leading experience, we have helped thousands of skilled workers, students, families, and entrepreneurs realise their Canadian dream. We understand the entire immigration process for student, business, and temporary, and permanent visa applications. With us you get:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Accredited and authorized Immigration Consultant registered with ICCRC</li>\r\n	<li>Personalized and dedicated professional service</li>\r\n	<li>Efficient, confidential, and transparent services with regular follow-ups</li>\r\n	<li>Dedicated team of experts with years of experience in the immigration industry</li>\r\n	<li>Expert at handling the most complex cases.</li>\r\n	<li>Honest and legal case representation</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '936336111_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTI=', 1, '2023-12-25 22:47:19'),
(53, 55, 'Quebec Occupation in-Demand List 2023', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>About Quebec Immigration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quebec is one of Canada&rsquo;s most coveted immigration destinations, owing to its vibrant culture, diverse population, metropolitan lifestyle, urban infrastructure, lucrative job market and ample scope for business innovation. Qualified candidates can successfully immigrate to Quebec through any of the following pathways:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Quebec Skilled Worker Program</li>\r\n	<li>Quebec Investor Program</li>\r\n	<li>Quebec Entrepreneur Program</li>\r\n	<li>Quebec Self-Employed Worker Program</li>\r\n	<li>Program for Refugees Abroad</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Quebec Occupation in Demand List 2023</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Skilled workers applying under the QSWP must ensure that their primary occupation is featured on the Quebec Occupation in Demand List 2023, which indicates all the skills shortages in Quebec&rsquo;s labor market that cannot be filled by the local population. Thus, qualified foreign nationals are invited to fill these vacancies. The list is regularly updated, and is one of the major eligibility requirements for skilled immigration to Quebec.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Three new pathways added for Quebec immigration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quebec Immigration Ministry released a new mandate which entails the introduction of three new immigration pathways for the aspirants. Each program will allow the selection of maximum 550 applicants and their family members annually. Below are the programs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>The permanent immigration pilot program for workers in food processing</strong> &ndash; The PR pathway will be for temporary foreign workers who have jobs in the food processing sector in Quebec. Program will commence on March 24, 2021.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The permanent immigration pilot program for orderlies</strong> &ndash; It is for applicants as orderlies to fill critical labour shortage in this field. Program will commence on March 31, 2021.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The permanent immigration pilot program for workers in the AI, information technologies and visual effects (IT/VE) sectors</strong> &ndash; There are two streams: AI and IT/VE for tech professionals which will come into effect on April 22, 2021.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Application Process for Permanent Residence in Quebec</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Each immigration pathway has a distinct set of eligibility <strong>Quebec requirements and application Procedures</strong>. The most popular route to permanent residence is the <strong>Quebec Skilled Worker Program</strong>&nbsp;(QSWP), which unfolds in two stages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Stage 1 &ndash; Obtain the Quebec Selection Certificate</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aspirants must submit an online Expression of Interest through the&nbsp;<em>Arrima</em>&nbsp;portal. The most highly eligible candidates will receive an invitation to apply for permanent selection from the Minist&egrave;re. Within 60 days of receiving the invitation, the candidate must apply for permanent selection to the Minist&egrave;re &ndash; online via&nbsp;<em>Mon Projet Qu&eacute;bec</em>. If approved, the candidate receives a Quebec Selection Certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Stage 2 &ndash; Apply for Permanent Residence</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon obtaining the selection certificate, a candidate must apply for the <strong>Canada Permanent Resident Visa&nbsp;</strong>to the federal immigration authority &ndash; Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada &ndash; as a Quebec-selected skilled worker. After due verification, IRCC may award a PR visa to the applicant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about Quebec In demand occupation list you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy&nbsp;and one of the most experienced immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '377011514_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTM=', 1, '2023-12-25 23:05:17');
INSERT INTO `cms` (`id`, `menu_id`, `title`, `description`, `video`, `image`, `url`, `status`, `created_at`) VALUES
(54, 56, 'Canada PNP 2023 - Provincial Nominee Programs for Skilled Workers', '<div>\r\n<h2>CANADA PROVINCIAL NOMINEE PROGRAMS</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Provincial Nominee Programs permits the provinces and territories of Canada to nominate skilled professional workers who want to immigrate, eventually settle down in Canada and contribute effectively to the local economy in a fruitful manner.&nbsp;Canadian provinces and territories who wish to participate in this immigration program, sign an agreement with Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC). This pact lets the provinces select applicants based on their respective requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nCanada&rsquo;s PNP Programs essentially accommodates prospective immigrant filing a petition through a specific province or territory in Canada and the related province has the legitimate right to nominate individuals and let them apply for permanent residence via the Canadian Provincial Nomination Program. Qu&eacute;bec is an exception to these programs as the province has its own pre-defined cluster of selection criteria.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe continued influence from The Citizenship and Immigration Canada&nbsp;(CIC) had made possible for many provinces and territories to settle down into a treaty with respect to skilled immigration agreements involving the particular requirement of recruiters and capital investment necessities for each geographical region. Hence a number of provinces in the nation have acquired their own specific business immigration schemes that are focused to motivate trained manpower to settle in these provinces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each and every province or territory of Canada has its own exclusive Provincial Nomination Programs, suitably molded to positively cater to the specific requirement of the province or territory, to draw business individuals, investors, and/or qualified manpower. The aspirant will require zeroing in on the specific Canadian province that he/she wishes to move to, through the provincial nominee schemes (as mentioned below):<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alberta Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>New Brunswick Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Newfoundland and Labrador Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Northwest Territories Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Nunavut Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Ontario Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Prince Edward Island (PEI) Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Quebec Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Saskatchewan Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n	<li>Yukon Provincial Nominee Program</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In one&rsquo;s own right, as a potential aspirant to the Maple Leaf Country you would be given a nomination from the administration of appropriate provinces, which is though subject to an obtainable employment offer from a provincial recruiter/job-provider. To be eligible to shift to the nation as a provincial nominee, you must present an application to the involved province or territory wherein you hope to stay, through its nomination course. For receiving a PR state of any explicit Canadian Province, you need to get an appraisal for your profile by the provincial visa and immigration authorities.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you have an invited to apply and a confirmed job offer from a provincial employer, Orange Global Consaultancy would lead your application through rest of the processes such as filing for various approvals from Human Resource Canada and provincial government and making certain that you follow provincial nomination procedures applicable through the skilled migration scheme. It will be succeeded by due preparation, and submitting your petition under the applicable federal submission procedure meant for the provincial nominee candidates.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOrange Global Consultancy and its certified authorized representatives, have several years of relevant experience in supervising and safeguarding the needs of the prospective provincial general skilled immigrants, and also the provincial investor and business class applicants.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith a view to submitting anapplication, through the Provincial Nominee Program (PNP), the candidates should, among others:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Havereceived a nomination from a specific Canadian province or territory, and afterwards submit a submission to the Citizenship and Immigration Canada<strong> </strong>(CIC), to obtain the nation&rsquo;s cherished <strong>Permanent</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Resident Canada</strong>&nbsp;position.</li>\r\n	<li>Each and every concerned province &amp; territory has its own particular nomination guidelines, and it could amend these without any prior notice. Given this, it is vital that the aspirants check province&rsquo;s&amp; territory&rsquo;s websites for the latest updates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\n<strong>How to Apply Canada PNP</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the above criterions are met, you are required to present a submission to the CIC for PR, as soon as a province or territory acknowledges your profile.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFollow these major steps to submit your submission for provincial nomination under the Express entry pool.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>File your application into the express entry pool.</li>\r\n	<li>File your application with the qualifying province.</li>\r\n	<li>Wait for confirmation for intent to nominate from the province.</li>\r\n	<li>File the application/provide required documents to the provincial agency.</li>\r\n	<li>Received provincial nomination</li>\r\n	<li>Update the information related to nomination the pool application.</li>\r\n	<li>Wait for invite.</li>\r\n	<li>File on-line permanent residence application with CIC, along with all documents and required fee.</li>\r\n	<li>Wait for file transfer to nearest visa post and complete rest of the formalities including medical and visa issuance.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the key benefits of applying to a Canada PNP program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Provincial Nomination speeds the application processing for your <strong>Canada PR</strong>&nbsp;will be processed quickly.</li>\r\n	<li>There is no Job Offer requirement for the PNP Canada which is another beneficial factor to consider</li>\r\n	<li>Some PNPs are linked with the express entry stream, thus offering the quickest way to settle in Canada.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>After receiving the PNP Nomination candidates are authorized to live and work in Canada for as long as they want.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant can sponsor relatives for a temporary and permanent stay after the Permanent Residency.</li>\r\n	<li>Canadian permanent residents have the access to travel throughout the country without any restrictions</li>\r\n	<li>Canadian citizenship can be easily attained once they live in Canada for the necessary amount of time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Express Entry Vs PNP Canada- Which is best to apply Canada PR? </strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Express Entry</strong> is the most common pathway that all the aspiring candidates choose for their Canada PR. If a candidate could not meet the score in accordance with the latest draw then he/she has another opportunity to receive Permanent residency through Canada PNP program. It is the most convenient way for the immigration as there is no points regulations and no additional requirements.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Which PNP require lowest IELTS score? </strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nSaskatchewan and Manitoba are the provinces which has no strict regulations for Language Proficiency wherein they accept the applications with the minimum CLB (Canadian Language Benchmark) 4.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe PNP professionals of Orange Global Consultancy would advocate which plan would be best for our customers, as per their specific case studies, thus bringing the finest option before them. The CIC clearly describes which immigration specialist can represent a petition on the behalf of their customers to the body. The CIC calls them sanctioned agents, even as the Regulated Canadian Immigration agents who happen to be members in good standing of the Immigration Consultants of Canada Regulatory Council are among them. In case you are signing-up an immigration advisor who charges money for his professional services to be on the safer side, make certain that he is a certified agent to represent your case with the CIC &amp; other government bureaus of the nation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PNP immigrants find good jobs in Canada</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Research by Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC), Statistics Canada revealed that immigrants who come to Canada through provincial nominee programs find better job opportunities and have stronger labor market outcomes. These newcomers also have the ability to earn high wages and demonstrate an excellent labor market participation with their skills, experience, and sheer determination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why PNP immigrants are successful in Canada?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates under PNP immigration streams are selected based on their calibre to meet the local labour market needs of a specific province and territory.</li>\r\n	<li>These migrants also high levels of human capital, such as strong language skills, impressive educational background, work experience, and strong networking skills.</li>\r\n	<li>PNP selection criteria often screens for Canadian work experience, Canadian education, and pre-arranged employment in Canada.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The goal of Orange Global Consultancy is to fruitfully make you well established in Canada through one of the PNP streams.&nbsp;In your favored province. In case you wish to<strong> Immigration to canada</strong>, and are eager to get established in the country that too in the province of your choice, send across your CV to info@orangeglobalconsultancy.</p>\r\n</div>', '', '984946016_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTQ=', 1, '2023-12-26 00:42:48'),
(55, 57, 'Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP)', '<div>\r\n<p>Ontario is the most progressive and developed province in Canada due to large corporations and multi-national startups. Toronto is the origin of all the progress, technological advancement, and growth. The majority of the people wish to settle in this particular province. And, it has a <strong>Provincial Nominee Program</strong>&nbsp;to boost immigration to this region. Foreign skilled workers can choose the program to move to Ontario with their families by meeting the eligibility requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>What are the pathways under Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are three categories under the OINP:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Employer Job Offer category &ndash; </strong>The program is for those skilled workers and international students who possess a permanent job offer from an Ontario employer. There are three sub-streams:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Foreign Worker stream:</strong> For Foreign skilled workers with the job offer</li>\r\n	<li><strong>International Student stream:</strong> For International graduates in Ontario with the job offer</li>\r\n	<li><strong>In-Demand Skills stream:</strong> For intermediate skilled workers in specific work sectors - construction, agriculture, trucking, and personal support workers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Human Capital category &ndash; </strong>The program is most popular among skilled foreign workers and international graduates. Anyone with <strong>Canada Express Entry.</strong>&nbsp;Profile and valuable work experience, education, language skills can apply for the program. It has two sub-streams:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Ontario&#39;s Express Entry:</strong> Express Entry has three streams:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Human Capital Priorities Stream: </strong>For skilled foreign workers</li>\r\n	<li><strong>French-Speaking Skilled Worker Stream: </strong>For skilled foreign workers with proficiency in French</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Skilled Trades Stream: </strong>For workers with experience in Ontario in a trade occupation</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>International Graduates (Master&#39;s &amp; Ph.D.):</strong> For International Master&#39;s and Ph.D. degree holders from Ontario</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Business category &ndash; </strong>For foreign entrepreneurs who wish to establish a new or buy an existing business in Ontario. It has only one stream:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Entrepreneur Stream: </strong>For the foreign entrepreneurs who can invest and establish or purchase a business in the province. The applicants need to meet other requirements as well.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the eligibility requirements for Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (Skilled)?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must have an active Express Entry profile in the CIC account for <strong>Canada Immigration</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Have minimum Bachelor&#39;s degree evaluated by Educational Credential Assessment (ECA) report for eligibility.</li>\r\n	<li>Must have minimum language level Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) 7 in English or French proved by a recognized language test.</li>\r\n	<li>Possess a minimum of 12 months of continuous full-time employment in a National Occupation Classification (NOC) level 0, A, or B occupation in the last five years.</li>\r\n	<li>Must demonstrate the genuine intention to live in Ontario with the family</li>\r\n	<li>Have a sufficient amount of settlement funds (legally acquired) for the initial stay</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the eligibility requirements for Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (Entrepreneurs)?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must have a minimum of two years of full-time business management experience in the last five years.</li>\r\n	<li>A business owner must have had an active role in the business management and owned a minimum of one-third of the business.</li>\r\n	<li>A senior manager can also apply, but he/she must have senior decision-making responsibilities in the business</li>\r\n	<li>The minimum net-worth should be CAD 800,000 (INR 4.83 Crore) for the business in the Greater Toronto Area (City of Toronto and Durham, Halton, York, and Peel regions). The minimum net worth of firms outside of the Greater Toronto Area is CAD 400,000 (INR 2.42 Crore).</li>\r\n	<li>The minimum investment should be CAD 600,000 (INR 3.62 Crore) and possess one-third of the equity in the business for the proposed business in the Greater Toronto Area. The minimum investment is CAD 200,000 (INR 1.21 Crore) with one-third equity for firms outside of the Greater Toronto Area.</li>\r\n	<li>Generate employment for a minimum of 2 citizens or permanent residents for the business within the Greater Toronto Area. And create a minimum of 1 job for the company outside Greater Toronto Area or business in the ICT or digital communications sector.</li>\r\n	<li>If you intend to purchase an existing business, you need to conduct an exploratory visit to the province. You must use 10% of the personal investment to improve the business and retain all the company&#39;s existing employees.</li>\r\n	<li>Must have minimum language level Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) 4 in English or French proved by a recognized language test.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the process of the Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (Skilled)?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get your academic credentials evaluated by assessment authorities</li>\r\n	<li>Score high points on the English language proficiency test</li>\r\n	<li>Have sufficient funds and demonstrate genuine intention to reside in the province</li>\r\n	<li>Meet the eligibility points requirement of 67 under the <strong>Canada immigration Points Calculator</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the expression of interest in the Express Entry System</li>\r\n	<li>Choose Ontario&#39;s Express Entry Human Capital Priorities Stream and create an account in the one-key account.</li>\r\n	<li>Create a profile in the OINP e-Filing Portal</li>\r\n	<li>Click on the file number beside the Human Capital Priorities Stream to begin your application</li>\r\n	<li>Upload all the documents and apply OINP</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the process of the Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (Entrepreneurs)?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Under the checklist and arrange all the documents to register an online Expression of Interest</li>\r\n	<li>Complete an EOI registration form along with the Self-Declared and Business Concept Score</li>\r\n	<li>Upload all the documents and submit the Express of Interest application by mail</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the online application fee of CAD 3500 (INR 2.12 Lac)</li>\r\n	<li>To complete the application assessment, attend the mandatory interview with the authority</li>\r\n	<li>If your application is approved, sign a performance agreement to demonstrate your commitments to invest and generate employment</li>\r\n	<li>You will receive a Temporary Work Permit support letter that will allow you to establish a business in Ontario</li>\r\n	<li>After incorporating and managing your business in Ontario, you will be eligible for a provincial nomination for permanent residence</li>\r\n	<li>Successful nominees will receive permanent residence within six months of the nomination</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the documents required for Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Photograph</li>\r\n	<li>Passport copies</li>\r\n	<li>Education degrees (ECA report)</li>\r\n	<li>Language Test Results</li>\r\n	<li>Employment documents (Reference Letters)</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of settlement funds</li>\r\n	<li>Resume/CV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the application fee and processing times of the Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Application Fee&ndash; CAD 1500 (INR 91,000) &ndash; Skilled, CAD 3500 (INR 2.12 Lac) - Entrepreneurs</li>\r\n	<li>Estimated Processing Times &ndash; 60 to 90 days (Skilled), 12 to 15 months (Entrepreneurs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you wish to attaind<strong> Canada immigration</strong> via Ontario PNP, you can register for our free immigration counseling and guidance. For more details, you can write an email at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in, or you can also choose to call us on <u>(+91)-8336933522.</u></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '957225121_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTU=', 1, '2023-12-26 00:55:04'),
(56, 58, 'Nova Scotia PNP for Skilled Professionals via Regional Labour Market Demand Stream', '<div>\r\n<p>Launched in 2003, the Nova Scotia Nominee Program (NSNP) allows the provincial government to address the economic and labor market needs of the province. Ever since its introduction, the program has been able to garner the attention of so many migrants seeking to migrate to Canada. Due to the province&rsquo;s booming economy and high-quality living, immigration to Nova Scotia has tripled in the last few years, all thanks to the introduction of the Atlantic Immigration Pilot (AIP) in 2017.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It would surprise you to know that the retention rate in Nova Scotia is more than 70% and that the province is highly lauded for its safe and welcoming environment for newcomers.&nbsp; The AINP and PNP pathways have helped the provincial government focus more on inviting skilled immigrants and making it easier for international graduates and temporary workers to apply for permanent residency,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, the provincial government of Nova Scotia also runs a &lsquo;Study and Stay&rsquo; program to help international students from India, China, and the Philippines stay and find job opportunities in Nova Scotia after they graduate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicants who fulfill the basic eligibility requirements of one of the streams can be nominated for permanent migration to Nova Scotia, with a processing time of three months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program is one of the most popular pathways to migrate to Canada. The program allows skilled foreign workers and recently graduated international students to live and work in Nova Scotia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The provincial government of Nova Scotia runs the following programs to invite skilled immigrants:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Nova Scotia Labor Market Priorities</li>\r\n	<li>Labor Market Priorities for Physicians</li>\r\n	<li>Physician</li>\r\n	<li>Entrepreneur</li>\r\n	<li>International Graduate Entrepreneur</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled Worker</li>\r\n	<li>Occupations-in-demand</li>\r\n	<li>Nova Scotia Experience- Express Entry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The program only invites workers who have the necessary skills and experience to contribute to the provincial economy. Nova Scotia is an immigration-friendly province featuring a comprehensive ranking system to filter candidates across various streams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program- Streams</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Nova Scotia Labor Market Priorities- </strong>The program selects eligible applicants through the federal express entry system who meet the local labor market needs. The government sends nominations to individuals who meet the minimum work-experience requirements and show sufficient funds to establish themselves in Nova Scotia successfully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be 21-55 years of age.</li>\r\n	<li>Be able to secure a valid full-time permanent job offer from an employer in Nova Scotia.</li>\r\n	<li>Have at least one year of professional work experience in the related job. Semi-skilled or low-skilled workers must demonstrate a minimum of six months of work experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Have a high-school diploma.</li>\r\n	<li>Have the training, skills, and accreditation for the job.</li>\r\n	<li>Prove language ability equal to Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) Level 5 if you are a skilled worker. For low-skilled workers, meeting CLB level 4 would get the invite.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Show sufficient financial sources and funds to settle in Nova Scotia.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Labor Market Priorities for Physicians- </strong>The stream is designed for Physicians who wish to migrate to Nova Scotia through the federal Express Entry system. The pathway is only available for physicians who have secured a letter of approval from the Nova Scotia Health Authority or the IWK Health Centre and receive a Letter of Interest from the Nova Scotia Office of Immigration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have an approved opportunity from the NSHA or IWK as either a general practitioner and family physician (NOC 3112) or a specialist physician (NOC 3111);</li>\r\n	<li>Provide a copy of a signed Return for Service Agreement with the Nova Scotia Department of Health and Wellness indicating commitment to live and work in Nova Scotia for a minimum period of two years;</li>\r\n	<li>Receive a Letter of Interest from the Nova Scotia Nominee Program within the Express Entry system;</li>\r\n	<li>Submit your application within 30 calendar days of the date on which your Letter of Interest was issued;</li>\r\n	<li>Meet the minimum work-experience requirements of the Express Entry stream for which you have qualified;</li>\r\n	<li>Demonstrate sufficient funds to establish yourself and your family in Nova Scotia successfully.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The physician stream assists the provincial authorities in hiring general practitioners, family physicians, and specialist physicians to live and work in Nova Scotia. The stream aims at supporting the NSHA and IWK to recruit and retain physicians with the required skills for positions that they could not fill with a permanent resident or Canadian citizen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be signed and dated by a person authorized to hire physicians at the NSHA or IWK</li>\r\n	<li>Be signed and dated by the applicant who is accepting the opportunity</li>\r\n	<li>Indicate eligibility for licensure with the College of Physicians and Surgeons of NS</li>\r\n	<li>Indicate that the applicant is eligible to apply for privileges and credentials with NSHA and the IWK</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entrepreneur- </strong>The pathway aims to welcome experienced business owners or senior managers to Nova Scotia and allow them to set up a business in the province. With this stream, entrepreneurs can establish a new business or buy an existing one. After operating the business successfully for a year, the entrepreneur may apply for permanent resident status.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be 21 years of age or older;</li>\r\n	<li>Be genuinely interested in living permanently in Nova Scotia while owning and actively managing a business in Nova Scotia;</li>\r\n	<li>Have a net worth of at least CAD 600,000;</li>\r\n	<li>Be able to invest at least CAD 150,000 of your own money in establishing a business in Nova Scotia;</li>\r\n	<li>Have at least three years&rsquo; experience actively managing and owning a business (1/3 ownership minimum) or more than five years&rsquo; experience in a senior business management role;</li>\r\n	<li>Have a score of at least five on the Canadian Language Benchmark</li>\r\n	<li>Submit an Expression of Interest</li>\r\n	<li>Receive an Invitation to Apply from the Nova Scotia Office of Immigration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>International Graduate Entrepreneur- </strong>The stream is for the recent international graduates of Nova Scotia who intend to settle in Nova Scotia permanently. However, to do so, they must have started or bought a business in the province and operated it for at least one year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be genuinely interested in settling in the province while carrying out business activities in Nova Scotia;</li>\r\n	<li>have at least one year&rsquo;s continuous experience actively managing and owning your current Nova Scotia business (33.33% ownership minimum);</li>\r\n	<li>Have completed a degree or diploma after at least two academic years of full-time, in-person study at a university in Nova Scotia or the Nova Scotia Community College;</li>\r\n	<li>Have a valid post-graduation work permit;</li>\r\n	<li>Have a score of at least seven on the Canadian Language Benchmark</li>\r\n	<li>Complete an online&nbsp;Expression of Interest&nbsp;and</li>\r\n	<li>Secure an Invitation to Apply from the provincial government.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Skilled Worker- </strong>the skilled worker stream allows employers in Nova Scotia to hire and retain foreign talent in the province. Foreign skilled workers and international graduates are eligible for this program. An employer can employ workers for job positions for which no local talent is available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have a full-time permanent job offer from a Nova Scotia employer;</li>\r\n	<li>Have one year of work experience related to the job.</li>\r\n	<li>Be 21 to 55 years old;</li>\r\n	<li>Have a high school diploma;</li>\r\n	<li>Have the appropriate training, skills, and accreditation for the job;</li>\r\n	<li>Prove language ability equal to Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) Level 5 if you are a skilled worker.</li>\r\n	<li>Show enough financial resources to settle in Nova Scotia successfully.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Occupations in Demand- </strong>This pathway targets individuals working across professions in massive demand in Nova Scotia. If your occupation is in demand in Nova Scotia, you may be eligible to apply for this stream.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have a full-time permanent job offer from a Nova Scotia employer in either NOC 3413 (Nurse Aides, orderlies, and patient service associates) or NOC 7511 (Transport truck drivers);</li>\r\n	<li>Have one year of work experience related to the job;</li>\r\n	<li>Be 21 to 55 years old;</li>\r\n	<li>Have a high school diploma;</li>\r\n	<li>Have the appropriate training, skills, and/or accreditation for the job;</li>\r\n	<li>Prove language ability equal to Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) Level 4 even if your first language is English or French;</li>\r\n	<li>Show enough financial resources to settle in Nova Scotia successfully.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Nova Scotia Experience- Express Entry- </strong>the pathway is created for highly skilled individuals planning to live and work in Nova Scotia. To apply, applicants must have at least one year of experience working in Nova Scotia in a high skilled occupation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>have at least one year of work experience in Nova Scotia;</li>\r\n	<li>be 21 to 55 years old;</li>\r\n	<li>have a Canadian high school credential or equivalent;</li>\r\n	<li>Prove language ability in English or French on the Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB).</li>\r\n	<li>have a profile in Canada&rsquo;s Express Entry&nbsp;system</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents Required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will need several documents to complete your application. You will also have to get documents from third parties such as educational institutions and governments to complete your application. Some of them are described as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Documents related to your job offer</li>\r\n	<li>Documents related to your work experience. To prove that you have the work experience and skills needed for the job, you must include letters of reference from your employers.</li>\r\n	<li>a copy of your high school diploma</li>\r\n	<li>copies of the licenses or certificates required for the job you have been offered, if needed</li>\r\n	<li>IELTS test results</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of passports, which must include the following:\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li>the passport number</li>\r\n		<li>the date of issue and expiry</li>\r\n		<li>the photo of the passport holder</li>\r\n		<li>the name of the passport holder as well as their date and place of birth</li>\r\n		<li>any changes to the passport holder&rsquo;s name, date of birth, or other identifying information</li>\r\n		<li>any changes to the passport&rsquo;s expiry date</li>\r\n		<li>any visas or visits to Canada</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Documents related to your spouse and children</li>\r\n	<li>Banking statements from the past three months showing all account balances and transaction history</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processing time </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The processing time for Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program can be three months or more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about&nbsp;Nova Scotia Provincial Nomination Program&nbsp;you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy and one of the most experienced immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '915933908_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTY=', 1, '2023-12-26 01:02:01'),
(57, 59, 'Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program - Alberta PNP', '<div>\r\n<p>So many aspiring immigrants have chosen the province of Alberta as their true home. Alberta is a hub of economic growth and development. It offers numerous opportunities for entrepreneurs. Alberta province provides well-paying jobs and has lower taxes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program has been replaced by the Alberta Advantage Immigration Program (AAIP). Under this new program, prospective immigrants with the right balance of skills and work experience required by the Canadian province of Alberta shall get their Alberta Provincial Nomination Certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Alberta Immigration Streams</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Alberta Opportunity Stream </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This stream is created for skilled workers who want to migrate to Alberta in eligible occupations taken out by the province. You are eligible to apply for this stream if you are overseas nationals who work in Australia and overseas graduates who have finished their studies in an approved Alberta post-secondary institution. You need a valid work permit, a minimum CLB of 4 or 5 as per the occupation, and a high school degree.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Alberta Express Entry Stream </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This stream permits Alberta to nominate applicants who have created the federal Express Entry system profiles. Those who have shown their ties to Alberta and have the skills to contribute to the province&#39;s economic growth. All you need is a profile in the <strong>Express Entry</strong>&nbsp;pool and an expression of interest to move to Alberta. Also, a CRS of 300 and working in an occupation in Alberta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Alberta Accelerated Tech Pathway </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This pathway is for Tech workers who have submitted their profile in the express entry pool. They become eligible under the Alberta Express Entry Stream. To be qualified for this pathway, not only do you need a minimum of 300 CRS points, but you are either required to be working or should have a got an in an eligible tech occupation in Alberta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rural Renewal Stream </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This stream is for applicants who have secured a job offer from an employer in Alberta to work in their rural communities. The eligible candidate requires a full-time job offer from an Alberta employer to work in an eligible occupation in a designated community. Also, language requirements, high school equal to Canadian standard of education, and enough funds to support themselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Alberta Farm Stream </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This Self-Employed Farmer Stream is designed for applicants who wish to immigrate to Alberta to start a farming business here. To apply to this stream, you must possess Farm management skills and a minimum investment of CAD 500,000, an Investment documented in a proposed business plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Graduate Entrepreneur Immigration Stream </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This stream of Alberta is for overseas graduates of approved Alberta post-secondary institutions who want to either establish or operate a business in Alberta. To apply to this stream, you need a valid Post-Graduate Work Permit (PGWP) during the application, a minimum CLB of 7 and must either establish a new business or operate an existing business with minimum ownership of 34%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Foreign Graduate Entrepreneur Stream </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This stream is for those foreign-educated international graduates who want to introduce a start-up business in Alberta and become <strong>permanent residents of Canada</strong>. One needs a minimum of six months minimum of full-time work experience in managing and owning the business. A business plan with projected financials and a minimum investment of $100,000 for an urban center, or $50,000 for a regional area</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rural Entrepreneur Stream</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This stream is for those immigrants who wish to start their own business in rural communities in Alberta. To apply for this stream, you need three years of minimum work experience as an active business owner or a manager or a minimum of 4 years of experience in the role of a senior manager within the past ten years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, the applicant should have a minimum net worth of $300,000 and a Minimum investment of $200,000 from the spouse&#39;s equity or the common-law partner. Not to forget, they must have a Community Support Letter from a participating rural Alberta community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Step by Step Process to immigrate to Alberta</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Step 1</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first step is choosing an ideal stream for you, depending on your situation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Step 2</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to submit your application for the stream which you have chosen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Step 3</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Procure your provincial nomination from Alberta</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Step 4 </u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the last step, you will be required to apply for permanent residence at Immigration, Refugees, and Citizenship Canada (IRCC).</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Top reasons to build your future in Alberta</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Breath-taking landscapes, diverse and welcoming communities, and excellent job opportunities are some factors that attract immigrants worldwide to Alberta.</li>\r\n	<li>Alberta is known for its diverse set of cultures and cities featuring a range of world-class services. The province offers an excellent quality of life and a plethora of career opportunities for skilled workers, and abundant business opportunities for foreign investors.</li>\r\n	<li>Life in Alberta is all about more nature, more income, and more opportunities from education to work, and to business.</li>\r\n	<li>Living in Alberta is pretty affordable. There is no provincial sales tax and no healthcare premiums. You can easily rent a house in Alberta at $1266.</li>\r\n	<li>Residents of Alberta enjoy a higher family income compared to the rest of Canada. Typically families in Alberta can earn a median income of $104,000 after tax. This is more than the Canadian average of $92,400.</li>\r\n	<li>You can easily buy a house in major cities for $450,000. As of November 2022, the average price of a house in Edmonton was&nbsp;$368,576, which is quite affordable than other large Canadian house markets.</li>\r\n	<li>Alberta has no health insurance premiums, however, all residents must register for the same. Residents of Alberta have access to free medical clinics and hospitals. Most medical services are covered under the Alberta Health Care Insurance Plan.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>FAQ: Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Question</strong>: What is the processing period for the Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program?<br />\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: The petition processing time for the AINP basically depends on the specific visa class you filed a petition for and also the CIC bureau to which you have presented your submission. But, it normally takes somewhere between 6 to 12 months for Skilled Worker and International Graduate Class, and nearly 9 to 15 months for the Semi-skilled Worker Class.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Question</strong>: What kind of service or employment offer is required to be qualified for the AINP?<br />\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: You require having stable, full-time letter of work from a recruiter/firm of the province.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Question</strong>: Do I require filing a petition to the CIC office post gaining nomination certificate from Alberta?<br />\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: Yes, you do!<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Question</strong>: Is it possible to get an update of my position or follow my Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program<strong> (</strong>AINP) petition?<br />\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: updates on position or follow-ups are denied.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Question</strong>: Do I require depositing any chargewhile presenting a petition to the Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program <strong>(</strong>AINP)?<br />\r\n<strong>Answer</strong>: There are notany such requirements. You don&rsquo;t have to make any payment at the said time. But, post getting the nomination, you require presenting fee to the CIC bureau with your petition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make contact with us for additional comprehensive information on the Alberta PNP or the Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program<strong> (</strong>AINP). Fill in the Appraisal Form to review your possibilities of the AINP permit sanction complying with the latest and amended immigration rules.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The CIC clearly delineates which Immigration agent can represent a submission, for their clients, with the organization. The CIC calls them sanctioned agents.The Regulated <strong>Canadian Immigration Cosultants</strong>&nbsp;are one of them; they are members in good standing of the Immigration Consultants of Canada Regulatory Council (www.iccrc-crcic.ca). Guarantee that in case you are employing an immigration agent, who gets paid for his services, that he is a certified agent to represent your case with the CIC, and additional government bureaus of Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program you can write an email on&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;</strong>and one of the most experienced immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '387267716_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTc=', 1, '2023-12-26 02:07:40'),
(58, 60, 'Saskatchewan PNP Points Calculator 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>If you want to immigrate to Saskatchewan, you need to immigrate via their very own provincial nominee program called Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program (SINP). The program assesses applicants under the categories of International Skilled Worker Category, Saskatchewan Experience Category, Entrepreneur Category, and Farm Category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to be able to move to this Canadian province, you need a minimum of 60 points of 100 which can be tallied by a tool known as the <strong>Saskatchewan PNP.</strong>&nbsp;Points Calculator 2023. If you want to live, work and economically establish yourself in this province then apply to the Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program (SINP).</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Application Procedure</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Saskatchewan Occupations In-Demand stream is aligned with the <strong>Express Entry.</strong>&nbsp;system. To submit an Expression of Interest, all applicants must meet the minimum eligibility requirements before registering their profiles in the SINP portal. Once the profile is submitted, candidates will receive a score from the&nbsp;SINP Ranking System. All profiles will be ranked against each other, and the highest-ranking candidates will receive an Invitation to apply in one of the SINP immigration draws.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once an applicant receives an invitation to apply, they must submit an official application for permanent residence within the given timeline. While doing so, they must pay a non-refundable fee of CAD 350.&nbsp; Saskatchewan notifies the selected applicants via e-mail, wherein it specifies that the applicant has been selected for the provincial nomination. This nomination makes an applicant eligible to apply for permanent residency through the federal immigration system.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>SINP Points Assessment Grid</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The SINP Points Assessment Grid is a system that assesses a candidate&rsquo;s eligibility to migrate to Saskatchewan. The maximum allotted scores for the grid is 100. To be eligible, a candidate must score at least 60 points out of 100. Do remember that all potential immigrants must submit a range of supporting documents along with their SINP application as proof of their fulfilling the 60-point criteria. This point grid also ranks profiles as part of Expressions of Interest. Only those candidates with the highest scores are invited to submit applications to SINP.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>SINP Points Assessment Categories</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>International Skilled Worker Category -for skilled workers who wish to live and work in the province.</li>\r\n	<li>Saskatchewan Experience Category - for those who are already living and working there.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrepreneur Category - for new business aspirants wanting to start a business in Saskatchewan</li>\r\n	<li>Farm Category - is for farmers who have the experience to plan and purchase a farm in Saskatchewan.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>How to Calculate Saskatchewan PNP Points </strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Points are calculated based on the factors of:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Education and Training</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled Work Experience</li>\r\n	<li>Language Ability</li>\r\n	<li>Age</li>\r\n	<li>Labour Market &amp; Adaptability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Connection to Saskatchewan &ndash; Labour Market &amp; Adaptability</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicants are given points based on their strong connection with the labour market of the province which showcases the intention and potential to settle as well as assist in the economic growth of the province as a newly added permanent resident.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Minimum requirements to apply under SINP?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are the minimum eligibility requirements to apply for the SINP provincial nomination.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You should be able to score a minimum of 60 points in SINP&rsquo;s point assessment grid.</li>\r\n	<li>An applicant should create an express profile along with a Jobseeker validation code</li>\r\n	<li>When it comes to proficiency in a language, the candidate should get at least Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) level 7</li>\r\n	<li>They are required to hold work experience in an occupation which falls under the category of NOC skill type 0, A or B.</li>\r\n	<li>Present proof of settlement funds as well as n intention to work and reside in the province</li>\r\n	<li>Also, they need to have at least one year of post-secondary training or education that is equal to education in Canada.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>What is the SINP EOI Points System?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Saskatchewan International Skilled Worker&rsquo;s Expression of Interest (EOI) is basically a point grid system with a maximum of 100 points that are given based on the selection factors. For an applicant to be qualified under the sub-category of Express Entry or Occupation in-demand, they should be able to score a minimum of 60 points. Out of the total 100 points, 70 is awarded to the applicants on the basis of Labour Market Success factors such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Skilled Work Experience</li>\r\n	<li>Education and Training</li>\r\n	<li>Language proficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Age</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The rest of the 30 points are awarded to the applicant on the basis of their Connection to Saskatchewan, as in a close family member or relative or any past student experience province or previous work experience in Saskatchewan.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Process to apply under SINP 2023?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can now apply for a Canada PR visa via SINP via a simple two steps procedure:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 1 - You can apply online via the <em>OASIS</em> portal for SINP. Post that, the SINP will evaluate your profile and on the successful assessment, you shall receive a provincial nomination certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 2 &ndash; With this certificate, you will be able to submit your <strong>Canada PR Visa&nbsp;</strong>application to the Immigration, Refugees &amp; Citizenship Canada (IRCC). This application shall be reviewed and processed by the IRCC in around 6 to 8 months. If you have a positive assessment of your application, you shall be granted your Canada PR visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How Orange Global Consultancy can help you?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Orange Global Consultancy is a pioneer in the immigration industry for over 28 years of experience. Our certified immigration consultants help you at every step of the immigration process right from submission of your immigration application, flawless documentation as well as one to one consultation with our visa experts who bring to the table years of knowledge and professionalism in the domain of immigration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about <strong>SINP Points Calculator</strong> you can write an email on <strong>info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</strong>&nbsp;and one of the most experienced immigration consultants&nbsp;will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on <strong>+91 8336933622.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '650352076_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTg=', 1, '2023-12-26 02:19:30');
INSERT INTO `cms` (`id`, `menu_id`, `title`, `description`, `video`, `image`, `url`, `status`, `created_at`) VALUES
(59, 61, 'Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program - SINP 2023', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>About the Saskatchewan Immigration Nominee Program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An increasingly large portion of aspirants are choosing Saskatchewan as their permanent abode in the vast landscape of the country. The affordable housing, diverse community life, and high employment rate in the province are appealing factors for immigrants who want their specific skill set to translate into significant job opportunities in Canada. Since 2015, the () has been inviting more than 14,000 immigrants annually, to settle in the province. As per the 2016 Census, 10.5% of Saskatchewan&rsquo;s population is comprised of immigrants. The majority of these are economic immigrants, who have been systematically chosen based on their occupation and other qualifications, to contribute to the local economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pathways under Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program allows the provincial government to nominate skilled immigrants to live and work in Saskatchewan as permanent residents. The province selects these immigrants based on their skills and eligibility to contribute to the labor market of the province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The categories under SINP are mentioned below:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>International Skilled Worker Category</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; designed for skilled immigrants who want to live and work in Saskatchewan. The category is further divided into the following sub-categories:\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>International Skilled Worker: Employment Offer</li>\r\n		<li>International Skilled Worker: Occupation In-Demand</li>\r\n		<li>International Skilled Worker: Saskatchewan Express Entry&nbsp;</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Saskatchewan Experience Category</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; For foreign nationals currently working and living in the province on a valid work permit. The following are the sub-categories:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Existing Work Permit</li>\r\n		<li>Health Professionals</li>\r\n		<li>Hospitality Sector Project</li>\r\n		<li>Long Haul Truck Driver Project</li>\r\n		<li>Students</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Entrepreneur and Farm Category</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; For entrepreneurs planning to carry out business activities in Saskatchewan. The category is also for experienced farmers who want to buy and operate their farms in the province.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>International Graduate Entrepreneur Category</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; For International Students who have completed their graduation from a post-secondary institution in Saskatchewan and are planning to start their business in the province.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>SINP also operates an &ldquo;enhanced&rdquo; stream, which is linked with&nbsp;Express Entry. SINP&rsquo;s International Skilled Worker: Express Entry sub-category permits the province to select skilled immigrants with the required skills and potential to contribute to the provincial nomination. Once an express entry applicant receives a provincial nomination, they are awarded 600 CRS points over their existing scores<br />\r\n<strong>How to Apply for the&nbsp;Saskatchewan PNP</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application process and eligibility criteria for each pathway varies. Each category is divided into several sub-categories which evaluate and select specific candidate profiles. For instance, the International Skilled Worker category is divided into three sub-categories:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Saskatchewan Express Entry &ndash; for candidates applying for nomination through the online Express Entry system.</li>\r\n	<li>Occupation-in-Demand &ndash; for applicants who are practicing a skilled occupation that features on Saskatchewan&rsquo;s in-demand occupation list.</li>\r\n	<li>Employment Offer &ndash; for those who possess a valid job offer from an employer in Saskatchewan.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The SINP process typically involves three steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: Apply for a nomination</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An applicant who has filed an Expression of Interest in the <strong>Express Entry System&nbsp;</strong>may receive a Notification of Interest from the provincial authorities, inviting them to apply for a nomination. Alternatively, the applicant can directly contact the Saskatchewan immigration authority and follow the online application procedure of the relevant sub-category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2: Receive a Nomination</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the applicant meets the stipulated requirements of the immigration program, they will be nominated by the province. They will be evaluated through according to distinct requirements relevant to the sub-category and/or a point allocation system based on their age, language skills, education, employment experience, adaptability, etc. Availability of sufficient settlement funds may also be taken into consideration. The nomination makes them eligible to apply for permanent residence to Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3: Visa Application</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon receiving the nomination, the applicant can to IRCC. After due verification, the authority may grant the visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>IELTS Requirement </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>International skilled workers applying via the Express Entry system must score Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) 7 or higher in the <strong>IELTS preparation,</strong>&nbsp;while workers applying under most other categories require a minimum score of CLB 4.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Processing Time</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Typically, authorities require 3 to 6 months to issue a nomination. Additionally, the IRCC processing time is 6 months for PR applications filed under the category, and 15 to 19 months for applications filed under the Occupation in Demand category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to be updated with the latest regarding EOI draws, <strong>Skilled Occupations Lists</strong>, etc. and gain in depth knowledge about immigration procedures and requirements, it is advisable to contact a genuine . Orange Global Consaultancy Immigration Services Pvt. Ltd. has consistently maintained legitimacy and quality in the variety of consultancy services offered, with the intention of facilitating the journey of hopeful immigrants towards their desired destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program you can write an email on <strong>info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</strong>&nbsp;and one of the most experienced immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '240418596_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NTk=', 1, '2023-12-26 02:25:11'),
(60, 169, 'British Columbia Provincial Nomination for Skilled Professionals', '<div>\r\n<p>The rapidly developing economy of British Columbia needs trained manpower in high-demand professions. The Express Entry BC (EEBC) &ndash; Skilled Worker category of the <strong>BC Provincial Nominee Programme</strong>&nbsp;(BC PNP) is a quicker manner to obtain Permanent Residence in the province.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a view to make the cut, it is required that you first entertain a lawful employment offer from a local recruiter. Pertinent training &amp; experience are also needed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nExpress Entry BC links to the Express Entry structure to increase the pace of the Permanent Residence course.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a view to make the cut for this stream, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Have obtained an Express Entry Profile Number and a&nbsp;Job Seeker Validation Code from the IRCC Express Entry&nbsp;structure. It proves you fulfill the bare minimum requirements for one of IRCC&rsquo;s Express Entry Schemes, namely, Federal Skilled Worker Programme, the Federal Skilled Trades Programme, and the Canadian Experience Class.</li>\r\n	<li>Have said YES to a permanent, indeterminate employment offer (a permanent job, or one with no fixed end date) from a local job-provider. It is mandatory that the job is in a National Occupational Classification skilled occupation (skill level 0, A or B).</li>\r\n	<li>Make the cut to work in your job in the province.</li>\r\n	<li>Possess not less than two 2 years of the directly related employment experience.</li>\r\n	<li>Prove you can take care of yourself and those who are dependent on you.</li>\r\n	<li>Have, or be qualified for, lawful immigration standing in the nation.</li>\r\n	<li>Fulfill the bare minimum language conditions.</li>\r\n	<li>Have a work offer in tune with the established BC employment rates for the specific line-of-work.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employer Eligibility</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is required that your recruiter/firm is prepared to support your petition. They must fulfill the different eligibility conditions and also cater to some particular responsibilities through the application procedure.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General Employer Terms &amp; Conditions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your recruiter/firm must, among others:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Be well established as a recruiter and have a good standing in the province.</li>\r\n	<li>Offer permanent, indeterminate (either permanent or with no fixed end date) job.</li>\r\n	<li>Have a reasonably good workstation and follow good business practices.</li>\r\n	<li>Ink an employer declaration.</li>\r\n	<li>Fulfill the mandatory domestic labour market recruitment conditions, where valid.</li>\r\n	<li>Make you a permanent, indeterminate employment offer.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide you with a payment that&rsquo;s in sync with the usual business standards.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How it Functions?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a view to begin the procedure, make a profile with our online application and registration structure, BCPNP Online. After your registration, you will get a total on the basis of your skills and job. Those with the highest totals will get an Invitation to Apply (ITA), via the BCPNP Online.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Latest Update:&nbsp;</strong>The&nbsp;<strong>BC PNP</strong>&nbsp;carried-out two draws in the month of September 2017, even as a total of 1,114 ITA were proffered across the Skills Immigration and Express Entry &ndash; BC streams, with an added 10 ITAs offered under the Entrepreneur Stream. Those who have received an ITA in these draws can presently present an application to the BC administration, for a provincial nomination certificate. And, with the certificate, they can present a petition to the Canadian Federal Administration, for PR in the nation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '148611366_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NjA=', 1, '2023-12-26 02:30:31'),
(61, 170, 'Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program for Skilled Professionals', '<div>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Programme</strong>&nbsp;(MPNP) allows the province to draw the precise immigrants who have the perfect credentials and whose qualifications and experience best suit the specific local job market. The province understands the numerous benefits the qualified immigrants may bring to both the region&rsquo;s economy and people. Against this backdrop, the Manitoba PNP was brought into existence, and tailored in such a way that the immigration procedure for the talented people keen to reside inside the province got accelerated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Two different methods are available for the prospective immigrants to submit an application to the&nbsp;<strong>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Programme 2017</strong>. Outside of <strong>Express Entry</strong>, they may send an Expression of Interest (EOI) openly to the Immigration Manitoba. In case the applicant gets a Manitoba nominee certificate from the MPNP, he may present a petition to acquire PR in Canada employing Express Entry, via creating a fresh profile and uploading their qualifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the other hand, those keen to move to Manitoba via the MPNP, may start out via generating a profile for the Express Entry that officially exhibits their interest in movement to the province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Immigration Manitoba Provincial Nominee Programme may send the individual a Notification of Interest (NOI) through Express Entry, sending an invite to him to present an EOI to the scheme.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case offered a Manitoba nomination, the would-be immigrant&#39;s profile for Express Entry then will be promptly given the nomination certificate with an extra 600 points under the Express Entry CRS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This noteworthy swell in the CRS total would fetch the person an Invitation to Apply (ITA) for PR in the nation through the following <strong>Canada Express Entry Draw.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Permanent Resident petitions for the nation processed via Express Entry are much faster; it takes less than 6 months to process it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MPNP Categories</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Programme 2017 has three classes, namely, Manitoba Invitation, Manitoba Connection, and Business Investor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Manitoba Invitation Stream</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the name suggests, an actual Letter of Invitation from the&nbsp;<strong>Manitoba Nominee Programme 2017</strong>&nbsp;is involved. With a view to get this invitation there is no requirement on the part of the would-be immigrant to reside in the province. The MPNP moves across the globe hunting for the gifted people who have abilities and experience that can make a difference to the province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Manitoba Connection Stream</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Candidates with a link to the province have many potential streams to PR and these streams involve a direct link to an individual, business or establishment (like a university, for instance) in the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Manitoba Business Investor Stream</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A successful Manitoba firm/enterprise is good for both the province and the business holder. This&nbsp;provincial nominee Manitoba immigration&nbsp;class is for those who wish to become a <strong>Permanent resident Canada</strong>&nbsp;in the province, for the object of either launching their own firm/enterprise or purchasing an already running one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Latest Update:</strong>&nbsp;This September 29, a combined total of 298 LAAs to the MPNP were doled-out to the aspirants in two sub-classes of the Skilled Workers category. While 258 LAAs were proffered to the candidates from the Skilled Workers in Manitoba sub-category, 40 were given to those from Skilled Workers Overseas&nbsp;sub-class.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '405330189_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NjE=', 1, '2023-12-26 02:38:53');
INSERT INTO `cms` (`id`, `menu_id`, `title`, `description`, `video`, `image`, `url`, `status`, `created_at`) VALUES
(62, 171, 'Canada PNP Draws- Latest Figure and Updates in 2023', '<p>The Provincial Nominee Programs are viewed as the fastest route to Canada PR Visa&nbsp;for skilled foreign workers with even low CRS. Canada has ten provinces, each having its provincial nominee program and criteria for selecting skilled immigrants as per their economic and demographic needs. Some PNPs are aligned with the Federal Express Entry system, while some operate individually. PNPs linked with the Express Entry select applicants from the pool and then nominate them to apply for permanent residency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On this page, you will find all the latest PNP draw updates related to various PNP streams. As 2023 is already here, let&rsquo;s take a run down to all the biggest Canada PNP Program&nbsp;draws conducted since the start of 2021. Currently, there are over 80 PNP immigration pathways run by Canadian provinces, so stay glued to this page to know which PNPs are operating and inviting newcomers across the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 21, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program issued a total of 620 ITAs in latest draw, which targeted three distinct streams. In the Skilled Workers Overseas stream, 27 applicants were given invitations who attained a minimum of 723 points under the strategic recruitment initiative. Additionally, the Skilled Worker in Manitoba program granted 298 nominations under the occupation-specific selection criteria, with candidates scoring 612 points within NOC groups 64 and 65. Furthermore, 239 invitations were granted to candidates across all profiles who were not initially selected in the occupation-specific draw with a minimum score of 631 points. Lastly, the International Education stream welcomed 56 applicants to Manitoba under the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 14, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A total of 142 nominations have been granted through the Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program to candidates who met the eligibility requirements. The draw specifically targeted individuals who have family connection and primary occupation in demand with CRS score between 300 and 500.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 12, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program released the latest draw with total of 300 nominations to eligible candidates under priority sector &ndash; Tourism and hospitality occupation with job offer from Alberta employer. The draw was conducted for those who scored CRS between 300 to 500 points. In this draw, the candidates are selected on the basis of job offer and Tourism and hospitality occupation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 12, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia conducted another invitation round for multiple categories and streams with a total of 183 invitations. The draw targeted Skilled worker, International graduate (includes EEBC option) streams.&nbsp; A total of 133 invitations were given to the Tech occupations with minimum 88 CRS score. A total of 36 invitations to early childhood educators (NOC 42202) and 14 nominations in healthcare occupations with a minimum cut-off score of 60 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 7, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw &ndash; French Speaking</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program held a latest provincial draw exclusively for the Express Entry Human French Speaking Skilled Worker stream applicants. The province invited an undisclosed number of qualified applicants who scored between 308 and 434 CRS points in TEER Category 0, 1, 2 or 3 of National Occupational Classification (NOC).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 6, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia conducted latest invitation round for multiple categories and streams with a total of 222 nominations. In the draw, 160 invitations were granted to the General (tech occupations) applicants under skilled worker, EEBC, International graduate / EEBC and Entry Level &amp; Semi-Skilled streams with minimum 89 CRS score. A total of 43 invitations to early childhood educators (NOC 42202) and 19 nominations in healthcare occupations with a minimum cut-off score of 60 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 31, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program (MPNP) has declared its unique region specific selection under skilled worker in Manitoba stream. Under the draw, a total of 288 nominations were granted to the applicants who are in employed in Manitoba and wish to reside outside of the city of Winnipeg. The minimum selection score was clocked at 600 points. Out of 288 nominations, 127 nominations were given to those applicants who maintained a valid express entry profile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 23, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia conducted a solo invitation round of draw with a total of 155 provincial nominations across various streams and categories. In the draw, 102 invitations were extended within the tech category, with qualifying scores of 88 points. A total of 28 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 20 nominations in healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103, 32104), with a minimum cut-off score of 60 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 15, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canada Express Entry released the second All-program invitation draw of August month with 4300 PR Visas. It means all these qualified Express Entry applicants and their families will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa along with social benefits. Moreover, the minimum CRS cut-off score was at 496 points. The CRS score was lower and invitations were higher as compared to the previous draw in this month..&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 3, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP) conducted a provincial draw exclusively dedicated to the Express Entry Skilled Trades Stream for trade occupations. In this draw, the province issued 2844 invitations to Express Entry candidates who held CRS scores ranging from 250 to 516 points. The selected NOC profiles were from groups of 720, 721, 722, 723, 724, 731, 732, 734 and 820</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 3, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; Trade Specific Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canada announced its first Trade category based invitation draw with 500 invitations. It means total of 1500 qualified skilled trade Express Entry applicants and their families will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa. Moreover, the minimum CRS cut-off score was at 388 points which is considered as lowest for skilled category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 1, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia conducted a single draw, awarding a total of 169 provincial nominations across various streams and categories. In the draw, 132 invitations were extended within the tech category, with qualifying scores of 88 points. A total of 39 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 23 nominations in healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103, 32104), with a minimum cut-off score of 60 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 20, 2023 &ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the first provincial draw of the month, the province of Prince Edward Island revealed a total of 106 nominations which includes 97 nominations from labor and express entry streams and 9 nominations from Business Work Permit Entrepreneur. These deserving candidates will receive an extra 600 points enhancing their prospects of securing Canadian permanent residency visas for their entire families.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 13, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program (MPNP) has unveiled its most recent draw, which targeted three distinct streams. In the Skilled Workers Overseas stream, 41 applicants were given invitations who attained a minimum of 774 points under the strategic recruitment initiative. Additionally, the Skilled Worker in Manitoba program granted 205 nominations under the occupation-specific selection criteria, with candidates scoring 604 points within NOC groups 3, 10, 14, and 75. Furthermore, 237 invitations were granted to candidates across all profiles who were not initially selected in the occupation-specific draw with a minimum score of 661 points. Lastly, the International Education stream welcomed 57 applicants to the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 11, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A total of 150 nominations have been granted through the Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program to candidates who met the eligibility requirements. The draw specifically targeted individuals from the tourism and hospitality sector with a job offer from Alberta employer. The minimum CRS score requirement was at 435 points. In this selection, candidates were assessed based on their occupation in tourism and hospitality sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 4, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program released the latest draw with total of just 12 nominations to eligible candidates under dedicated healthcare pathway with a job offer from Alberta employer. The draw was conducted for those who scored minimum of 354 points. In this draw, the candidates are selected on the basis of job offer and healthcare occupation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 6, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP) conducted a provincial draw exclusively dedicated to the Express Entry Human Capital Priorities stream for tech occupations. In this draw, the province issued an undisclosed number of invitations to Express Entry tech candidates who held CRS scores ranging from 479 to 485 points. The selected NOCs were 20012, 21211, 21223, 21230, 21231, 21232, 21233, 21234, and 21311</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jul 6, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; Healthcare Specific Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a historic development, Canada has unveiled its second category-specific invitation draw for the healthcare sector, extending a total of 1500 invitations which is 1000 higher than the previous healthcare draw. Furthermore, the minimum Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) cut-off score for this healthcare category was set to the lowest 463 points which is 13 points lower than the previous draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jun 28, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; Healthcare Specific Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breaking News! Canada announces its first ever category based invitation draw for the healthcare category with 500 invitations. It means total of 500 qualified healthcare Express Entry applicants and their families will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa. Moreover, the minimum CRS cut-off score was at 476 points which is considered as low for healthcare category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 27, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a total of 185 provincial nominations, British Columbia released its double draw for multiple streams and categories. First draw had 130 invitations under tech category with required score ranging from 87 to 106 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 30 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 20 nominations were given to healthcare occupations and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103, 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 6, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia province conducts regular draws for the eligible candidates. In the recent double draw for multiple streams and categories, the province granted a total of 162 nominations. First draw invited 112 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 90 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 24 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 21 nominations were given to healthcare occupations and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103, 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 20, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia released the double draw for multiple streams and categories with a total of 149 nominations. First draw invited 107 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 90 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 18 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 19 nominations were given to healthcare occupations and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103, 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 5, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw &ndash; French Speaking</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program held a provincial draw exclusively for the Express Entry Human French Speaking Skilled Worker stream applicants. The province directly invited 278 candidates who scored between 312 and 487 CRS points. The draw targeted to specific occupations and profiles under the OINP List of targeted occupations for French applicants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 1, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program announced its latest draw for three different streams. Skilled Workers Overseas stream invited a total of 31 applicants who scored minimum 801 points under strategic recruitment initiative. Total of 262 nominations were given under the occupation specific selection who scored 607 points for NOC groups of 11, 13, 21, 42, and 44. And, another set of invitations of 240 for all profiles that were not