>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest Saskatchewan provincial nominee program announced draw under the two popular streams with a total of 1044 candidates were nominated. The Express Entry stream granted 784 invitations to those who scored minimum EOI score of 67. Whereas, the Occupation In-demand stream granted 260 nominations to the applicants with same minimum 67 points for targeted in-demand occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 18, 2022 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw &ndash; Skilled Trades</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program announced the latest draw of Ontario&rsquo;s Express Entry Skilled Trades Stream with an undisclosed number of invitations. The invitations were granted to those applicants who scored between 250 and 482 CRS points. The targeted applicants were those who have minimum one year of experience in Ontario in the skilled trade occupation listed in Group 72, 73 and 82 in the NOC List.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 16, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a total of 202 provincial nominations, British Columbia released its double draw for multiple streams and categories. First draw had 162 invitations under tech category with required score ranging from 85 to 107 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 29 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202) and 11 nominations were given to healthcare occupations with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 9, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second double draw by British Columbia province in the May released for multiple streams and categories with a total of 150 nominations. First draw invited 93 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 90 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 34 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 23 nominations were given to healthcare occupations and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103, 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 8, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Again, Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program held a provincial draw exclusively for the Express Entry Human Capital Priorities stream. The province directly invited 2,349 express entry candidates who scored between 427 and 482 CRS points. The draw targeted to specific occupations and profiles under the OINP List of targeted occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 5, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the recent Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program provincial draw, the province invited an undisclosed number of applicants under the category of Express Entry Human Capital Priorities stream. These candidates were selected based on the points scored between 475 and 482. The draw targeted to specific tech occupations and profiles under the OINP List of targeted occupations such as NOCs, 20012, 21211, 21223, 21230, 21231, 21232, 21233, 21234, and 21311.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 3, 2023 &ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest Saskatchewan provincial draw announced a total of 1032 candidates were nominated under the two popular streams. The Express Entry stream granted 739 invitations to those who scored minimum EOI score of 68. Whereas, the Occupation In-demand stream granted 293 nominations to the applicants with same minimum 68 points for targeted in-demand occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 2, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first draw of British Columbia province in the May month announces double draws for multiple streams and categories with a total of 171 provincial nominations. First draw invited 133 invitations under tech category with minimum score from 104 to 107 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 22 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 16 nominations were given to healthcare occupations and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103, 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 27, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program announced its latest draw for its exclusive pathway of Skilled Worker Overseas. This particular draws granted a total of 558 invitations who scored minimum 616 points. Out of the total invitations, 344 nominations were given to the applicants with a valid Express Entry profile number and job seeker validation code.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 26, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second round of invitation for Canada Express Entry in the April month announced 3500 PR Visas in a All-Program round of invitation. It means total of 3500 qualified Express Entry applicants and their families will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa. Moreover, the minimum CRS cut-off score was at 483 points which was lower than the last draw</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 25, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia province announces back to back draws for multiple streams and categories with a total of 168 provincial nominations. First draw invited 113 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 90 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 28 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), and 27 nominations were given to healthcare occupations with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 20, 2023 &ndash; Quebec PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quebec Immigration Ministry announced their April round of invitations for the Quebec Regular Skilled Worker Program (QSWP) with a total of 1020 invitations to eligible skilled candidates. The invitations were given to those applicants who scored minimum of 598 points or have a valid job offer from outside the territory of the Montreal Metropolitan Community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 20, 2023 &ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the latest provincial draw by the province of Saskatchewan, a total of 1067 candidates were nominated under the two popular streams. The Express Entry stream granted 623 invites to those who scored minimum EOI score of 69. Whereas, the Occupation In-demand stream granted 444 nominations to the applicants with same minimum 69 points for targeted in-demand occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 20, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba province announced its latest draw for its Provincial Nominee Program under the different streams. Skilled workers in Manitoba stream invited a total of 249 applicants who scored minimum 615 points for selected occupation codes. And, 194 nominations were given under the same stream for all profiles that were not selected in the occupation-specific selection with minimum of 651 points. The International education stream invited 38 applicants. And, Skilled Worker Overseas invited 26 candidates with a minimum score of 719.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 18, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The third provincial draw of British Columbia province was conducted for multiple streams and categories with a total of 208 provincial nominations. First draw invited 158 invitations under tech category with minimum score from 85 to 107 points. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 29 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), and 16 nominations were given to healthcare occupations and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 &amp; 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 12, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The April month Canada Express Entry invitations dips to a 3500 PR Visas for All-Program round of invitation. It means total of 3500 Express Entry candidates and their families received invitations who will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa. And, the minimum CRS cut-off score was clocked at 486 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 11, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second provincial draw of British Columbia province was conducted for multiple streams and categories with a total of 132 provincial nominations. First draw invited 99 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 85 for 35 tech occupations. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 25 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), and 8 nominations for 39 healthcare occupations with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 4, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program announced a total of 175 provincial nominations under a single stream of BC PNP. This time, British Columbia granted invitations under tech category for 152 candidates with minimum score from 85 to 106 for tech occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>April 4, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program declared multiple draws for its sub streams. The Masters Graduate Stream announced an undisclosed number of invitations with minimum EOI score of 52. In another draw, PhD Graduate stream granted nominations to undisclosed candidates with minimum of 48 score. And, a total of 6 nominations to the candidates registered for federal Economic Mobility Pathways Project under the Employer Job Offer: Foreign Worker stream.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 30, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the second draw of the month, Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program released a total of 150 nominations to eligible candidates. The draw was conducted for those who scored minimum of 372 points. In this draw, the candidates are selected on the basis of Family connection and primary occupation in demand within a CRS score from 300 to 500.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 30, 2023 &ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the third provincial draw of the month, Prince Edward Island province announced a total of 113 nominations under labour and express entry streams. The eligible candidates will be granted additional 600 points that will help them to attain Canadian permanent residency visa for the entire family.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 30, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The provincial round of draw of British Columbia province released a total of 211 provincial nominations under the different streams of BC PNP. First draw invited 165 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 85. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 23 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), another 23 nominations for healthcare occupations and 5 nomination for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103 &amp; 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 29, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canada creates history by granted hat-trick 7000 invitations in the back-to-back Canada Express Entry Draw for All-Program round of invitation. A total of 7000 Express Entry candidates received invitations who will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa along with the family. And, the minimum CRS cut-off score was 481 which is the lowest CRS cut-off since the resumption of the draws since pandemic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 23, 2023 &ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the recent provincial draw by the province of Saskatchewan, more than 496 candidates are nominated under the two popular streams. The Express Entry stream granted 184 invites to those who scored minimum EOI score of 82. Whereas, the Occupation In-demand stream granted 312 nominations to the applicants with same minimum 82 points for targeted in-demand occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 23, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a back-to-back Canada Express Entry Draw, Canada records another highest All-Program round of invitation for Canada Express Entry candidate. In draw announced again 7000 invitations to the eligible candidates who will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa along with the family. And, the minimum CRS cut-off score was 484 which is one of the lowest CRS cut-off since the resumption of the draws since pandemic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 21, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The third provincial draw of British Columbia of the month released with a total of 258 invitations under the different streams of BC PNP. First draw invited 202 invitations under tech category with minimum score from 85 to 106. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 34 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 17 nominations for healthcare occupations and 5 nomination for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103 &amp; 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 16, 2023 &ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prince Edward Island province announced the latest draw with a total of 138 nominations under labour and express entry streams. In a separate draw for entrepreneurs and business professionals, a total of 6 nominations were granted to the applicants under the Business Work Permit Entrepreneur stream who scored a minimum of 52 points under EOI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 15, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The highest All-Program Draw is registered by Canada Express Entry Program. In the recent draw, 7000 invitations to the eligible candidates who will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa along with the family. And, the minimum CRS cut-off score was 490. If more than one candidate has the lowest score, then the time of submission will be taken into consideration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 14, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The recent provincial draw of British Columbia released a total of 235 invitations under the different streams of BC PNP. First draw invited 197 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 83. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 23 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 10 nominations for healthcare occupations and 5 nomination for other priority occupations (NOCs 31103 &amp; 32104) with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 10, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a back-to-back provincial draw, the Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program declared the latest invitation round under the category of Express Human Capital Priorities stream. It invited 815 eligible candidates under the stream who scored CRS points from 479 to 489. The draw targeted to specific tech occupations and profiles under the OINP List of targeted occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 9, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program released the recent draw with a total of 134 nominations to eligible candidates. The draw was conducted for those who scored minimum of 301 points. This is the lowest CRS requirement by any province of Canada for the PR Visa. And, more applicants have better chance of getting the nomination from Alberta Province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 9, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program declared its latest provincial draw for all the aspirants under the different streams. Skilled workers in Manitoba stream invited a total of 224 applicants who scored minimum 612 points for selected occupation codes. And, 277 nominations were given under the same stream for all profiles that were not selected in the occupation-specific selection who scored minimum of 675. The International education stream invited 53 applicants. And, Skilled Worker Overseas invited 43 candidates with a minimum score of 666.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 9, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program declared the latest draw under the category of Express Human Capital Priorities stream. It invited 822 eligible candidates under the stream and scored CRS points from 469 to 489. The draw targeted to specific healthcare occupations and profiles under the OINP List of targeted occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 7, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest provincial draw of British Columbia released a total of 274 invitations under the different streams of BC PNP. First draw invited 229 invitations under tech category with minimum score from 85 to 105. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 26 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202) and 19 nominations for healthcare occupations with a minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>March 2, 2023 &ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prince Edward Island province released the latest draw with a total of 46 nominations under labour and express entry streams. The invitations were granted to those applicants who applied for PEI PNP, met the eligibility of the program and whose occupation is in high demand in the province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 28, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the recent draw by British Columbia province, it announced a total of 169 invitations under the different streams of BC PNP. First draw granted 145 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 83. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 18 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202) and 6 nominations for healthcare occupations with minimum of 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 23, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest draw by Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program announced for all the immigration aspirants under the different streams. Skilled workers in Manitoba stream invited a total of 207 applicants who scored minimum 615 points for selected occupation codes. And, 298 nominations were given under the same stream for all profiles that were not selected in the occupation-specific selection who scored minimum of 693. The International education stream granted 51 nominations. And, Skilled Worker Overseas invited 27 candidates who were invited under strategic recruitment initiative with a minimum score of 721.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 22, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The province of British Columbia announces the provincial draw with total of 246 invitations under the different streams of BC PNP. First draw granted 203 invitations under tech category with minimum score from 85 to 103. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 18 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 20 nominations for healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 16, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program announced recent draw with a total of 100 invitations to eligible candidates. The draw was conducted for those who scored minimum of 357 points. It means that the low CRS score applicants have better chance of getting the nomination from Alberta Province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 16, 2023 &ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prince Edward Island province announced the latest draw with a total of 222 nominations under labour and express entry streams. In a separate draw for entrepreneurs, a total of 6 nominations were granted to the applicants under the Business Work Permit Entrepreneur stream who scored a minimum of 70 points under EOI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 15, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry - PNP Specific Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The February month announced the exclusive Canada Express Entry draw specifically for the applicants who received provincial nominations. The draws announced 699 invitations to eligible candidates. The exclusive draw was rolled out for PNP candidates who already attained nomination and an additional score of 600 CRS under the PNP programs of Canadian provinces. The minimum cut-off score was clocked at 791 points under the PNP Specific Canada Express Entry Draw</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 15, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry - PNP Specific Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The February month announced the exclusive Canada Express Entry draw specifically for the applicants who received provincial nominations. The draws announced 699 invitations to eligible candidates. The exclusive draw was rolled out for PNP candidates who already attained nomination and an additional score of 600 CRS under the PNP programs of Canadian provinces. The minimum cut-off score was clocked at 791 points under the PNP Specific Canada Express Entry Draw</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 14, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program declares the recent double provincial draw with total of 237 invitations under the different streams. First draw granted 183 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 83. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 29 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 20 nominations for healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 55 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>February 9, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program announces the latest provincial draws for all the immigration aspirants under the different streams. Skilled workers in Manitoba stream invited a total of 221 applicants who scored minimum 720 points. International education stream granted 55 nominations. And, Skilled Worker Overseas invited 32 candidates who were invited under strategic recruitment initiative with a minimum score of 709.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 26, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program releases the recent provincial draws for eligible applicants under the different streams. Skilled workers in Manitoba stream invited a total of 253 applicants who scored minimum 726 points. International education stream granted 60 nominations. And, Skilled Worker Overseas invited 23 candidates who were invited under strategic recruitment initiative with a minimum score of 713.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 31, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its 5 provincial draws in a month for British Columbia Provincial Nominee! BC PNP announced fifth draw of the month of January with 243 invitations under the different streams. First draw granted 243 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 85. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 18 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 18 nominations for healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 24, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program is on a roll now! BC PNP announced fourth draw of the month of January 2023 with 275 invitations to eligible applicants under the different streams. First draw granted 221 invitations under tech category with minimum score from 82 to 105. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 31 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 18 nominations for healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 19 &amp; 23, 2023 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program announced double draw with grand a total of 200 invitations to eligible candidates. The first draw on January 19th granted 46 invitations to eligible applicants who scored minimum 324 points. The second draw on 23rd granted 154 invitations to eligible applicants who scored minimum 385 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 19, 2022&ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first draw of Prince Edward Island province in the year 2023 announced a total of 216 nominations under labour and express entry streams. In another another draw, a total of 7 nominations were granted to the entrepreneurs under the Business Work Permit Entrepreneur stream who scored a minimum of 62 points under EOI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 17, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the third draw of the month of January 2023, the British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program announced 192 invitations to eligible skilled worker applicants under the different streams. First draw granted 154 invitations under tech category with minimum score from 82 to 105. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 18 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 15 nominations for healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 12, 2023 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program begins the year 2023 on a promising note. The latest draw is announced for all the immigration aspirants under the different streams. Skilled workers in Manitoba stream invited a total of 260 applicants who scored minimum 734 points. International education stream granted 42 nominations. And, Skilled Worker Overseas invited 20 candidates who were invited under strategic recruitment initiative with a score of 713.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 11, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another historic All-Program Draw by Canada Express Entry Program. Again the Canada granted 5500 invitations to the eligible candidates who will receive unconditional Canada PR Visa along with the family. And, the minimum cut-off score was clocked at 490 for the Express Entry candidates which was dropped by 17 points. If more than one candidate has the lowest score, then the time of submission will be taken into consideration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 11, 2023 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The year 2023 begins the All-Program Draw with historic whopping number of invitations. This time the Express FSW draw granted 5500 invitations to the eligible candidates. And, the minimum cut-off score was clocked at 507 for the Express Entry candidates. If more than one candidate has the lowest score, then the time of submission will be taken into consideration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 10, 2023 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw &ndash; Employer Job Offer</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program declared a unique draw for the sub category of Employer Job Offer stream. It invited 402 eligible candidates under the Employer Job Offer &ndash; Foreign Worker Stream who scored 35 points or above. The draw was targeted to the skilled trade occupations under the OINP List of targeted occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 10, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the second draw of the months, the British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program announced around 150 invitations to eligible skilled worker applicants under the different streams. First draw granted 123 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 90. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 5 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 17 nominations for healthcare occupations, and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 5, 2023 &ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw &ndash; Entrepreneur Stream</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The province of Saskatchewan announced its draw of 2023 for the Entrepreneur stream. The draw invited a total of 50 applicants under the Entrepreneur with provincial score (Highest - 130, Lowest &ndash; 80, Average &ndash; 95). The stream is dedicated to the entrepreneurs who can start and run business in the province of Saskatchewan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>January 4, 2023 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program opens the year 2023 with a double Draw with total of 211 invitations under the different streams. First draw granted 163 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 105. Second draw granted invitations for two streams &ndash; 28 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202) and 20 nominations for healthcare occupations with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December 29, 2022 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Manitoba Provincial Nominee Program ends the year on great note. The latest draw is announced for all the immigration aspirants under the different streams. Skilled workers in Manitoba stream invited a total of 202 invitations who scored minimum 750 points in the EOI. International education stream granted 38 nominations. And, Skilled Worker Overseas invited 40 candidates who were invited under strategic recruitment initiative with a score of 711.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December 22, 2022- Ontario PNP update</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program (OINP) issued 14 invitations to apply under the Entrepreneur Stream. Invitations to apply were issued for expressions of interest that received a score of between 140 and 173.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December 21, 2022- Invitations to apply issued for the Masters Graduate stream</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program issued invitations to apply to candidates in the Express Entry pool who may qualify for the&nbsp;Masters Graduate stream&nbsp;with a CRS score of 46 and above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December&nbsp;21, 2022&nbsp;&ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saskatchewan&nbsp;invited&nbsp;153 candidates from the SINP Express Entry stream, plus&nbsp;315 from the Occupations In-Demand stream.&nbsp;Only certain occupations were invited. The score of the lowest ranked candidate was&nbsp;80 points&nbsp;for both subcategories.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December&nbsp;19,&nbsp;2022&ndash;&nbsp;</strong><strong>Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>On December 19, Ontario conduced a Tech Draw to issue notifications of interest to targeted occupations under Ontario&rsquo;s Express Entry Human Capital Priorities stream. The OINP targeted candidates with a comprehensive ranking system score of 484-490 and work experience in the following NOC codes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>21211&nbsp;- Data Scientists</li>\r\n	<li>21231&nbsp;- Software engineers and designers</li>\r\n	<li>21230&nbsp;- Computer systems developers and programmers</li>\r\n	<li>21232&nbsp;- Software developers and programmers</li>\r\n	<li>21234&nbsp;- Web developers and programmers</li>\r\n	<li>21233&nbsp;- Web designers</li>\r\n	<li>21223&nbsp;- Database analysts and data administrators</li>\r\n	<li>21311&nbsp;- Computer engineers (except software engineers and designers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December 8, 2022 &ndash; Alberta PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alberta Immigrant Nominee Program ends the year 2020 with grand draw of 129 invitations to eligible candidates. These invitations were granted to those candidates who has a valid express entry profile, eligible occupations under the new TEER system, and scored minimum of 305 points. The selected applications will receive an additional CRS points of 600.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December 6, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>December month begins with the British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program Draw inviting a total of 193 eligible skilled worker applicants under the different streams. First draw granted 144 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 95. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 32 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 12 nominations for healthcare occupations, 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>December 2, 2022 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Manitoba Provincial nomination announced its latest draw for all the immigration aspirants. The draw granted a total of 305 nominations to eligible applicants under existing Streams. The International Education Stream approved 56 nominations, Skilled Workers Overseas granted 43 nominations with minimum EOI score of 673. Out of the total 305 nominations, 31 approvals were granted to those candidates with a valid Express Entry ID and Job Seeker Validation Code.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>November 28, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>BC Provincial Nominee Program announced its latest provincial draw with a total of 336 nominations to skilled worker applicants under the different streams. First draw granted 253 invitations under tech category with minimum score of 105. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 49 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 42202), 24 nominations for healthcare occupations, 5 nominations for healthcare assistants (NOC 33102), and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 31103 and NOC 32104) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>November 18, 2022 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest Manitoba Provincial nomination invited a total of 518 nominations to eligible applicants under existing Streams. The International Education Stream gave 198 nominations, Skilled Workers Overseas granted 143 nominations with minimum EOI score of 686. Out of the total 518 letters of advice, 125 nominations were granted to those candidates with a valid Job Seeker Validation Code and Express Entry ID</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>November 17, 2022&ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The November month draw of Prince Edward Island province announced a total of 141 nominations under labour and express entry streams similar to the previous draw. In another PEI draw, the business work permit entrepreneur stream invited a total 8 applicants with a minimum cut-off score of 62.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>November 9, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Parallel to the previous All-Program Draw, this time also Express FSW draw granted the record breaking number of invitations of 4750 invitations to the eligible candidates. And, minimum cut-off score was again 496 which is 4 points lower than the previous draw. Canada continues to grant the maximum quota of invitations to the eligible skilled professionals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>November 8, 2021 &ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saskatchewan province announced the latest provincial draw for its two existing streams. The Express Entry stream granted 10 invitations to those applicants who scored minimum EOI score of 69 under this stream. Whereas, the Occupation In-demand stream granted 21 nominations to the applicants with minimum 69 points under this stream for targeted in-demand occupations. A total of 4 invitations also granted to the Ukrainian Refugees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>October 26, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canada continues to grant Express Entry FSW draws twice a month with record breaking number of invitations. This particular draw invited an enormous total of 4750 invitations to the eligible candidates which is again 500 invitations more than the previous draw. And, minimum cut-off score was 496 which is 4 points lower than the previous draw. The Express Entry draws will continue increase the invitations and reduce the cut-off score and backlogs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>October 20, 2022&ndash; Prince Edward Island PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The province of Prince Edward Island released its latest draw that granted a total of 194 nominations under labour and express entry streams. In another PEI draw, the business work permit entrepreneur stream invited a total 10 applicants with a minimum cut-off score of 72.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>October 12, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program released the provincial draw with a total of 374 nominations to qualified applicants under the different streams. First draw invited 320 candidates under tech category with minimum score range of 78 to 114. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 25 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 4214), 19 nominations for healthcare occupations, 5 nominations for healthcare assistants (NOC 3413), and 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 3114 and NOC 3213) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>October 12, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The October month Canada Express Entry FSW draw is breaking all the previous records. This draw invited an enormous total of 4250 invitations to the eligible candidates which is again 500 invitations more than the previous draw. And, minimum cut-off score was 500 which is 4 points lower than the previous draw. All the recent Express Entry draws indicate that Canada is back to normal, backlogs are reduced, and require more skilled professionals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>October 4, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia Province marked the first nomination of October month with a total of 239 nominations to qualified applicants under the different streams. First draw invited 184 candidates under tech category with minimum score range of 82 to 120. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 13 nominations for healthcare occupations, 5 nominations for healthcare assistants (NOC 3413), 5 nominations for other priority occupations (NOC 3114 and NOC 3213) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 29, 2022 &ndash; Quebec PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quebec Immigration Ministry granted the latest Quebec Regular Skilled Worker Program (QSWP) draw with a total 1,195 invitations to eligible candidates. The invitations were given to those applicants who scored minimum points of 597. The selected candidates will receive Canada PR Visa under the Quebec Regular Skilled Worker Program (QSWP).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 29, 2022 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program announced the latest draw of Skilled Trades Stream with 1,340 invitations. The invitations were granted to those applicants who scored minimum of 266 CRS points. The targeted applicants were those who have minimum one year of experience in Ontario in the skilled trade occupation listed in Minor Group 633 or Major Groups 72, 73 or 82 in the NOC List.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 28, 2022&nbsp;&ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saskatchewan province announced the latest provincial draw for its two functional streams. The Express Entry stream granted 639 invitations to those applicants who scored minimum EOI score of 83 under this stream. Whereas, the Occupation In-demand stream granted 507 nominations to the applicants with minimum 81 points under this stream for targeted in-demand occupations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 28, 2022 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario PNP declared its latest tech draw with 1,179 invitations to tech applicants under Human Capital Priorities Stream for PR Visa. The invitations were granted to those applicants who scored minimum 496 CRS score. The targeted occupations NOC were 0213 Computer System managers, 2147 computer engineers, 2172 database analysts, 2173 software engineers, 2174 computer programmers and 2175 web designers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 27, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program announced its double draw with a total of 268 nominations to qualified applicants under the different streams. First draw invited 215 candidates under tech category with minimum score of 100. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 28 nominations for early childhood educators (NOC 4214), 15 nominations for healthcare professionals, 5 nominations for healthcare assistants (NOC 3413) and 5 nominations for priority occupations (NOC 3114 and NOC 3213) with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 8, 2022 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The new chapter of Manitoba Provincial nomination invited a total of 278 nominations to eligible applicants under different Streams. The International Education Stream gave 41 nominations, Skilled Workers Overseas granted 20 nominations with minimum EOI score of 703. Out of the total 278 letters of advice, 76 nominations were granted to those applicants with a valid Express Entry ID and Job Seeker Validation Code.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 7, 2021 &ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program announced a back to back two provincial draws in just 2 days. The first draw occurred on 6th September with a total of 617 nominations for eligible applicants under its two streams (express entry stream invited 159 candidates and Occupations-in-demand invited 218 and 240 applicants. In the second draw on 7th September, the province granted 1086 nominations (express entry stream invited 521 &amp; 143 candidates and Occupations-in-demand invited 422 applicants).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>September 7, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia province announced its double draw with a total of 374 nominations to eligible applicants under the different streams. First draw granted 361 nominations under regional category including tech occupations with minimum score from 71 to 95. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 8 nominations for early childhood educators 4214, and 5 nominations for regional healthcare professionals with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 26, 2022 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the latest edition of Manitoba PNP draw, the province invited a granted a total of 353 nominations to eligible applicants under different Streams. The International Education Stream issued 36 nominations, Skilled Workers Overseas granted 58 nominations with minimum EOI score of 708. Out of the total 353 nominations, 73 nominations were granted to those having a valid Express Entry ID and Job Seeker Validation Code.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 23, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Tech Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest British Columbia PNP nominations were allotted to 205 eligible applicants under the regional category including tech occupations. The draw nominations were granted to streams of Skilled Worker (minimum score 101), Skilled Worker &ndash; EEBC (minimum score 106), International graduate (minimum score 87), International Graduate &ndash; EEBC (minimum score 91), and Entry Level and Semi-Skilled (minimum score 75).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 11, 2021 &ndash; Saskatchewan PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saskatchewan Immigrant Nominee Program announced the august month provincial draw with a total of 745 nominations for eligible applicants under its two streams. The express entry stream invited 433 candidates under selected occupations with minimum EOI score of 68 points. And, occupation-in-demand stream granted 312 nominations to selected occupations with minimum EOI score of 68 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 11, 2022 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The recent draw by Manitoba Province declared a total of 345 nominations / letter of advice were granted to the eligible candidates under different Streams. The International Education Stream issued 55 nominations, Skilled Workers Overseas issued 33 nominations with minimum EOI score of 718. Out of the total 345 nominations, 86 nominations were given to those with a valid Express Entry ID and Job Seeker Validation Code</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 10, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia PNP issued a bunch of draws with a total of 163 invitations in the target occupations and streams. First draw granted 155 nominations under the BC tech draw for tech occupations with minimum score from 76 to 114. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 5 nominations for Early childhood educators 4214, less than 5 nominations for regional healthcare professionals, less than 5 nominations under NOC 3413 (Healthcare Assistants), and less than 5 nominations under NOC 3114 &amp; 3213 with minimum 60 cut-off point score for all streams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 3, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia PNP issued double draw in the beginning of August month with a total of 166 invitations in the target occupations. First draw granted 133 nomination under the BC tech draw targeted for tech occupations with minimum score of 90. Second draw granted invitations for different streams &ndash; 9 nominations for healthcare professionals, 5 nominations under NOC 3413 (Healthcare Assistants), 5 nominations under NOC 3114 &amp; 3213 with minimum 60 cut-off point score for all streams.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>August 3, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The new Canada Express Entry FSW draw has increased its approval bracket from the previous draw. This draw invited a total of 2000 invitations to the eligible applicants. Again, this has 250 more invitations than the previous draw. The minimum cut-off score was 533 which is 9 points lower than the previous draw. All these trends indicates that in coming draws invitations will get increased and CRS Points cut-off points may further decline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 28, 2022 &ndash; Manitoba PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The new Manitoba PNP Provincial draw announced a total of 354 nominations / letter of advice were granted to the eligible candidates who applied under different Streams. The Skilled Workers Overseas issued 15 nominations with minimum EOI score of 726 and International Education Stream issued 41 nominations. Out of the total 354 nominations, 56 nominations were allocated to those with a valid Express Entry ID and Job Seeker Validation Code</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 28, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>British Columbia PNP announced the June month provincial draw with a total of 182 invitations in 3 different draws and target occupations. First draw was tech draw with 159 invitations targeted for tech occupations with score from 75 to 124. Second draw granted 17 invitations for applicants under NOC 4214 (Early Childhood Educators) with minimum 60 cut-off score. Third draw invited 6 candidates under Healthcare professions with minimum 60 cut-off point score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 21, 2022 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw &ndash; French Speaking Candidates</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario Immigrant Nominee Program issued its latest draw for French-speaking candidates under the Express Entry French-Speaking Skilled Worker stream. The draw permitted an undisclosed number of approvals to the candidates who scored a CRS score of minimum of 440. The selected candidates must have selected occupations in the information technology, teaching, and healthcare.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 9, 2022 &ndash; Ontario PNP Draw &ndash; French Speaking Candidates</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ontario announced unidentified number of invitations to eligible French speaking candidates under the Express Entry French-Speaking Skilled Worker stream. The draw permitted to those candidates who scored a CRS score of minimum of 481. The selected candidates must have eligible profiles in the selected occupations in teaching, translators, and healthcare.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>June 8, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry - PNP Specific Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The June month announced the first Canada Express Entry draw with a whopping invitations to 932 eligible candidates. The exclusive draw was rolled out for PNP candidates who already attained nomination and an additional score of 600 CRS under the PNP programs of Canadian provinces. The minimum cut-off score was clocked at 796 points under the PNP Specific Canada Express Entry Draw</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>July 6, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry Draw &ndash; All Program Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breaking News!! After a long pause of 18 months, Canada announced its first FSW draw. The draw granted a total of 1500 invitations to the applicants who applied under the programs of Express Entry, including the Federal Skilled Worker Program. The minimum cut-off score was 557, which was on the higher side compared to the pre-pandemic levels. After clearing the initial backlogs, the Cut off score will substantially decline in the upcoming draws.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 25, 2022 &ndash; Canada Express Entry - PNP Specific Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Canada Express Entry rolled out exclusive draw for PNP candidates. The particular draw is targeted for those candidates who already attained nomination and an additional score of 600 CRS under the PNP programs of Canadian provinces. The draw invited 589 invitations to eligible Express Entry candidates with a minimum cut-off score of 741 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>May 24, 2022 &ndash; British Columbia PNP Draw</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The province of British Columbia announced its latest provincial draw with a total of 3 draws for differe</p>', '', '798002718_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NjI=', 1, '2023-12-26 02:52:05');
