(74, 172, 'Online IELTS Coaching: How to prepare for IELTS', '<div>\r\n<h4><strong><u>Crack the IELTS with our Online IELTS Coaching Module</u></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>International English Language Testing System (IELTS) is widely recognized English Language Examination that is used to evaluate the linguistic proficiency of the candidate. This medium is used by almost all the authorities associated with Skilled Immigration, Relocation, Business Migration, Work Permit and Overseas Education. Considering the different modules such as speaking, listening, reading and writing in the test, the process may look difficult. But don&rsquo;t you worry, Orange Global Consultancy has it covered for you!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Orange Global Consultancy has a panel of CELTA Certified IELTS Training Coaches dedicated for providing comprehensive training for all the Immigration seekers and Overseas Education Aspirants.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>What are the benefits of IELTS Coaching?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You will have your own objective assessment of your English language abilities.</li>\r\n	<li>With the IELTS Coaching, you will gain better knowledge of the English language and can enhance your skills in Speaking and Writing.</li>\r\n	<li>With precise study material and constant training, you can score better scores of bands required for Immigration or International Education.</li>\r\n	<li>Having a target set, you will be motivated to study harder and improve your competencies</li>\r\n	<li>You will be awarded certification that is widely recognized by thousands of authorities, institutions, companies and professional bodies around the world.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>How does IELTS help you migrate?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For every immigration seeker, it is a thumb rule to score high marks in the English Language Proficiency Examination. These scores can make or break the immigration application. Higher the scores, higher is your chance of getting selected by the Immigration authorities. If an applicant appear for IELTS Examination without any training, 9 out of 10 times, he / she will end up with low IELTS Scores.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this digital era, it is fairly easy to enroll for IELTS Coaching according to the hours of training and price. With proper IELTS training from the experts, you can attain the much needed scores. These scores will help you get high Immigration points which will guarantee your immigration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>How Orange Global Consultancy can you help you with IELTS Coaching?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Orange Global Consultancy Immigration is the Industry&nbsp;carrying out comprehensive Immigration solutions and advising ideal customized immigration program for each client.</li>\r\n	<li>Orange Global Consultancy IELTS Coach will train you individually to prepare you for the speaking, listening, reading and writing modules of the IELTS test.</li>\r\n	<li>These four skills will be extensively covered in the 24 sessions with a duration of 60 minutes</li>\r\n	<li>Our IELTS Coaches are CELTA Certified Industry Veterans who will provide all the tips, hacks and strategies to crack the IELTS test and get you closer to your desired score.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>How the IELTS training is conducted?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>One-on-one Training Session</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Training conducted by CELTA Certified Trainers and highly experienced trainers</li>\r\n	<li>Mode of training - Online</li>\r\n	<li>Flexible Timings - 7:00 AM to 11:00 PM</li>\r\n	<li>Number of Hours - 24 sessions of 60 minutes each and 6 hours of self-Learning on a Learning Management software developed by CELTA Certified Trainers.</li>\r\n	<li>Eligibility criteria for one-on-one training:</li>\r\n	<li>Payment - Additional charges of 15000 + GST has been paid and the agreement for the same has been signed by the client</li>\r\n	<li>Must be received in full before IELTS training begins</li>\r\n	<li>IELTS one-on-one training cannot be made part of running offers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Please note:</em></strong><em> if the above criteria is not met, then the individuals shall receive Group Training Sessions with a student to faculty ratio as 10:1</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Group Training Session</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Training conducted by CELTA Certified Trainers and highly experienced trainers</li>\r\n	<li>Program - 30 Hour Schedule</li>\r\n	<li>Group Sessions</li>\r\n	<li>Student to Faculty Ratio - 8:1 maximum 10:1</li>\r\n	<li>Weekend Training - Available</li>\r\n	<li>All Group sessions will be of 90 minutes each</li>\r\n	<li>Mode of training - Online through ZOHO Webinar</li>\r\n	<li>Only 2 sessions of the Program can be re-scheduled, if missed by the student; anything beyond that will not be entertained.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '', '539835679_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NzQ=', 1, '2023-12-26 23:31:01'),
(75, 173, 'What is the Minimum IELTS Score for Canada PR Visa 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>Moving to Canada can be a life changing experience, especially when you are planning to settle with your family. It is an uphill task, and as you must be knowing that even the thought of migration cannot be completed without looking at the Canada PR process, which in turn helps you to make it to any of the Canadian provinces legally and safely.&nbsp; So ensure while filling out on your <strong>Canada PR Visa</strong>&nbsp;application that you follow every step of the process that can lead to successful application submission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The EE system manages three of the major economic class immigration programs namely Federal skilled worker Program (FSW) Canadian experience class (CEC) and Federal skilled trades (FST). Points for this programs are granted based on the six selection factors of age, work experience, educational qualifications, and proficiency in English or French language.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since language proficiency is one of the main requirements to qualify under any of the<strong> Canada Immigration</strong> pathways, it is important that you can get a qualifying score. One of the main factor upon which an applicant can increase their scores is IELTS or proficiency in English or French language. A minimum IELTS for Canada PR is CLB 7 that required in all the bands of reading, writing, listening and speaking to manage to get a good score.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>IELTS Score Requirements for Express Entry</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you ask for Minimum IELTS score for <strong>Canada Express Entry</strong>&nbsp;getting a CLB 4 or lower means that you get no points which can lessen your chances for a total point score. Only a Canadian Language Benchmark of 10 or higher, will see you witness an increase of 32 to 34 points. If you are applying via National Classification (NOC) A jobs, the minimum IELTS for Canada PR is CLB 7, whereas for NOC B jobs, the requirement is CLB 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Canada Express Entry system is one of most popular pathway to migrate to Canada. All you need to do to be eligible to apply is to score a minimum of 67 points or more on the Comprehensive Ranking system. Scores besides the language proficiency be granted based on the multiple factors of age, , work experience, educational qualification as well as additional factors such as arranged employment along with the genuine intention to reside and economically establish themselves in any of the Canadian provinces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As an applicant you will be required to score a minimum of IELTS overall band score 6 as it is the minimum band requirement for Canada &nbsp;PR visa in IELTS or CLB (Canadian Language Benchmark) level 7 to be qualified &nbsp;for a PR Visa as a skilled worker. This will be the same for three economic class immigration programs under Canada Express entry namely Federal Skilled Worker Program (FSWP), Federal Skilled Trades Program (FSTP) and Canadian Experience Class (CEC).</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>IELTS Score for Canada PR Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your IELTS band required for Canada PR 2023&nbsp;will have to be evenly 6 in each bands as it helps you secure a good point weightage. A quick processing and approval of Canada PR visa application leads to a faster Invitation to Apply for permanent residence in Canada. With a permanent residency card of Canada you can avail free education till the age of 18, after which you can pursue higher studies at subsidized rates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apart from this, you can avail free healthcare coverage, cutting down on your huge medical expenses that can burn a hole in your pocket. Also, social security services such as employment insurance, unemployment allowance, child support and aid as well as family related, disability and maternity benefits. All this, and more ill make you reside in Canada a comfortable and easy affair.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are ways via which you can get high scores if you have not been able to get the required scores. The best way to do this for a candidate to take the help of<strong> IELTS Online Coaching</strong>. By taking mock practice tests it shall help you to improve with feedback from your mentors. This shall help you gain confidence while speaking, writing, reading or listening. There are even books which guide you step by step methods on how to ace your IELTS for Canada immigration.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Minimum IELTS Score To Get Canada PR in 2023</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When you give IELTS test you receive a paper copy of your minimum IELTS score in the Test Report Form (TRF), through delivery via mail 13 days post the test date for a paper-based test and 3 to 5 days after you take an online test for the same. For 2 years these test scores will be valid when it comes to Canada immigration. An IELTS overall band score 6 is equivalent to CLB (Canadian Language Benchmark) Band 7. To secure a chance on top scores in the very first go the best way to go about is to enrol in IELTS online classes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pathways like Canada Express entry system, Business Immigration Program, Family Class Immigration inclusive of Partner visas as well as Grandparents visa, numerous Provincial Nominee Program and Canadian Experience Class or CEC are some of the top pathways for securing Canada PR visa. Other accepted English tests which can be an alternative to IELTS are the TEF test and CELPIP General.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But if you want to work in Canada then there is a change in the Minimum IELTS score. For instance, to become a lawyer you will need a minimum score of 7 in every section of the IELTS to be eligible whereas as a nurse you will need a minimum overall score of 6.5 and 7 for Speaking. This differs from profession to profession. Just make sure you know the IELTS score for the occupation you want to apply as an applicant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about <strong>Minimum IELTS score for Canada&nbsp;</strong>you can write an email on <strong>info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</strong>&nbsp;and one of the most experienced immigration consultants&nbsp;will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on <strong>+91 8336933522.</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '217160614_download (1).jpg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NzU=', 1, '2023-12-26 23:39:10'),
(76, 174, 'What is the Average Salary in Canada in 2023 ?', '<div>\r\n<p>When you think of moving to Canada, the first thing that comes to your mind is how much Salary you will earn in Canada? People who apply for a <strong>Canada PR Visa</strong>&nbsp;must know about the average Salary a person makes in Canada to maintain a stable life and better career opportunities. Irrespective of the work experience and the profile in which you are working, Canada offers an average salary to its residents and citizens per month to lead a comfortable life. A person working full-time in Canada typically earns an average salary of 120,000 CAD&nbsp;per year. The Average Salary in Canada ranges from 30,200 CAD&nbsp;to 534,000 CAD.&nbsp; The average wage includes housing, transportation, and other benefits. How much compensation you earn in Canada also depends on your profile, sector, and industry type.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Median Salary</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Median Salary is 112,000 CAD per year, which means that 50% of the population earns less than 112,000 CAD while the other half earns more than the said amount.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What is the difference between the average and the median salary?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Both the median and the average Salary are the indicators of your growth in Canada. If your Salary is above the average and the median, you are doing quite well in Canada. Whereas, if your Salary is lower, then there is a scope for improvement. Median and the average salaries are measures of the &quot;middle of the market&quot; regarding compensation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Organizations in Canada target employees at either the average wage in Canada&nbsp;or the median rate without compromising the company&#39;s overall operational cost. Your Salary also depends on your education, level of skills, and experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Average Salary in each Canadian province</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Canada has ten provinces and three territories. Each province is different in economy, demographic conditions, employment opportunities, workforce availability, and wages. Since their economy is diverse, the Average Salary in Toronto will differ from Regina, which is in Saskatchewan. Therefore, before you pick a provincial nominee program for immigration, it&#39;s crucial to know the average Salary an individual earns in a specific province.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Typically, average salaries remain higher in the following provinces:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ontario</li>\r\n	<li>Alberta</li>\r\n	<li>British Columbia, and</li>\r\n	<li>Quebec</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The salaries mentioned in the above table are subject to change depending on your experience and expertise. Your qualification and knowledge of the job market influence your average salary in Canada per month or year. The salary levels are also based on the location and the career field.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What are the highest-paying jobs in Canada?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Specialist Physicians- $117, 00-$375,000</li>\r\n	<li>Mining, Oil and Gas Extraction- $113,506.12</li>\r\n	<li>Dentists- $168237</li>\r\n	<li>Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services- $76,077.56</li>\r\n	<li>Senior Managers in Finance and Communication- $77,805 &ndash; $129,629</li>\r\n	<li>Airline pilots&nbsp;&ndash; $35,233 &ndash; $146,274</li>\r\n	<li>Senior Software Engineer- &nbsp;CA$109,737</li>\r\n	<li>Public Administration- $75,799.88</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Hopefully, the salaries mentioned above have encouraged you to learn about <strong>Canada PR requirements</strong>&nbsp;from India. You can call one of our immigration experts to start your Canadian success story.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek more information about the&nbsp;<strong>Average Salary In Canada</strong>&nbsp;you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in<strong>&nbsp;</strong>and one of the most experienced immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91 8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '292670079_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=NzY=', 1, '2023-12-26 23:43:39'),
(77, 163, 'Everything about Labour Market Impact Assessment (LMIA)', '<div>\r\n<p>A Labour Market Impact Assessment is an official permit or a document that empowers the Canadian employer to hire a skilled foreign worker legally into their company or business. A positive LMIA determines a strong need for a skilled foreign worker to fill the vacancy. Furthermore, it also denotes that no other Canadian worker or <strong>Canad PR Visa</strong>&nbsp;Holder is available or capable of doing that job. Therefore, Canadian Employers would need a positive LMIA to hire skilled workers overseas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a skilled professional, you can move to Canada for Employer with the help of LMIA, or you can choose pathways that are LMIA-exempt. Therefore, you need to identify whether your pathway requires an LMIA process or work permit, then your employer must do one of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify the LMIA exemption codes and work permit exemptions</li>\r\n	<li>Choose the appropriate LMIA exemption or work permit code according to your hiring situation</li>\r\n	<li>Include the exemption code in your offer of employment OR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Contact the International Mobility Workers Unit if they are hiring a foreign worker who is currently outside Canada and comes from a visa-exempt country</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What are the minimum eligibility requirements?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employers:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must demonstrate that their job offer business is authentic and legitimate</li>\r\n	<li>Submit a Transition plan for the same position and work location</li>\r\n	<li>Must advertise the job vacancy on the Government of Canada Job Bank</li>\r\n	<li>Also, conduct a minimum of two additional acceptable modes of recruitment with the occupation</li>\r\n	<li>Wages must be similar to the Canadian workers or residents</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the employer receives the LMIA, the skilled foreign worker can apply for a Canadian work permit and eventual <strong>Canada immigration</strong>. To apply for Work Permit, Workers need:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A valid Canadian job offer</li>\r\n	<li>An employment contract</li>\r\n	<li>A copy of the LMIA</li>\r\n	<li>And the LMIA number</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What is the process to get an LMIA?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Your employer must acquire a positive LMIA from Employment and Social Development Canada (ESDC) to work in Canada. The LMIA application process differs from the type of program your employer is hiring for. The employer can hire:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>high-wage workers</li>\r\n	<li>low-wage workers</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled workers via Seasonal Agricultural Worker Program</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled workers via Agricultural Stream</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You must follow the below process to achieve a positive LMIA:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must meet the program eligibility requirements for both employer and employee</li>\r\n	<li>The employer must have a job bank to authenticate the process</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the application and all documents such as LMIA application, business legitimacy proof, proof of recruitment, employment contract, and job offer</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the processing fee of the program on the official portal</li>\r\n	<li>You will receive a positive Labour Market Impact Assessment in a letter form</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What are the pathways that do not require LMIA?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Many pathways or scenarios allow Canadian employers to hire temporary foreign workers without an LMIA for the Canada PR Visa</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you have been for a Canadian employer for a minimum of one year under the LMIA-exempt work permit, then you can work in Canada without an LMIA for forthcoming years</li>\r\n	<li>You may not need LMIA if your current job offer is LMIA-exempt covered by an international agreement such as CUSMA or GATS (Professionals, Traders, and Investors)</li>\r\n	<li>If your job offer is covered by an agreement that includes &ldquo;Significant Investment&rdquo; projects</li>\r\n	<li>You may not need LMIA if you are exempted from &ldquo;Canadian Interests&rdquo;:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Significant benefits &ndash; You will bring social, cultural, and economic benefits to Canada (mainly for Canada Self Employed Program)</li>\r\n	<li>Reciprocal Employment &ndash; You can get a job when Canadians have similar opportunities overseas</li>\r\n	<li>Designated by Minister &ndash; Profession under academics that includes guest lecturers, researchers, and visiting professors through a recognized federal program</li>\r\n	<li>Charity and Religious Workers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You can also achieve LMIA-exemption through the provision for intra-company transferees (Canada Intra-company Transfer Program)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you become eligible for International Mobility Program, you can attain LMIA exempt entry to Canada. Your employer must submit an employer compliance fee and an offer of employment form through the official Employer Portal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information about the LMIA process, employment opportunities and <strong>Canada Immigration</strong> process, you can reach us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in or call us at 8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '610426068_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=Nzc=', 1, '2023-12-26 23:49:55'),
(78, 164, 'Improve your chances of selection under Federal Skilled worker Category Express Entry Program', '<div>\r\n<p>There is no doubt that Canada&#39;s Express Entry program is the most popular immigration pathway globally. This comes under Canada&#39;s Federal Skilled Worker Category and is one of the Canada Government&rsquo;s Economic Immigrants Streams. Through express entry, millions of newcomers have found a safe abode and permanent settlement in Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Choose the suitable National Occupation Classification (NOC) Code</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Choosing an in-demand occupation as your primary NOC can improve your chances under <strong>Canad PNP</strong>&nbsp;. With minimum one year of experience in the chosen NOC, the more the work experience, the better are your chances.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Language proficiency is essential</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you ask any experts to maximize your chances, the most straightforward answer would be to &ndash; improve your Language Scores. Under the Canada Express Entry Program, Language proficiency test scores are the deciding factor and key to getting a competitive Comprehensive Ranking Score (CRS) score. You can also claim points for both English and French under the point system to ensure that you are getting as many points as possible. You can also re-appear for your language tests to obtain the desired scores for your immigration. It is advised that these tests are given after appropriate coaching to enhance the possibility of a higher language score.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Follow proper documentation process before submission</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take all the measures to perfect the documentation process by strictly adhering to the document checklist. The checklist encompasses a detailed list of all relevant documents to help you score those necessary CRS scores. It is better to take the help of experienced immigration consultants who have years of experience meticulously dealing with the immigration process. At Orange Global Consultancy Immigration, we have more than years of industry experience and goodwill in serving our clients in the entire <strong>Canada Immigration</strong>&nbsp;process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Complete another academic program and gain more experience</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have submitted your expression of interest application and waiting in the pool, you can consider an alternative solution. Gaining more work experience and additional educational qualifications is a long-term strategy for improving your immigration <strong>CRS Score</strong>. And you can consider overseas education in Canada for any master&rsquo;s degree, which will reward your post-graduate work permit for further employment opportunities in Canada. Your Canadian qualification and experience will contribute to the CRS skill transferability factors section, enabling you to breach the CRS cut-off points comfortably and get an invite to apply for a Canada PR visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Make the best use of representative</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Orange Global Consultancy, you get the additional premium service of an authorized RCIC licensed under CICC. Our RCIC Agent, Mr. Sanjay Sharma (R709081), is based in Thornhill, Ontario, Canada, and has recognizable experience helping immigrants settle in Canada. He will provide all the support and legal help in preparing your immigration application. Furthermore, he will be the first point of contact with the immigration authorities by representing your application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you wish to improve your chances of getting selected for the <strong>Canada Express Entry</strong>, you can register for our free immigration counseling and guidance. For more details, you can write an email at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in,&nbsp;or you can also choose to call us at (+91)-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '511458207_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=Nzg=', 1, '2023-12-26 23:56:20'),
(79, 161, 'For Canadian Immigration, If You Hire An Immigration Consultant, Take the Services of Authorized Representatives!', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>Immigration , Refugees and Citizenship Canada</strong> (<strong>IRCC</strong>) the Government of Canada, facilitates and regulates the arrival of immigrants to Canada, protects refugees and offers help to newcomers to Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Analyzing profiles, specifically for various <u>ongoing</u> and <u>upcoming</u> provincial nominee programs, and looking for possible customized options.</li>\r\n	<li>Advice possible small budgeted business options: Subject to eligibility, confirmation of expression of interest to go for this option, investment, and approval of the work permit, the clients may look forward to gaining additional points to get an ITA under the CRS ranking.</li>\r\n	<li>Possible affordable study abroad options: Subject to eligibility, going for this option can help qualified clients in gaining bonus points for Canadian qualifications, work permits, and in due course, points for their Canadian experience. Clients who can successfully follow the above process may gain additional points to get an ITA under the CRS ranking.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>For Businessmen and Investors</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For Businessmen and high net worth individuals,&nbsp; Management background with leading hospitality industry icons and being a small boutique retailer founder provides his insight to manage business applications of all kinds. This includes and is not limited to start-ups, entrepreneurs, Immigrant Investor Programs, owner-operators programs, Intra-company transfer programs. We can offer a comprehensive portfolio of business investment ideas of varied investment amounts per our client&rsquo;s capabilities, organize exploratory visits and offer all related services, including company incorporation, office space, accounting, and staffing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>For All Clients</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We complete post-landing scale