(90, 149, 'Canada aims to invite around 1.5 Million Newcomers by 2026', '<div>\r\n<p>As a yearly tradition, IRCC has announced the most-awaited Immigration Levels Plan for 2024 to 2026, outlining the details of intended invitations and approvals under different immigration categories. With the new yearly plan, the government demonstrates unwavering support to bring foreign talents, prioritize economic development, drive family reunification, and support humanitarian crises. Canada realizes immigrants play an essential role in propelling the economic channels, filling the labor gaps, and boosting the job market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a recent declaration, Canada announced that it will invite 485,000 new permanent residents in the year 2024, which represents 1.2% of Canada&#39;s current population. Moreover, the IRCC plans to increase the PR invitations by 500,000 in 2025 and invite the same 500,000 newcomers by 2026.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Impact of Canada Immigration Levels Plan (2024-2026) on the future of Canada:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Canada has laid out the long-term goal of focusing on economic growth by inviting more foreign skilled professionals. This is reflected in their target of welcoming over 60% of permanent resident admissions to the economic class in 2025.</li>\r\n	<li>Last year, Canada achieved the target of 4.4% of French-speaking New Permanent Residents (Outside Quebec). Canada plans to increase the approval rate of new Francophone immigrants by 6% in 2024, 7% in 2025, and 8% in 2026.</li>\r\n	<li>The government of Canada continues to prioritize healthcare and STEM professionals&nbsp;as firms to fill labor force gaps in meeting sustainable initiatives, supporting family reunification, and supporting humanitarian efforts.</li>\r\n	<li>Canada identifies severe labor shortages in key sectors such as health care, transportation, and construction without pressurizing the existing housing, health care, and infrastructure crisis. The new plan is intended for sustainable and stable population growth.</li>\r\n	<li>The new increased plan reveals significant progress by the IRCC in delivering new digital systems and improved customer service, resulting in increased application processing and reduced backlogs.</li>\r\n	<li>Over the last five years, Canada has invited around 38,000 tradespeople for permanent residency under the Federal Skilled Trades Program, Canadian Experience Class, and <strong>Provincial Nominee Program</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>Canada believes bringing new immigrants to fill labor gaps will also help channel the National Housing Strategy. This ambitious government plan will invest over $ 82 billion to provide homes for Canadians.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to grab this wonderful opportunity to settle in Canada? Do you wish to maximize your chances? You can connect with our experts for the<strong> Canada PR Visa</strong>&nbsp;process on 8336933522 or by mailing at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '857974798_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTA=', 1, '2023-12-27 02:50:49'),
(91, 150, 'Canada Business Visa Faqs 2023', '<p><strong>1.What is the Canada Business Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; The Canada Business Visa, officially known as the Start-Up Visa Program, is designed for entrepreneurs who want to start a new business in Canada.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Who is eligible for the Start-Up Visa Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; To be eligible, applicants must have a qualifying business, get a letter of support from a designated organization, and meet other criteria, including language proficiency and financial requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. What type of businesses qualify for Start-Up Visa Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; The business idea or concept must be innovative and scalable that has the potential to generate employment for Canadian Residents and Citizens. Your business&rsquo;s products and services must be unique such as Eco-friendly home cleaning products, Home automation &amp; security service, Virtual interior design services, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. What is a designated organization?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Designated organizations are business groups in Canada that have been approved to invest in or support possible start-ups through the Start-Up Visa Program. These include venture capital funds, angel investor groups, and business incubators.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. How to acquire investment or letter of support from a designated organization?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; You must have a detailed business plan outlining your products and services related information, finances, staffing and market research. You need to contact these investment bodies and pitch your business idea to acquire investments. If they are convinced, they will enrol you for a program and grant letter of support / investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Is it mandatory to apply as a sole applicant for Start-Up Visa Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Under the Start-Up Visa Program, you can apply as a business team with up to 5 members in a group. Each applicant must have a minimum of 10% of voting rights attached to company outstanding shares. The applicants and the designated organization must collectively hold more than 50% of the voting rights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7. What are the language requirements for the Start-Up Visa Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Applicants must prove their proficiency in English or French by taking an approved language test. Adequate language skills are crucial for successful business operations and integration into the Canadian business environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8. What financial requirements are there for the Start-Up Visa Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Applicants need to show that they have sufficient settlement funds to support themselves and their dependents while establishing their business in Canada. The required amount depends on the size of the family.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>9. How long does it take to process a Start-Up Visa application?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Processing times can vary. However, the goal is to process applications within a few months. It&#39;s advisable to check the most recent processing times on the official immigration website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>10. Can family members accompany the principal applicant?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Yes, family members (spouse or common-law partner, and dependent children) can be included in the application. They will also receive Canadian permanent residence if the application is approved.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>11. What happens after obtaining the Start-Up Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Once approved, entrepreneurs can move to Canada to start and operate their business. They are given a conditional permanent residence, and after meeting the conditions, they can apply for full permanent residence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>12. Can I change my designated organization after receiving a letter of support?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; No, changing the designated organization after receiving a letter of support is not allowed. The initial letter of support is specific to the designated organization that supported the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>13. Is professional guidance recommended for the Start-Up Visa application?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Yes, seeking professional guidance from immigration consultants or legal experts can be beneficial to navigate the application process effectively.</p>', '', '239182831_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTE=', 1, '2023-12-27 02:54:07'),
(92, 75, 'How to apply for Australia PR Visa - Permanent Residency Process for Indians', '<h2>How to Apply for Australia&nbsp;PR?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia has emerged as a popular destination for Indians looking for a high-quality life abroad for many years. Australia continues to be the most loved country for migrants because of many reasons such as promising job opportunities, higher wages, multicultural environment, pleasant climate, world-class education, and excellent career prospects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the Australian Bureau of Statistics, as of 30 June 2020, over 7.6 million migrants were living in Australia. This was 29.8% of the people born overseas. Indians are the second source of migration in Australia after England. Currently, 721,000 Indians are living in Australia. China takes third place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Considering such impressive numbers, it is no surprise that Australia is indeed an incredible country that Indians love to settle. The craze of Australia immigration continues to rise among skilled Indians seeking to become global citizens. However, not many of them know the ins and outs of <strong>Australia PR Process from India</strong>. So, if you are one of them, you have come to the right place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The immigration system in Australia allows skilled foreign workers to apply for permanent residency based on their talents and abilities to contribute to its economy. The <strong>Australia Immigration</strong>&nbsp;pathways are open to anyone from any country. If you want to live, work, and study in Australia, you have many visa streams: skilled visas, student visa options, investment pathways, and many more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But before that, let&#39;s talk about the benefits of an Australia PR visa:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Right to live, work, and study anywhere in Australia</li>\r\n	<li>Sponsor eligible family members for permanent residency</li>\r\n	<li>Free education for children up to a certain age</li>\r\n	<li>Access to social and healthcare benefits</li>\r\n	<li>Apply for citizenship after meeting the eligibility requirements</li>\r\n	<li>A permanent resident has most of the rights and entitlements of a citizen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is an Australia PR visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An Australian permanent resident holds a permanent visa but is not a citizen of the country. The PR visa allows holders to live, work, and study in the country, but they cannot apply for government jobs or vote. Permanent residents are the citizens of their home country. However, they can apply for Australian citizenship provided they meet the eligibility criteria of the same.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible to apply for permanent residency in Australia?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible to apply for permanent residency in Australia, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be under 45 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>have had your&nbsp;Registration of Interest&nbsp;(ROI) selected</li>\r\n	<li>Have achieved at least&nbsp;65 points.</li>\r\n	<li>Have a valid skills assessment</li>\r\n	<li>Have competent English language skills</li>\r\n	<li>Meet the health and character requirements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the application for Australia PR Fees?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As per the recent guidelines of the Australian Immigration Authority, below is the updated list of application fee:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Primary Applicant - 4115 AUD</li>\r\n	<li>Dependent Applicant - 2055 AUD</li>\r\n	<li>Child fees - 1030 AUD (Per Child)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Australia PR Visa Pathways for Indians</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The government of Australia offers several pathways for Indians to apply for a PR visa. These categories come with different eligibility requirements for immigration aspirants. Based on the requirements, one can use the following visa categories to immigrate to Australia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Subclass 189 &ndash; Skilled independent visa</li>\r\n	<li>Subclass 190 &ndash; Skilled state-sponsored visa</li>\r\n	<li>Subclass 489 &ndash; Skilled regional visa</li>\r\n	<li>Subclass 890 &ndash; Business visa</li>\r\n	<li>Subclass 891 &ndash; Investor visa</li>\r\n	<li>Subclass 132 &ndash; Business talent visa</li>\r\n	<li>Child visa</li>\r\n	<li>Partner visa</li>\r\n	<li>Parent visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step-by-step process to apply for permanent residency in Australia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: Check your eligibility </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To begin with, you must check whether you are eligible for the PR visa or not. For this, you may check the Department of Home Affairs website and learn about the visa options, basic requirements, documents needed, fee, and processing time for the visa. In this step, you must also select the most appropriate visa pathway based on your skills, education, and experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> <strong>Apply for skill assessment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now apply for the positive assessment of your education credential assessment through a designated authority. Different occupations have different assessment bodies to check whether your skills meet the standards Australian employers look for to work in a relevant occupation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3: Submit an expression of interest</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this step, you must submit an online expression of interest in Australia&#39;s SkillSelect system. SkillSelect is an online system that manages skilled worker visa applications for Australia. The <strong>Australia Poin System</strong> evaluates a profile based on several parameters, including a candidate&#39;s age, language skills, education, work experience, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Based on this information, the system allocates a score to the applicant. A candidate must score at least 65 points to qualify for a visa stream.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4: Wait for the invitation and apply for a visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your scores are sufficient, you will receive an ITA from DHA Australia. You have 60 days to respond to your invitation to apply and submit all necessary documents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the processing time?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A candidate needs to go through different stages to apply for permanent residency Australia. Each step has a different timeline. However, the General Skilled Migration visa pathways usually take around three to five months to get processed completely.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required for Australia PR visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some key documents applicants need to submit to migrate to Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Educational certificates</li>\r\n	<li>English language proficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Work experience certificates (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel documents (passports, permission to migrate from relevant authorities)</li>\r\n	<li>Medical and police verification certificates</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of settlement funds (bonds, bank accounts, cash, shares etc.)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nEven if you seek&nbsp;more information about&nbsp;Australian Visa&nbsp;for Indians you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>', '', '747597599_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTI=', 1, '2023-12-27 03:03:05'),
(93, 76, 'How to apply for Migrate to Australia from India', '<div>\r\n<p>If we are to talk about which of today&rsquo;s highly urbanized countries is worth unravelling, one cannot skip the thought of Australia. <strong>Australia migration</strong>, to one of the sixth largest country in the world with the most robust economy and a highly skilled workforce, proffers you with a kaleidoscope of diverse communities and cultures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People, particularly <strong>skilled migrants</strong> from India, see Australia as the ideal country to immigrate to, with a high employment rate, higher wages, and a far higher quality of life and services.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the process for Migrate to Australia?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As a prosperous nation, <strong>Australia Visa</strong>&nbsp;is gifted with an excellent Quality of Life and if you&rsquo;re certain about moving in, then you must understand its organized immigration system and straightforward immigration laws.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs the country doesn&rsquo;t pose any discrimination on the basis of race, religion, gender, or caste, the process for Immigration to Australia from India is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You have to choose your occupation (if listed) from SOL / CSOL, to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Get the skills assessment from the relevant assessing authority.</li>\r\n	<li>If you&rsquo;re moving to Australia under sponsorship/nomination subclass then, you must get a&nbsp;sponsorship/nomination&nbsp;from an Australian state or territory</li>\r\n	<li>You have to submit &amp; show an EOI (Expression of Interest) on SkillSelect</li>\r\n	<li>ONCE your profile is selected and you receive an invitation to apply, <strong>applying for an Australian</strong> visa requires you to submit the application (along with the immigration fees) within the next 60 days for VISA APPROVAL.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to migrate to Australia from India?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having one of the Advanced and well-developed economies in the world, huge number of Indians have made their home in Australia. Over the last few years Australia has seen an upsurge in the no. of Indian immigrants due its favoring climate, employment opportunities, culture and customs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nYou too can take the path of <strong>Australia Immigration</strong>, under these easy yet stringent visa subclasses:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong><u>SUBCLASS 189</u>&nbsp;</strong>- A Permanent Residence Visa, to live and work in Australia, wherein the applicant has to score a minimum of 60 points upon assessment, to meet the qualifying criteria for the General Skilled Migration visa.</li>\r\n	<li><u><strong>SUBCLASS 190</strong></u>&nbsp;- This subclass of PR Visa permits the applicant to live, settle and work in Australia. Under this Subclass of PR Visa, the candidate is required to be nominated by the state, or territory government</li>\r\n	<li><u><strong>SUBCLASS 491</strong></u> - Newly launched Subclass 491 Skilled Work Regional (Provisional) Visa. This visa category has been introduced by the Australian Department of Home Affairs, and has commenced from 16 November 2019.</li>\r\n	<li><u><strong>SUBCLASS 188</strong>&nbsp;</u>- Provisional Visa designed for business owners and investors operational at the second stage of business innovation and investment program.</li>\r\n	<li><u><strong>SUBCLASS 888</strong></u>&nbsp;- The permanent stage for subclass 188 Business Innovation and Investment visa that ensures <strong>Australian citizenship</strong> for the business investor</li>\r\n	<li><u><strong>SUBCLASS 132</strong></u> - Business Talent (Migrant) visas or Subclass 132 visas are Permanent visas granted to individuals who are commercially well established to create or develop an existing business in Australia.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><u><strong>Benifits of Immigration to Australia:</strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everyone nowadays is looking for new opportunities, and Australia&#39;s Immigration is the finest option. In Australia, you can finish your education, work, and establish a business. Simply by live in a different country, you can develop yourself in a variety of ways. It&#39;s an intriguing game to visit and live in a foreign region, as well as learn about a different culture and customs away from home. Before you know it, this will have changed your life in unfathomable ways, and you will be an entirely different person professionally. Here&rsquo;re more benefits:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Rich and abundant Flora and Fauna makes Australia an environmentally friendly country to inhabit in.</li>\r\n	<li>One of the top performing economies in terms of business dealings and educational attainment.</li>\r\n	<li>Flourishing center for trade and finance.</li>\r\n	<li>Cradle of Multiculturalism- Australia is a cultural center for indigenous and immigrant cultures. As a matter of fact, BBC has coined Australia as &lsquo;the lifestyle superpower&rsquo; of the globe.</li>\r\n	<li>Rapidly emerging educational hub.</li>\r\n	<li>Top class healthcare facilities aided with extensive medical research.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Home to the historical and ancient Aboriginal communities, who immigrated to Australia prior to European settlement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Documents Requirement for Immigrate&nbsp;to Australia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following are the fundamental documents necessary for skilled <strong>migration program</strong> from India to Australia:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Civil Status or Identity Documents, such as your voter ID, PAN Card, Birth certificate, and marriage certificate, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Experience Certificate proving you have sufficient work experience as required by the state Government.</li>\r\n	<li>Must pass the Language benchmark set by the Australian Government</li>\r\n	<li>If you have dependent Children, then you need to submit child birth documents.</li>\r\n	<li>Must provide a Police Clearance Certificate to prove that you were not charged against any criminal offence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<u><strong>Australia PR Point Calculator System:</strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The secular country, Australia is known for its well-defined and forthright immigration system. Once the EOI is submitted in SkillSelect, your profile will be rated and ranked on certain key factors, such as, Work Experience, Education, Language Proficiency in English, Age, and Sponsorship/Nomination from an Australian state or territory. The minimum points you need to qualify is 60 under the point-based visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Australian point calculator is one of these tools that gives candidates points based on different factors to help figure out how good they are. It is a tool that helps people who want to moving&nbsp;to Australia figure out how likely they are to meet the requirements for permanent residency (PR).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicants with a score of 65 or higher are qualified to register an application in Skill Select, the Government of Australia&#39;s platform for determining the eligibility of immigration candidates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Skilled Immigration Program of Australia employs a point-based system known as Skill Select, which is also known as the Australia PR point calculator. It is intended to attract highly qualified people who wish to live and work in Australia. The method has been constructed in such a way that it ensures the selection of just those applicants who have the necessary skills and experience to fill labor market gaps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>Fees and&nbsp;Costs of&nbsp;</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Australia&nbsp;PR visa fee for the Primary Applicant is 3755$ AUD, additionally if you have dependents then, for Spouse is 1875$ AUD, and per Child 940$ AUD.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about immigrating to Australia you can write an email on info@orangrglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '961587840_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTM=', 1, '2023-12-27 03:11:56'),
(94, 77, 'Australian PR Visa Requirements in 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>The Australian Department of Home Affairs (DHA) offers numerous easy-to-follow visa categories that suit the aspirants of all kinds. Right from Business Visas to Student Visas, from Tourist Visas to Skilled Worker Visas the number of visa kinds offered both permanent and provisional by the DHA is fairly big. To get any of these visas, it is compulsory to fulfill the obligatory&nbsp;Australia&nbsp;Visa<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Requirements<strong>&nbsp;</strong>and pay the necessary visa fees.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhile for the different permanent visa categories, you require fulfilling the compulsory <strong>Australian Permanent Residency</strong>&nbsp;requirements, which are comparatively harder to fulfill; for the impermanent categories, such as the Tourist Visas, you require fulfilling Temporary Visa requirements which are somewhat easier to meet.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOf all the categories of visas up-for-grabs, the Skilled Worker Visas enjoy widespread popularity. Offered through the General Skilled Migration (GSM) Programme, also known as SkillSelect, these visas necessitate fulfilling the compulsory Australia visa requirements<strong>&nbsp;</strong>to obtain them.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Eligibility Criteria for Australia Skilled Worker Visa</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All applicants, whether skilled or sponsored workers, must be younger than 45.</li>\r\n	<li>They must be of sound mind and character, as proven by a necessary character certificate.</li>\r\n	<li>They must have a good IELTS score.</li>\r\n	<li>They must choose a profession from the Australian SOL/CSOL to apply for.</li>\r\n	<li>They must achieve a score of more than 60 points based on important profile variables such as age, education, English proficiency, and work experience, among others.</li>\r\n	<li>They must have their skills evaluated by a Skill Assessment Authority.</li>\r\n	<li>They must fill out an Expression of Interest form and submit it to the Australian Immigration Authority online.</li>\r\n	<li>If they apply through the sponsored or nominated visa categories, they must obtain a nomination from an Australian state or territory.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Australia Visa Requirements for Skilled Worker Category</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nSkilled Worker Visas are permanent by nature and so you require fulfilling the mandatory <strong>Australia PR Visa</strong>&nbsp;Requirements for these to get them this year.</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Age</strong>: As per the requirements for emigrating to Australia<strong>,&nbsp;</strong>under the visa category in question, you must be less than 45 years old when you submit an application.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>English Language</strong>: You should have adequate skills in the English language to do a job in the Maple Leaf Country (not less than at a skilled stage).</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Nominated Profession</strong>: At the time of submitting your application, you need to nominate a skilled line-of-work, which suits your particular abilities &amp; qualifications. It is mandatory that the profession finds mention on the Australian Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Skills Assessment</strong>: Prior to you submit your petition, as per the Australian visa&nbsp;requirements and beyond for the specific visa category, you must have your skills duly assessed by the Australian reviewing organization chosen to review your nominated line-of-work (which will typically have particular qualifications conditions).</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Health Appraisal</strong>: As per the Australian visa application requirements<strong>&nbsp;</strong>for the particular category, your health must be practically good and you should not be suffering from any communicable disease that may present a danger to the well-being of the local Australians. You must have your health appraised by a panel doctor and go through a medical examination.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Character Appraisal</strong>: You should be of a good character and there should be no criminal charges slapped against you even as this too will be reviewed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Get The Minimum Required Points</strong>: You require getting not less than 65 points on the points test to meet the Australia&nbsp;visa requirements for the specific visa category.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In case you cannot fulfill the mandatory Australian Visa Requirements for the category and successfully sail through the Points Test, then you should not continue with a GSM application.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>How to Obtain a Permanent Resident Visa to Australia from India</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The Australian Skilled Worker Visa is an &quot;invitation only&quot; program, which means you must be invited by the Department of Home Affairs (former DIBP) before you may apply for a PR visa to Australia.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The first step is to declare your interest in the form of an expression of interest (EOI). You must determine how many points you may be entitled to under the Skill Select point scoring system as part of your EOI.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Although you are not needed to give proof to support your self-assessed point score during the EOI stage, if you are invited to apply, you will be asked to supply the papers to support your EOI points claim. Candidate must apply within 60 days after receiving an ITA (Invitation to Apply) and must demonstrate that at the time of application, you meet all visa criteria as well as your EOI points score.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>As a result, if you receive an invitation to apply but are unable to gather all of the required documents within 60 days, you will either run out of time and miss your chance to apply, or you will submit an application that will fail due to a lack of evidence.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>As you can see, it is critical to prepare the full case before to the EOI process. The first stage in preparing for your Australian Skilled Visa Eligibility is to identify a suitable skilled occupation and compute your points score.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Different Subclasses for Australia Skilled Worker Visa&nbsp;</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>There are various options and classifications by which an applicant might relocate to Australia. The following are examples of subclasses:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; <strong>Australia Skilled Independent Immigration Visa Subclass189</strong>: This visa is for individuals with in-demand skills and competencies in the country. It is a visa with a point system. And this visa is only for candidates who do not have sponsorship from a state or territory government or a relative who lives in Australia. It permits the individual to live and work in Australia and enjoy all of the services such as medical, educational, social, and so on. The individual can also petition for citizenship after spending a certain amount of time in the homeland.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; <strong>State Sponsored Visa (Sub Class190):</strong> The Sub Class 190 visa program is for candidates who have skills and abilities that are in demand in a specific state or territory of a country, as demonstrated by the independent states occupation list, but are unable to meet the eligibility criteria required to obtain a skilled independent visa. This visa is based on an invitation.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>It takes 60 points, which are computed based on age qualification, experience, and an English test.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>This visa permits you to live and work in Australia, as well as apply for Australian citizenship after spending a certain amount of time in a certain state.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; <strong>Skilled Regional (Provisional) Visa (Sub Class 489): </strong>This visa is a four-year temporary visa for applicants who have skills and abilities in demand in a specific state or territories of a country, as demonstrated by the independent states occupation list, but are unable to meet the criteria required to obtain a sponsored visa (subclass 190).</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>It is a visa that requires an invitation. This visa allows you to reside and work in Australia for four years and to travel as many times as the visa allows.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; <strong>Australia Employer Nomination Scheme Subclass 186:</strong> The employer nomination scheme for Australia is primarily intended for qualified temporary residents or trained personnel who are based abroad and may, at the time of application, be residing and actively engaged in a job. This visa is part of the group of employer-sponsored visas. Applicants may apply for the permit only after being nominated by an Australia-based recruiter/company.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; <strong>Business Talent in Australia (subclass 132):</strong> The Significant Business History Stream and the Venture Capital Entrepreneur Stream are subcategories of this visa category. The first is intended for successful business owners or partners who want to take on a key management role in a brand-new or established business. The number two position is reserved for individuals who have obtained at least AUD1 million in funding from an Australian venture capital firm.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Skilled Worker Visa for Australia from India</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The skilled worker migration process in Australia is becoming increasingly complicated. Because current rules are continuously being changed to reflect Australian policy requirements, and new rules are being implemented, application processes can quickly become complicated.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Orange Global Consultancy Immigration offers advice on how to assess eligibility for the Australian Skill Select visa at a basic level. However, to increase your chances of success, seek a personalized eligibility assessment from an immigration consultancy.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>For more information, Connect with our visa professionals who are ready to help you by calling 8336933522 or mail us at info@orangeglobalcunsultancy.in</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '226943381_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTQ=', 1, '2023-12-27 03:26:35'),
(95, 78, 'Top 5 Benefits of Australian PR Visa - Benefits of Australia PR 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>Australia, the name at once conjures up the image of a highly developed country inhabited by a progressive and healthy society consisting of people from almost all nations&nbsp;of the world. There are numerous benefits of <strong>Immigration to Australia</strong>&nbsp;which attracts the people from all over the world to make Australia their home. Also known as Down Under, and one of the leading immigration hotspot Australia is made up of individuals from nearly 200 nations, forming a society with diverse social, linguistic, and cultural skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia&nbsp;with its culturally diverse society and rapidly developing economy proffers opportunity to all those who wish to move and reside on its soils. At the present, close-to 22 million people stay in Australia&nbsp;even while the population is heading north continuously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>About a quarter, or 25% of the Australian population, consists of the non Australian citizens even as the same proves the Australia&rsquo;s gigantic immigration rate. The key factor behind this can be justified by understanding the many <strong>benefits of Immigration to Australia</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nTo begin with, the nation has a successful, tried, and trusted immigration strategy and well laid-out and easy-to-follow immigration schemes. Australia is a rather attractive immigration hotspot for business development and growth in the 21<sup>st</sup> Century. Thanks to the presence of massive natural resources and continuously developing economy, the country is a wonderful place for ambitious <strong>Businessmen and Investors</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australian immigration department (DIBP)&nbsp;offers an opportunity to qualified and gifted people to work or settle within the nation by carrying-out a point test. Successful businessmen can either make an investment in an existing company or set-up their own venture in the country and gain benefits from the nation&rsquo;s thriving and stable economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia requires more trained manpower to back and grow its development process and for the same the DIBP has made some of the most easy and hassle-free immigration policies for trained work force that one may come across anywhere. Employees with a valid offer of job can be sponsored by their recruiters even as the same tremendously simplifies the permit sanction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are numerous social benefits&nbsp;of immigration to Australia from India. The nation is strikingly attractive with a migrant friendly society. It boasts of first-class education and health systems, and Canberra offers significant funding to these fields. Australia&nbsp;has political stability and is one of the globe&rsquo;s most attractive destinations for good quality of life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Environmental Advantages of Migration to Australia comprise the presence of numerous climatic zones. Australia extends from the tropical far-north to the cool temperate climate of the south. The residents can get pleasure from different climates by travelling inside the nation&rsquo;s boundaries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia&nbsp;runs and manages a wide range of leisure activities and fun destinations. The citizens take pleasure in playing several varieties of sports. Apart from this, Australia has many natural wonders in the form of stunning beautiful beaches, exotic national parks, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia offers high living standards to its people. To smoothly cover large distances between its far-flung cities, the nation runs and manages efficient and quick transport facilities. All leading Australian cities are very well connected, via perfectly planned transport routes. People can freely and easily travel across the nation. For those who are fond of good food, Australia provides superlative restaurants with huge range of choices from across the globe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coming back to the issue of the <strong>benefits of Australia PR</strong>, the nation provides high standard and rationally priced accommodation, vis-&agrave;-vis other countries. Australia offers unhindered work rights to the partners of qualified sponsored manpower with both temporary and permanent entry permits. No restriction whatsoever exists on the number of visas that can be given to the gazette professionals and other trained aliens employing the well-known temporary entry scheme.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia has more supple and smooth temporary entry provisions, in relation to other immigration destinations. Post gaining a temporary visa and residing in the country for some time, it becomes rather easier for a candidate to gain permanent residency permit in Australia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Advantages of the Immigration to Australia!</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Qualified workers, entrepreneurs, students, and pleasure seekers every one of them are greeted with many <strong>benefits of Australia PR</strong>. Australia&nbsp;provides high quality lifestyle and lodging to the aliens. Students interested in pursuing higher studies find Australia to be the most suitable &amp; viable immigration hotspot.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Flexible, Easy-to-follow Immigration Laws</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia offers unrestricted work rights to the dependents of skilled sponsored workers with permanent and temporary entry visas. No restriction whatsoever are imposed on the number of visas to be offered to professionals and other trained visitors who exploit the temporary entry scheme. Australia&nbsp;also boasts of comparatively more flexible and updated temporary entry arrangements, in respect of most other destinations. Those on temporary principal permits typically manage to suitably apply for majority of the country&rsquo;s permanent resident visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Rewarding Employment Opportunities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For the trained workers from abroad, hardly any country can actually match Australia&rsquo;s amazing appeal. Australia has a drastically low rate of unemployment as compared to other nations. Australia actively welcomes migrants who have the necessary job expertise to fill its many vacancies in the labor force and add to the nation&rsquo;s economic success. Remarkably, more than 8 out of every 10 migrants who have skilled independent work permits manage to obtain a well-paying job within just six months of landing in the nation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Wonderful Geographical Surroundings</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia boasts of an unmatched natural beauty even as it has several species of plants and animals which are exclusively native to its soil. Australia&#39;s round-the-year warm weather makes it just an ideal destination for outdoor culture. It amply gets reflected in the lively lifestyle of its inhabitants. Migrants, eager to live a full life, find Australia just ideal for the same. Australia also possesses some of the globe&rsquo;s most stunning wilderness areas with some of them being designated national parks.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Amazing Culture</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For the culture conscious visitors, again not many countries can really match the unrivaled charm of Australia which is essentially an immigrant-friendly country. The country boasts of a rich kaleidoscope of arts, culture, with theater, concerts, art exhibits, films and cultural carnivals being some of the regular activities. Further boosting the immigration destination&rsquo;s appeal is the fact that it offers some of the best wine and food in the world. And its quality, and the rich cultural diversity of its populace, amply shines through its many world renowned eateries and restaurants, well situated throughout the nation&rsquo;s length and breadth.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>High Living Standards</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The standard of living in Australia, by and large, is comparatively higher, vis-&agrave;-vis other countries of the globe. Australia boasts of one of the most flourishing economies across the world. This economic growth is also well reflected in its people&rsquo;s lifestyle. The Australian cities of Melbourne and Sydney have an eclectic and pulsating lifestyle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard of living of a country is reviewed chiefly by three factors: its resources, well being of the population, and standard of living. The educational facilities and the health services offered by Australia to its people are one of the finest that one gets to see anywhere in the world. The World Health Organization (WHO) also certifies Australia&nbsp;for having a very low crime rate, as compared to most other nations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia&nbsp;also boasts of a housing facilities which is of a better standard. Still, pretty inexpensive when one compares it against other leading immigration destinations. Australia&rsquo;s schools, hospitals, and public transport clearly reveal the amazingly high standard of living for those residing in the nation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before planning to move to the nation, discover if you are, in reality, qualified. You can do the same, via filling an <strong>Online Immigration Assessment Form for Australia</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about immigrating to Australia you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '828623577_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTU=', 1, '2023-12-27 03:38:09');
