(96, 80, 'Immigration Services for Australia from India in 2023', '<p>It should come as no surprise that Australia is one of the hottest destinations in terms of immigration for many aspirants across the globe. This certainly has given a boost to the <strong>Australia Immigration</strong>&nbsp;services from India as more and more people are interested in migrating to this country for a better future.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAustralia is a multi-cultural ethnic country with a large number of Indians residing in various parts of the country. Despite, more and more Indians are heading towards Australia by leveraging visa services to Australia from established and well-known Immigration Consultants.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThese days, there is absolutely no dearth of immigration service providers in many parts of India who are proficient in providing quality immigration services at reasonable prices. One can easily approach them through a single Google search and they will get in touch with you to solve all your doubts and queries.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReaching to a professional consultant is always advisable as they have the relevant expertise on different visa categories one can choose from as per the requirement. These consultants make use of their extensive knowledge and experience to guide candidates regarding the evaluation process, credentials assessment, and visa options to opt.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt&rsquo;s a no secret that the formalities for filing a petition can be rather complicated and may be even time-consuming. It is all the more essential for the intended immigrant to keep themselves updated about the latest visa and immigration developments and amendments. Given this, it is all the more advisable to take the help of these service providers for the Australia Immigration Services.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSo, below are the visa categories that perspective candidates can choose from while apply for<strong> Australia Visa</strong>:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Australia&nbsp;Skilled Immigration&nbsp;Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a general visa category designed for skilled foreign professionals who wish to live and work in Australia. The program is operated under SkillSelect, which is an online point-based system that evaluates a candidate&rsquo;s eligibility to move to Australia based on their skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe purpose of this program is to attract highly-skilled and employable people to Australia, who can contribute to its growth and economy. Under this migration program, prospective migrants and workers can use their skills, professional experience, and educational background to settle in Australia.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Australian Family Migration Visas</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This visa category allows individuals to join their partners or families in Australia. Under this program, eligible persons can sponsor their immediate family members after meeting the certain set of requirements. The sponsor must be an Australian citizen, permanent resident, or an eligible New Zealand citizen.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Australian Family Migration visa is divided into the following categories:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Parent Visa</li>\r\n	<li>Dependent Children</li>\r\n	<li>Spouse Visa</li>\r\n	<li>Interdependent Partner Visa</li>\r\n	<li>Fiance Visa, and</li>\r\n	<li>Other Relatives</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nAustralia Business Visas<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Australia Business Visa&nbsp;program allows high net worth business owners, entrepreneurs, and investors to permanently settle in Australia via investment route. To succeed, one needs to submit a relevant investment plan to the Department of Home Affairs, and also needs to show a strong business background in their home country.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Australia Visit Visas</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Tourist stream visa (subclass 600) is a visitor visa that lets you to enter Australia as a tourist or a visitor. It is a temporary visa which can be used for the purpose of recreation activities, vacation, or visiting friends or family. There are multiple visa options to choose from to obtain a visa and enter the country for a limited period of time.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Australian Temporary Visas</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australian Temporary Visas are designed for individuals who wish to enter the nation on a temporary basis to contribute to its social, cultural, and economic development. With this visa, one can easily work and live in Australia for a limited time. Additionally, it is mandatory for the candidates to obtain a sponsorship by an Australia organization, which must be further approved by the Department of Home Affairs before filing for the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A Word of Advice</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>While you choose one Australia Immigration Conusltant for yourself, beware of the many fraud service providers. Before you decide to pay them and seek their so-called professional services, check their credibility and success record for immigration services to Australia. Do not fall a prey to any advertisement. Do solid research and hire the consultant who has a very good record and who is trustworthy.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThough you may be required to pay a little more, please remember: your very life is at stake! Wrong guidance and/or faulty support from a rookie may &lsquo;kill&rsquo; your dreams. Even if, by luck, you manage to move to Australia, later on your visa may be cancelled if your papers, and/or the information furnished along with these, are found fake. It is, therefore, strictly advisable that only after you are 100% sure of your choice, make the final decision!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhile you are reading this page you might consider taking help from Orange Global consultancy for your Australia Immigration process, helping people get settled overseas on permanent residency basis. Send your CV to <strong>info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</strong>&nbsp;and the experts will shortly get in touch with you to help you with your Australia Immigration Plan.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', '', '355693066_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTY=', 1, '2023-12-27 03:44:19'),
(97, 79, 'New Australia Points System of Subclass 189/190/491', '<p>The myriad Australia immigration Programs have been conceptualised to strategically select only the most qualified applicants. Certain filters have been designed to ensure that only desirable profiles that can significantly contribute to the economy are invited to pursue the <strong><a href=\"https://www.abhinav.com/australia-visa.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">A</a>ustralia PR Process</strong>. One such tool is the Australia points calculator, which allocates points to the candidate based on several factors to determine their potential. This tool is also useful for immigration aspirants to estimate their ability to fulfil the <strong><a href=\"https://www.abhinav.com/australia/Australian-Immigration-Requirements.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">A</a>ustralia PR requirements</strong>. Candidates who can score 65 or more Australia PR points may lodge their application in SkillSelect &ndash; the Australian government portal that determines eligibility of applicants.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Points-tested Visa Categories</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are four visa subclasses that evaluate the eligibility of applicants based on the <strong><a href=\"https://www.abhinav.com/australia-immigration/check-your-eligibility-for-australia.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">A</a>ustralia PR Points Calculator</strong>. Two of these points-tested visa categories are direct pathways to permanent residency Australia, while two are provisional visas which can eventually lead to securing Australia PR.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) Visa (Subclass 188)</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled Independent visa (Subclass 189)</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled Nominated Visa (Subclass 190)</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled Work Regional (Provisional) visa (Subclass 491)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Selection Factors of the Australia Point System</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe criteria under each points-tested visa subclass is distinct, designed specifically to assess the aspirant&rsquo;s ability to fulfil the purpose for which they are being granted a visa. Under each stream, points are granted based on targeted parameters which determine the potential of an applicant to contribute to the local and national economy.&nbsp;The assessment criteria and minimum requirements of the point system are detailed below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Australia Points System Changes </u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With effect from 16<sup>th</sup> Nov 2019, the Points System for Australian General Skilled Migration Visas (Subclass 189 visa, Subclass 190 visa and Subclass 491 visa) experienced certain changes. Below are the changes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Specialist education qualification</strong>: Candidates with Master&rsquo;s Degree by research / Doctorate degree from an Australian educational institution, can obtain <strong>10 points</strong> now. Earlier, it was <strong>5 points</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Partner skills: </strong>Candidates having skilled spouse under the age of 45 can acquire two set of points:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li><strong>Spouse Language &amp; Skill Assessment: </strong>If you spouse competent is having competent language skills and positive skill assessment along with his/her occupation falling under Skilled Occupation List (SOL), can get <strong>10 points</strong>. Earlier, it was <strong>5 points</strong>.</li>\r\n		<li><strong>Spouse language proficiency:</strong> If your spouse or de facto partner is having competent language skills, then you can get additional <strong>5 points</strong>.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Spouse Adaptability:</strong> There is two-fold points change in the Spouse Adaptability:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>If you are single, then you are entitled for <strong>additional 10 points. </strong>Earlier, there were <strong>no points </strong>for single applicant.</li>\r\n		<li>If you have a spouse or de facto partner with either Australian citizenship or Australia permanent residency, then you are entitled for <strong>additional 10 points</strong>. Earlier, there were <strong>no points </strong>for Australian Citizen or PR Spouse.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><strong>State Nomination/Sponsorship:</strong> If you obtain nomination by a state/territory or sponsorship by a family member, you can get <strong>15 points</strong>. Earlier, it was <strong>10 points.</strong> Currently, the 15 points criteria are applicable to Subclass 491 visa and Subclass 190 visa only.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>It is essential to keep in mind that the point system is simply one of the numerous requirements that must be met in order to be eligible for<strong> immigration to Australia</strong>. The obtaining of an Australian visa by an Indian citizen can throw open a plethora of doors leading to potential prospects. The aspirant can submit an application through SkillSelect if it has been determined that all requirements are capable of being met. Following an appropriate review of the candidate&#39;s application, the candidate may be extended an invitation to submit an application for the applicable visa subclass. Finding out how many points you have is the first thing you need to do in order to increase your chances of being granted immigration.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n	<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n	<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about Australia PR&nbsp;Points System for 189/190/491 you can write an email on <strong>info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</strong>&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '816176762_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTc=', 1, '2023-12-27 03:51:55'),
(98, 81, 'Australia PR Points Calculator for Skilled Migration', '<p>The Skilled Migration program for Australia follows a point-based system known as SkillSelect or Australia PR Points Calculator. The system is designed to attract highly-qualified professionals who want to live and work in Australia. The system is created in such a way that it considers only those applicants who have the right skills and experience to best meet the labor shortage needs of the country. There are different types of streams available under the skilled migration visas that require applicants to score minimum<strong> Australia PR Points</strong>&nbsp;in order to qualify for the <strong>Australia PR Visa</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The points distributed under the Australia Immigration Points Calculator system are linked with an applicant&rsquo;s ability to make economic contributions to Australia. The system considers various factors such as age, education, work experience, language proficiency, and adaptability factors, before awarding scores to a profile. For skilled visas, it&rsquo;s important for a candidate to at least score 65 points to maximize their maximum chances of receiving an ITA.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below are the visa categories for which Australia PR points calculator is extensively used:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Subclass 189 visa</li>\r\n	<li>Subclass 190 visa</li>\r\n	<li>Subclass 491 visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h6>Subclass 189 visa</h6>\r\n\r\n<p>The Skilled independent visa subclass 189 is a permanent visa for anyone with in-demand talents in the country&#39;s flourishing labor sector. Candidates are granted permits using a Points Based System (not sponsored). It allows holders to come to Australia if they have good English language skills, work experience, and qualifications in a vocation in high demand in the famed immigration hotspot. The permit uses a points system to select visa applicants who are in high demand in Australia&#39;s national labor market.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo put it another way, the skilled independent subclass 189 is essentially a points-based permanent permit/visa, despite the fact that it is intended for trained/qualified experts from abroad and tradespeople who do not have sponsorship from an Australian recruiter/firm, a territory or state, or a family member. The bearer of the (Sub-class 189 visa Australia) Immigration Permit has the right to live and work in Australia on a permanent basis anywhere in the country. Significantly, candidates for the visa might include some of their family members in their visa petitions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h6>Subclass 190 visa</h6>\r\n\r\n<p>The Skilled Nominated Visa Subclass 190, also known as Skilled Immigration to Australia, is a points-based Permanent Residence Permit intended primarily for skilled experts and tradespeople with nominations from an Australian territory or state. Visa holders are allowed to live and work anywhere in the sponsoring state/territory. Applicants may also reveal the names of some of their family members in their visa applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h6>Subclass 491 visa</h6>\r\n\r\n<p>The Skilled Regional visa (subclass 489), one of the key Australia Permanent Residency paths, has been superseded by the newly established Subclass 491 Skilled Work Regional (Provisional) Visa. The Australian Department of Home Affairs established this visa category, which becomes effective on November 16, 2019.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis is a point-based visa designed specifically for talented people who want to live and work in a regional area of Australia. You are also sponsored by an Australian State or Territory Government or an eligible family member residing in a designated regional area of Australia with this visa.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith this visa, you can stay in Australia for up to five years. Australia&#39;s designated area is any section of the country other than Sydney, Brisbane, Gold Coast, Perth, and Melbourne. Newcastle, Wollongong, and the NSW Central Coast are designated regional zones, as is the Subclass 489 Skilled Regional visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Eligibility Criteria for Australia PR Score (65-Point Calculation Method)</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The Australia PR point calculator is based on a number of variables. Each factor is granted a score. Your points total will be the sum of the amount of boxes you can check off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h6>Partner Skills (Maximum 10 points)</h6>\r\n\r\n<p>In certain circumstances, your spouse can help you earn points.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You get 10 points if you are single (no spouse or de facto partner).</li>\r\n	<li>You gain 10 points if your partner is an Australian citizen or permanent resident.</li>\r\n	<li>If your spouse is under 45 years old, has a &#39;competent&#39; score on the English proficiency test, is in the same occupational code and visa subclass as you, and has a positive appraisal of your skills, you will gain 10 PR points.</li>\r\n	<li>You earn 5 points if your partner is fluent in English but does not have the same talents as you or does not belong to the same visa subclass as you.</li>\r\n	<li>Australian Specialist Education (5 points)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>With at least two academic years in a relevant field, a Master&#39;s by research or Doctorate from an Australian educational institution will get you 5 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h6>Study in Regional or Metropolitan Area (5 points)</h6>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to study in regional Australia or a low-population location, you will be awarded 5 points, most likely in an attempt by the Australian government to encourage people to settle in regional areas.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOther factors that can get you extra points include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you know a community language, you will receive 5 Australian PR Points.</li>\r\n	<li>You get 5 points if you completed a professional year in Australia in your specified skilled occupation for at least 12 months before receiving your invitation to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>You get 5 points if you have a State Nomination (190 visa).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '858503952_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTg=', 1, '2023-12-27 03:58:45'),
(99, 82, 'Australia Skilled Select - Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)', '<p><strong>Q: How expressing an interest through Skill Select and presenting my profile are useful for me, from sponsorship perspectives? </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> These activities could mean the difference between your selection and non selection. Under the new format offered by Skill Select, when you do so, your whole information becomes accessible to the recruiters exploring the available talents, for recruitment purposes. If an employer from Australia finds your profile really interesting, he may contact you and discuss the existing opportunities. This could also improve your chances of obtaining sponsorship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: What is the invitation&rsquo;s validity time and what takes place, post the expiry of the invitation?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> The invitation&rsquo;s validity period is 60 days. The petition should be submitted to the <strong>Department of Immigration and Border Protection (DIBP)</strong>&nbsp;inside the said duration. In case the profile is not picked-up inside two years of the EOI&rsquo;s submission, the petition for EOI will lapse even as the same will be removed from the data bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Can I present a petition with 60 points even if I gain no points in the IELTS?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Yes! You can submit a petition under such a state-of-affairs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: In the Subcategory 489, in case an individual concludes his mandatory stay of 4 years in Australia, can he get PR inside that 4 years, and incase he fails to obtain PR, what occurs?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> In such a case it is crucial that he has been residing and doing a job in the identified state/region for not less than two years in the appropriate profile. He can submit a petition for Australia PR Visa after two years, and may gain the same in case he is fruitfully employed in the state, and in case he is not found guilty of any wrong doings during the period. If he is found guilty of breaching the terms of the 489 Permit, he will be denied PR.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Do we require doing an EOI &amp; state sponsored at the same time?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> An aspirant can submit an EOI submission, and also apply for state sponsorship, and after approval is given for the latter, the EOI will be duly updated. The <strong>Department of Immigration and Border Protection (DIBP)</strong> will proceed to offer an invite following these developments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Is an offer of employment obligatory for the Subcategory 489?&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> You are advised to check the particular state requirements since some Australian states could necessitate a validated Job offer from state sponsorship under the Sub-category 489. A duly validated employment offer is compulsory to gain state sponsorship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Can I change my visa subcategory after the EOI lodgment?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong>&nbsp;Yes, you can do so! It is possible to update your EOI with any details through the two year time. You will gain an opportunity to keep updating your profile in Skill Select anytime when you wish. You also have the right to generate on your EOI continuously as your papers/certificates ought to be with more employment experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Should the ACS &amp; the IELTS be legitimate at the time of invitation?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Yes! However, in the backdrop of the fact that the EOI will be held in the bank for two years, the same may not pose any issues to most of the candidates. Still, in certain cases where individuals have gone through the skills assessment/IELTS much before the EOI lodgment, the same could present some problems, particularly for the IELTS. It also denotes that the EOI should be filed in as soon as the results for the IELTS &amp; skills evaluation are obtainable. In case a decision is not made inside two years, the petition will cease to be part of EOI bank. The ACS skills appraisal will also expire post two years, and in case the candidate is eager to re-file, he will require getting evaluation done. He will also have to present a fresh EOI submission. Though the EOI form talks about the IELTS report has a validity of 36 months, the IELTS report has a validity of two years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Are there separate lists of professions for State sponsored &amp;Regional sponsored, or is it advisable to follow one list?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> There are two types of occupations lists. One is the <strong>Occupations lists</strong>&nbsp;with Schedule 1 and 2 which is called CSOL. For independent skilled migration, the professions given in SOL 1 For State Sponsored and <strong>Regional</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Schemes</strong>, only Schedule 2 professions can be duly followed. Apart from this, in case of state and regional programs, it is essential that the claimed line-of-work is also given in state/regional lists. Against this backdrop, for independent skilled overseas movement, you will refer to the professions given in SOL 1, and for state/regional sponsorship, you will refer to Schedule 1 and &nbsp;2 AND state lists.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: What&rsquo;s the basis of selection from the EOI? Is it entirely based on points?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> It is based in ranking inside the pool which will keep on changing. In the backdrop of the fact that an EOI submission can be analyzed by recruiters/state/federal bureaus, the EOI may not be wholly based on points.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case a recruiter/firm or state is happy with a profile that occupies a not-too-high position in the pool ranking, the same will still be preferred. Still, it is essential that every selected profile fulfills the bare minimum points-requirement &ndash; 60 or 65 points whatever the case could be.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: How the petition shall be selected from the EOI bank and what&rsquo;s the estimated time period?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> The submission will be in the bank for a period of two years, and can be seen anytime during the two years time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The petition will be chosen from the bank depending on when the same is chosen and duly shortlisted by a recruiter/state/region/federal bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The submission will be given a position, on the basis of the points that you obtain. The ranking will continue to undergo changes as fresh petitions continue to land in the pool. Hence, the petitions that could be gaining higher points (65 points or above) will occupy a higher rank. At certain times, the ranking may be decided by the line-of-work to which a candidate belongs to, even while those who are from extreme shortage profession could be given higher ranks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is NO estimated time period that can be given to a candidate. His profile can be chosen at any time, or not chosen at all for the duration of the two years for which his profile will occupy a place in the pool. In case he is not chosen, he loses the amount spent on Skills appraisal, and the IELTS Test, and also what he has offered as consulting charges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: The states continue to improve the laws, and in case the EOI is shown today with an one specific set of requirements then what will take place in case it takes a very long time even as the state concludes the quota or amends any conditions?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Generally, the states follow the set of rules fixed by the Federal/Central Government, except for picking up the professions they prefer for sponsorship, and the IELTS test requirement for every line-of-work. Save for these two areas, the states are powerless to do much about &ldquo;regulatory&rdquo; improvements. The eventual visa is proffered by the federal/central administration, irrespective of state/regional administration rules.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Does profession has no meaning at all in case of a family member sponsorship?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> It is essential that the aspirant belongs to either Schedule 1. It is also vital that the relative is residing in the chosen area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Is the sub-category 489 a 4-year or a 3-year permit? Can I submit a petition for the PR Permit on the basis of the present laws or the one that will prevail post 3 or 4 years? Shall I file a petition before my permit loses its validity?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> <strong>Sub-class 489</strong> is a 4-year Permit. You will be qualified to submit a petition for PR on the basis of the laws applicable at the time of submitting your submission. You have the right to file a petition pose two years for PR after arriving in the state/region, but prior to the end of 4 years when your permit loses its validity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: In the case of state sponsorship, the major candidate, partner, and kids will stay and do a job in the specific state. However, can kids pursue studies outside that state&rsquo;s territorial limits?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> It is very doubtful that the advantages of funded education will be obtainable outside the states that have offered sponsorship to the candidate. It is important that the family resides in the selected state/region for which the particular permit was offered.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: What to do in case I come across some technical difficulties while employing Skill Select?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Such circumstances are not uncommon. But no need to worry! , You are advised to visit the Support page of the Skill Select before pressing the button given for the &lsquo;<strong>Skill Select Support</strong>&rsquo;. The same will provide all-inclusive data, comprising Skill Select user guides, technical FAQs, etc. You will not have more than one chance to access your EOI account. Besides, you can only mention 1 e-mail address so that you can remain in touch with Skill Select for any invitation objects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: What is the compulsory pass marks meant for the points based permits?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Visa subclasses 189, 190 and 489 &ndash; 60 points;</li>\r\n	<li>Visa subclasses 885, 886 and 487 - 65 points;</li>\r\n	<li>Visa Subclass 188 (business innovation &amp; investment visa) - 65 points</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Who accesses the specifics of the Skill Select&rsquo; aspirants?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> This actually depends on the choices(s) made by the candidate in the EOI petition. In case you have settled for an employer sponsored or state or regional permit, employer/state/regional may review your profile in the EOI bank. In case you have opted for the independent or family sponsored permit, Skill Select will exclusively utilize your specifics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Can I submit an EOI, even if am yet to sail through the language test for English &amp; skills evaluation from the relatedorganization?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Before you submit a completed EOI, and in case you are pre-setting an EOI for a points based permit, successfully clear the test meant for the English language &amp; also skills appraisal. Even if you may not be required to attach the germane papers to the EOI, present the correct data in your EOI. Guarantee that it is similar to the one given on the supporting documents.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Can a candidate find-out his ranking in the EOI pool?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> No! It cannot be done. The ranking position continues to undergo key changes, thanks to the filing or the withdrawal of other EOIs from the Skill Select.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Can I present an EOI in Australia?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Yes of course! But you need to satisfy the pre-decided conditions. It needs to be borne in mind that the EOI is not a permit submission, and you will not be given a bridging permit/visa. In case you gain an invite to present a visa submission, you have to satisfy the requirements to get the visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Is it compulsory to offer a written statement in the EOI?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> The answer is in the negative. The EOI will ask questions--the basis of which will be the permit you may be interested in. Your answer will have adequate statistics for your EOI to be successfully presented.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: In case I fail to get an invite, can I be get my money back spent for the skills appraisal&amp; the language test for English?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> The answer again is in the negative. Only because you have filed an EOI does not mean you will get an invite. You, as an applicant, have to bear the expenses while preparing your EOI and in case the petition fails to get selected from the pool then you will not gain any refund whatsoever for the expenses incurred for appearing for the IELTS Test &amp; assessment for skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: What to do if the situation, circumstances, or information undergoes any improvements, post the submission of my EOI?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Update you EOI to depict any freshly gained qualification or experience that may have come your way even while the SkillSelect will notice it, and in case appropriate, will automatically update your position.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: What if an invitation is not mailed to me to submit a submission for permit, will I have the review rights?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> You will be denied the right in such a case. The review process is meant for only those qualified people whose submissions for a permit have been dismissed. In this case, the EOI is not a permit submission.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Are some other avenues available that I can utilize for posting objects?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer :</strong> Frankly, NO! You can only use the online facility Skill Select for EOI submission. Aspirants, who are sent in invitations to file a petition for a permit/visa, the particulars given in the EOI will be exploited as part of their petitions. It is vital that the aspirants suitably verify their claims and present evidence when they suitably submit a petition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Can I employ the professional services of an immigration agent of Australia, for the object of presenting the EOI petition and, in case the petition is chosen out of the EOI bank, for the remaining part of the immigration procedure?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Answer : </strong>Yes you can! You are absolutely free to do the same. You can employ the professional services of an immigration advisor to assist you with the EOI submission process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about immigrating to Australia you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '165183477_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=OTk=', 1, '2023-12-27 04:04:05'),
(100, 83, 'Australia Immigration Visa For Indians in 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>Australia and the Department of Home Affairs (DHA) which supervises and controls the process of Australia Immigration run a very efficient and innovative visa application system in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its SkillSelect Programme for the General Skilled Migration (GSM) offers the golden opportunity to the deserving skilled candidates from across the globe to settle in<strong> Australia permanently.</strong> Applicants must assess their credentials and suitability for Immigration to Australia on certain parameters, using the <strong>Australian PR Points Calculator</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Basically, two main pathways to obtaining Work Visas are available. For one, sponsorship is required and it is mandatory that a firm is ready to sponsor the visa applicant. The sponsoring firm must prove that it&rsquo;s obligatory to have the applicant. For the next option, it is compulsory that the candidate has a skill which is in such high demand in the nation that the Australian administration is ready to offer an invitation to the skilled applicant having the necessary skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Australia PR Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a &quot;Permanent Resident&quot; visa that is only available to those who are not Australian citizens. Not only is the process highly systematic and organized, but it is also advanced enough to evaluate applications based on an individual&#39;s qualifications for <strong>immigration and citizenship</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once granted, a PR visa allows the person to live in Australia indefinitely. In addition, a five-year travel permit is included. This travel facility allows the bearer to depart and return to Australia until its expiration date.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Permanent residents enjoy the same rights and privileges as citizens, including access to subsidized or free medical and legal care. A PR visa holder does not have the freedom or ability to vote in state/territorial or federal elections unless they registered before 1984.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After a certain period of time, a permanent resident is eligible for citizenship. When this period is up, the candidate must take a citizenship test and complete a few more requirements. It can take anywhere from 3-12 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It should be noted that a PR visa can be revoked at the discretion of a competent minister if the holder is found guilty of a criminal offense.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Australia PR Visa Categories</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTake a look at the below mentioned are the different types of visa category which you can choose from as part of the <strong>Australia PR</strong>!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1) Skill Based PR Employer Nomination Scheme Subclass 186 Visa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2) Skilled Independent Subclass 189 Visa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3) Business Innovation and Investment Subclass 188 Visa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4) Regional Sponsored Migration Scheme Subclass 187 Visa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5) Business Talent Visa Subclass 132 Visa 6) Skilled Nominated Visa Subclass 190 Visa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Work Visas may be either permanent or temporary, depending on the state-of-affairs and <strong>immigration system</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThose who manage to get the required cut-off o points get an Invitation to Apply (ITA) for Australia Immigration and Permanent Residency (PR) though getting an ITA is no guarantee that one will certainly get an Australia immigration visa. An ITA basically just enables the candidates to apply for a visa. The recipients will get a visa only if they can successfully fulfill the mandatory requirements for the category under which they may apply later after getting the ITA.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe visa candidates have numerous other good visa options also, such as Business Visa, Student Visa, Spouse Visa, Child Visa, Aged Parent Visa, to name a few.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBusiness Visas especially are much sought after. The DHA offers numerous kinds of Business Visas with Business Innovation and Investment - Subclass 188 (Provisional), Business Innovation and Investment - Subclass 888 (Permanent), and Business Talent - Subclass 132 being just some of them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThese Australia Immigration Visa<strong> </strong>options<strong> </strong>are basically for those who are either launching or running a business or venture in Down Under.&nbsp; Moreover, one may obtain visas for other business associated objects, like investing, for instance.&nbsp; These are though not very easy to get. The reason: there is a weighty amount of paperwork to illustrate the strict terms &amp; conditions are fulfilled.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe applicants must check the latest <strong>Australian Immigration News&nbsp;</strong>for the most recent updates on the visa and immigration rules involving Australia immigration Consultants. The reason: these change periodically and if one does not keep self well updated he may not be able to submit an application that&rsquo;s in sync with the new immigration rules.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor example, one will learn that now the 457 Visa is not available and it its place one has the Temporary Skilled Shortage (TSS) Work Visa.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor successful and hassle-free <strong>Immigration to Australia from India</strong>, aspirants are advised to contact experts dealing with Immigration Australia. These professionals will help and guide them with the somewhat long draw out and difficult&nbsp;Immigration and Visa<strong> </strong>process for Australia<strong>.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Requirements for an Australia PR Visa</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>An Australia PR visa is a point-based system. As a result, obtaining it is a combination of offline and online actions. As per the <strong>latest news</strong> and guidelines, following are the essential requirements:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>1. Keep the documents close at hand</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Aside from educational and ordinary travel paperwork, an individual needs two primary documents:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; IELTS (International English Language Testing System) score to determine an applicant&#39;s English proficiency.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A skill assessment is a test done by a person in charge to see how skilled an applicant is in a certain field.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>2. Choose an Appropriate Visa</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Recognize that there are various forms of <strong>skilled migrant</strong> PR visas in Australia. As a result, it is critical that an applicant select the one that best meets his or her needs. The most prevalent types are:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; State Nominated PR Visa (Subclass 190)</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Non-sponsored visa subclass 189</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; Subclass 186 - Employer-sponsored visa</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>3. Select an SOL Profession</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>After selecting a specific PR visa, an applicant must select a vocation from SOL (Australia Skilled Occupation list).</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>4. Use the Point-Based System to Apply</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>After completing the aforementioned formalities, the applicant must apply directly to Australia&#39;s point-based system. To do so, he or she must file an EOI (Expression of Interest) online using the Australian Skill Select System for <strong>skilled visa</strong>. Skill Select is a web-based system that stores and manages an applicant&#39;s personal information such as name, age, gender, work experience, language ability, qualification, and so on.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The system assigns points based on the profile factors. To apply for a PR visa using the system, an applicant&#39;s total score must be at least 60 points. The bigger the number of points, the better the chances of receiving an invitation to apply for a PR visa.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>5. Character and Health Requirements</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Aside from the aforementioned standards, an applicant must also meet his or her character and health requirements. An applicant&#39;s moral character must be strong, and he or she must be mentally able to work and live in Australia.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>The Advantages of a PR Visa to Australia</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A PR visa holder has total freedom to pursue the educational course of his or her choice.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; As a PR visa holder, you can work and live <strong>Australia permanently</strong> and travel freely within and outside of the country.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A PR visa holder has access to the Australian Government&#39;s health insurance.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A PR visa holder may apply for Australian citizenship if the qualifying criteria are met. &bull; A PR visa holder may sponsor a family member&#39;s visa, which can be either temporary or permanent.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A person with a PR visa can also get social security benefits.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; A PR visa holder has the right to work for any employer and the flexibility to travel to New Zealand or apply for their visa.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>If you want to learn more about <strong>immigration and citizenship</strong> of Australia,&nbsp;send an email to info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in and one of our experienced immigration consultants will contact you to answer your questions and concerns. You can also call us at <strong>+91 8336933522.</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', '136747092_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTAw', 1, '2023-12-27 04:23:16');
