(101, 84, 'Subclass 189 Australia Skilled Independent Visa - Skilled Migrant Visa', '<div>\r\n<h2>Skilled Independent Visa Subclass 189</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe Skilled independent visa subclass 189 is the permanent visa for all the individuals having skills in demand, in the country&rsquo;s thriving labour market. The permit is proffered to the candidates, via Points Based System (not sponsored). It enables the holders to immigrate to Australia, in case they have a good proficiency in the English language, employment experience, and also qualifications in a vocation in need in the famous immigration hotspot. The permit employs the points test to choose visa applicants who are in a field of high demand in the national labour market of Australia.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo put it differently, the skilled independent subclass 189 is essentially a points-based permanent permit/visa, even as it is meant for those trained/qualified experts from abroad &amp; tradespersons, who do not have any sponsorship from any of these an Australian recruiter/firm, a territory or state, a family member. The holder of the (Sub-class 189 visa Australia) Immigration Permit is entitled to reside and get professionally involved on a permanent basis anywhere throughout the nation. Significantly, the aspirants for the visa can mention some of their family members in the petitions presented for the visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Eligibility Criteria for the Skilled Independent Visa Subclass 189</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The Skilled Independent Subclass 189 visa is not available to everyone who wants it. The 189 Skilled visa subclass has few established eligibility conditions for applicants. The following qualifications are required:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; You must have been asked to apply for the visa subclass 189, and you must submit an expression of interest to indicate your plan to apply for the visa subclass 189.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; For the visa subclass 189, your nominator should be a State Government agency or any Australian territory. You may apply for this visa only if you have been nominated in accordance with the requirements.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; If you are requested to apply, you must be younger than 45 years old.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; When applying for the Skilled Independent Visa subclass 189, you must certify that you have the necessary skills as determined by the Australian skills assessment body.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; You must meet the English qualifying criteria and be fluent in the English language at the required level.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&bull; To be qualified for visa subclass 189, you must have a score of at least 65 points in your Expression of Interest.</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Requirements of Australia Visa Subclass 189 (Skilled Independent):</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Only those individuals can befittingly present a petition who possess an invite from the concerned organization. To suffice the Australia 189<strong> </strong>visa requirements<strong>,</strong> it is vital that the candidate:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submits an Australia Expression of Interest (EOI);&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Possess a vocation/line-of-work, given on the concerned skilled profession list;</li>\r\n	<li>Possess a suitable skills assessment for the given profession;</li>\r\n	<li>Is less than 50 years of age when he gets the invite;</li>\r\n	<li>Satisfies the compulsory English language requirements;</li>\r\n	<li>Obtains a minimum of 60 test points; and</li>\r\n	<li>Satisfies the character &amp; health conditions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nIt is essential that, before the submission for Australia Skilled Independent (Sub-class 189)<strong> </strong>Immigration Visa, the aspirant must submit an Expression of Interest (EOI), through Australia Skill Select. It is crucial that the Australia EOI submission has the information regarding positive skills evaluation from the concerned skills assessment group, and also the essential details related to the IELTS Test&nbsp;score.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Benefits of Australia Visa Subclass 189 (Skilled Independent):<br />\r\n&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This popular permit enables the holders and minor aspirants (if any) mentioned in the permit submission to reside as permanent residents in Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>Since it is basically a permanent residence visa, the holders are entitled to stay in the country for an indefinite period.</li>\r\n	<li>Australian PR Holder is entitled to all the benefits like access to healthcare which is Australian government subsidized, access to social security benefits, basic and advances education and the person owning this visa can also apply for Australian citizenship.</li>\r\n	<li>The Visa holder can convert his Australia Permanent resident&nbsp;citizenship status once he completes his stay of 4 years.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Subclass 189 Point Test Calculator / Australia Point System</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to acquire the Permanent Residency in Australia, an applicant must secure the required score of minimum 65 points under the subclass 189 points test calculator. The applicants are awarded certain points under the <strong>Australian PR Points</strong>&nbsp;system based on the parameters of Age, English Language Proficiency, Educational Qualification, Work Experience etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Subclass 189 Visa Processing Time</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The entire application procedural time under the 189 Skilled &ndash; Independent Points-tested visa will take around 6 to 11 months to receive PR Permit post submission of your application.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Subclass 189 Visa Cost / Fees</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The visa fees for Primary Applicant under the skilled independent visa subclass 189<strong> </strong>is 3755 AUD<br />\r\n<br />\r\nInterested in presenting a submission for Australia Skilled Independent (Sub-class 189) Immigration Visa? If yes, please share with us:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your updated CV</li>\r\n	<li>Your partner&rsquo;s bio-data, in case applicable</li>\r\n	<li>Particulars of kids, in case applicable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Do I Apply for Visa Subclass 189?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Only on invitation can you apply for the skilled independent visa (subclass 189). Invitees must apply within 60 days of receiving the invitation. Only after the SkillSelect assessment can the procedure move further. Higher first exam scores will boost your chances of acquiring this visa. Based on the timing of submission and other factors, the immigration service may examine or prioritize applications. Close relatives and family members can also be included in the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are applying for the Skilled Independent Visa (Subclass 189), Orange Global Consaultancy Immigration can guide you for all your immigration related queries. We are a team of certified migration experts for Australia, who have thorough knowledge of all the visa subclasses and point based immigration system of Australia.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll you need to do is fill the <strong>Free Assessment Form</strong>, our experts at Orange Global Consultancy Immigration will assess your profile and give you a call back with the complete assessment report and key suggestion and advice as to how you can secure your subclass 189 Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about immigrating to Australia you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '534254320_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTAx', 1, '2023-12-27 04:39:09'),
(102, 85, 'Australia Skilled Nominated Visa Subclass 190', '<div>\r\n<h2>Skilled Immigration to Australia</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe Skilled nominated visa subclass 190 also widely known as Skilled Immigration to Australia is fundamentally a points-based Permanent Residence<a href=\"https://www.abhinav.com/australia-visa.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;</a>Permit, and principally meant for those skilled experts and trades people who have nominations from an Australian territory or a state. The visa holders may reside and get professionally involved anywhere throughout the specific sponsoring state/territory. The applicants also have a right to reveal the names of some of their family members in their visa-petitions.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits of Subclass 190 Visa Australia</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The permit enables you and any your family members, who have also been proffered the permit, to, among others:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Reside in the country for an indefinite time-frame.</li>\r\n	<li>Get fruitfully and professionally engaged and pursue studies in the country.</li>\r\n	<li>Register for Medicare the nation&rsquo;s popular and widely used plan for health associated care &amp; costs.</li>\r\n	<li>File a petition for the prized and the much sought-after Australian citizenship (of course, in case you are qualified).</li>\r\n	<li>Offer sponsorship to entitled family members for PR.</li>\r\n	<li>Make a trip to and from Australia, for a period of 5 years, from the date the permit is provided (post that time, you will require a Resident Return Visa (RRV) or a new permit to come back to the country).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Who Can Apply for a Subclass 190 Australian Visa?</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The following list shows who can apply for a subclass 190 visa and what they need to do.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Even though this is a specific group, a lot of people will fit into this section.</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Comes from a job on the list of occupations for the 190 subclass visa nomination</li>\r\n	<li>It is possible to do a good job skill assessment.</li>\r\n	<li>They should get at least 65 points.</li>\r\n	<li>The person is chosen by a state or territory of Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>Post an EOI, and you&#39;ll be asked to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Age ranges from 18 to 44</li>\r\n	<li>You speak English well.</li>\r\n	<li>One who is healthy and has good character.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><u><strong>Requirements of Australia Visa Subclass 190:</strong></u><br />\r\n<br />\r\nPetitions for the permit are only, and exclusively, by invites. For the invitation objects, it is vital that the aspirants, among others:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Present an Australia Expression of Interest (EOI), and also be suitably nominated/sponsored by an Australian state/territory;</li>\r\n	<li>Be professionally associated with a vocation/line-of-work which finds a place on the applicable list of the skilled professions;</li>\r\n	<li>Possess a suitable skills appraisal for the given profession;</li>\r\n	<li>Be less than 50 years at the time the invite is proffered;</li>\r\n	<li>Successfully fulfill the necessary English language conditions; and</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain at least 60 test points.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The aspirants ought to also satisfy the required character &amp; health prerequisites, have the ability to carry the bare minimum settlement funds, and be ready to stay and do a job in the sponsoring Australian state/territory.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Subclass 190 Point Test Calculator/Australia Point System:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe 190 visa points calculator&nbsp;is the system designed to assess the immigration score needed to acquire the PR in Australia. The deciding score of the Australian PR is 65 points or higher which will enable the candidate to attain the Australian Permanent Residency. The points under the Australia PR Points&nbsp;system are based on the parameters of Age, English Language Proficiency, Educational Qualification, Work Experience etc.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Subclass 190 Visa Processing Time:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe processing time of Australia Subclass 190 may vary. however, for 75% of applications the processing time is 7 months and for 90% of the application, it is 9 months. The applicants should submit all their documents on time in order to avoid deferment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>How to Apply for Subclass 190 Visa Australia:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nApplying for the Subclass 190 Visa may seem stringent at beginning but once you understand the procedure, it becomes relatively easy to process the application. Like all the immigration pathways, the candidate must fulfill the eligibility requirements and complete the below process.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must partake the skills assessment of the nominated occupation with the suitable government body considering your profile. Your assessment will be reviewed by The Department of Immigration and Border Protection (DIBP) which will further decide whether you are capable of undertaking your chosen occupation in Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>Upon receiving favorable skills assessment, you are required to submit the Expression of Interest (EOI) through the Skill select program. Furthermore, to increase your chances you have to apply for state or territory government nomination also.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are short-listed, you will be granted the Invitation to apply (ITA) which will enable you attain the Permanent Residency within 60 days.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Subclass 190 Visa Cost/Fees:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe visa fees for Primary Applicant under the skilled nominated visa subclass 190<strong> </strong>is 3755 AUD.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Why Applications Are Rejected After Being Invited To Apply?</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Common reasons for application rejection include an applicant&#39;s:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>&bull; Was Not Entitled To Get All Of The Points In Their EOI</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>It is the responsibility of the EOI owner to provide substantiation for all claims made in their SkillSelect EOI. The following are common explanations for this denial:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Claim community language credentialed points after your qualifying has ended. Your CCL certificate must be valid on the date that NSW invites you to apply for these points.</li>\r\n	<li>Claiming professional year points without eligibility. To qualify for these points, you must have worked in your nominated (or a closely similar) employment.</li>\r\n	<li>Claiming points for skilled employment prior to the date on which you are deemed proficient in your occupation is ineligible.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>&bull; Does Not Satisfy The Residency Prerequisite</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>You must have resided in either New South Wales (NSW) or an overseas country for a minimum of six months.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>&bull; Extra Points Claimed For Employment</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>If your skills evaluation indicates the date you were declared proficient in your occupation, you cannot receive credit for skilled employment performed prior to this date. This is especially true for ACS and the majority of VETASSESS evaluations.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>If your assessment does not include this date, you cannot receive credit for skilled employment performed prior to completing your qualification.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>To ensure that you are entitled to accept your invitation to NSW, you should confirm that you are eligible to claim all points in your SkillSelect EOI and that you have only claimed approved skilled employment.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>If you have incorrectly claimed points, you are ineligible to accept your NSW invitation, if extended. No exclusions exist for any reason.</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Alternative Migration Pathways</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>For prospective skilled migrants, NSW nomination for the Skilled Nominated visa (subclass 190) is merely one of several visa choices. Home Affairs gives out a variety of visas, such as temporary and permanent employer-nominated visas.</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about skilled nominated visa subclass 190 you can write an email on <strong>info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</strong>&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '249599254_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTAy', 1, '2023-12-27 04:49:16'),
(103, 86, 'Skilled Work Regional Provisional Visa Subclass 491', '<div>\r\n<p><strong><u>491 Skilled Work Regional Visa- Provincial</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the important <strong>A</strong><strong>ustralia Permanent Residency</strong> pathways Skilled Regional visa (subclass 489) has been replaced by the newly launched Subclass 491 Skilled Work Regional (Provisional) Visa. This visa category has been introduced by the Australian Department of Home Affairs, and has commenced from 16 November 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is basically a point tested visa is especially for those skilled workers who wish to live and work in a regional area of Australia. Also, with this visa you are sponsored by an Australian State or Territory Government or an eligible family member residing in a designated regional area of Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With this visa you can stay in Australia for up till a duration of 5 years. Designated area of Australia is any part of the country, except Sydney, Brisbane, Gold Coast, Perth and Melbourne. Similar to Subclass 489 Skilled Regional visa the regions of Newcastle, Wollongong and the NSW Central Coast are regarded as designated regional areas.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>How much points required for 491 Visa?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since subclass 491 is a points-tested visa, once you submit your EOI in SkillSelect you will be granted a indicative points score that will be based on the claims you have made, In case you can obtain 65 points or more you will be granted an Invitation to Apply&nbsp;for this visa type. Even if you are invited to apply your invitation will state the number of points that you will be required to score when your application is evaluated for granting of the said visa.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>491 Visa&nbsp;Benefits</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You will be allowed to stay in any regional or designated area of Australia for a period of 5 years.</li>\r\n	<li>With this visa you can live, work and study in a designated regional area of Australia</li>\r\n	<li>Also, you can travel to and from Australia as many times as you want, till the time the 491 visa is valid.</li>\r\n	<li>You can include eligible members of your family in your visa application.</li>\r\n	<li>The best part about applying via this visa pathway if you fulfill the eligibility requirements, you can even transition to permanent residency in Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>There is priority 491 visa processing time granted to regional visa applications.</li>\r\n	<li>Incentives are granted to newcomer immigrants for staying in these regional or designated areas for a longer term.</li>\r\n	<li>Additional points are granted to 491 visa applicants.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>When will you be invited to apply for 491 visa?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be given preference by the Australian department of Immigration in the following order of hierarchy:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>First priority will be granted to candidates who have a partner who is skilled (in terms of work experience and educational qualifications) or an applicant without a partner.</li>\r\n	<li>Second priority will be given to a prospective candidate who has a partner having proficiency or competency in English language.</li>\r\n	<li>Last and final preference will be given to candidates who has a partner who is neither eligible for proficient English or has skilled partner points.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Can 491 Visa Holders lodge other Visas?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The holders of 491 visa will not be able to able to lodge under certain visas till the time they have held a 491 visa and have fulfilled its conditions for a period of 3 years. This will include skilled permanent residency visas like <strong>Subclass 189</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>Subclass 190</strong>, Business visas (124, 132 and 188) visas, Employer Nominated PR Visa (186) as well as onshore partner visa (820). The need for immigrants to live and work in a regional or a designated area of Australia is driven by the need to assist economic development and increase population density in sparsely occupied regional areas of Australia.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Does 491 Visa lead to Permanent Residency?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As discussed above, the 491 visa is a five-year residency visa, but if you meet all its eligibility requirements you can even apply for permanent residency in Australia via the subclass 191 (Permanent Residence (skilled regional) visa. But prior to taking this step you are required to meet the following eligibility 491 visa requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>As an applicant you should have lived, worked or studied in an Australian regional or designated area for a minimum time of 3 years (under 491 visa subclass).</li>\r\n	<li>In the duration of these three years you must have minimum earnings of $53,900.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>What happens to current 489 visa holders and those who lodge a 489 visa before the change?</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Existing 489 visa holders or those who have lodged for 489 visa before the date of 16<sup>th</sup> November, 2019, will have to continue their permanent residency pathway journey via the visa subclass 887.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '534495554_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTAz', 1, '2023-12-27 05:15:30'),
(104, 129, 'New Subclass 494 Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional Visa', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>Relocate to Australia through the New Subclass 494 Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional Visa!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>On 16<sup>th</sup> November 2019, the Subclass 494 Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional Visa was introduced to replace the Subclass 187 Regional Sponsored Migration Scheme Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Australian government intends to direct more foreign talent towards the country&rsquo;s regional areas, which are facing major workforce shortages in several key occupations. To increase immigrant inflow and retention in these areas, the Department of Home Affairs (DHA) has launched two innovative new visas &ndash; the <strong>Subclass 491 Visa</strong>&nbsp;and the Subclass 494 Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>What is the Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This <strong>Australia Visa</strong>&nbsp;allows employers in regional Australia to sponsor overseas skilled workers who can fulfill local labor market requirements. Through this pathway, foreign nationals &ndash; who are qualified to occupy job vacancies that cannot be filled by the domestic Australian population &ndash; can live, work and study in a designated regional area for up to five years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Can an Australian employer nominate a foreign skilled worker for this visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Subclass 494 Visa has two sub-categories &ndash; the Employer Sponsored stream and the Labor Agreement stream. Under the Employer Sponsor stream, an eligible Australian employer can nominate a foreign worker to work in an occupation that is facing skills shortages in the local labor market &ndash; in a position under the sponsoring business or an associated entity of such business, located in a designated regional area. This occupation is known as the nominated skilled occupation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The employer must be lawfully operating a business in Australia, and be an approved work sponsor or have applied to become a standard business sponsor, in order to submit a nomination application for the foreign worker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>How will the introduction of this visa impact the validity of the Subclass 187 Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since 16<sup>th</sup> November 2019, the Subclass 187 Visa has been closed to new applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>What will happen to Subclass 187 Visa applications that are awaiting a decision from the DHA?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pending RSMS Visa applications submitted prior to 16<sup>th</sup> November 2019 will continue to be processed as per the transitional arrangements. Subsequently, the DHA will declare the visa outcome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>What are the Subclass 494 visa benefits?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Regional visa applications will be processed on a priority basis, resulting in a shorter processing time.</li>\r\n	<li>Immigrants will be offered incentives for long-term settlement in regional areas.</li>\r\n	<li>A broader range of occupations are eligible for this regional visa, compared to non-regional visas.</li>\r\n	<li>Eventually, the visa holder can become eligible to apply for permanent residency Australia.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>What are the Subclass 494 Visa requirements?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to be eligible to apply for this visa, an aspirant must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be under 45 years of age.</li>\r\n	<li>Be nominated by an approved sponsor.</li>\r\n	<li>Have at least competent English language skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Have the necessary skills, work experience and qualifications required for the nominated occupation.</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain a positive skill assessment from the relevant assessing authority.</li>\r\n	<li>Meet the DHA&rsquo;s health and character requirements.</li>\r\n	<li>If applying under the Labor Agreement Stream, be the subject of a labor agreement signed between the nominating employer and the federal government.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>How does the 494 Visa lead to permanent residence?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After three years of living in Australia on a valid Subclass 494 visa, the visa holder can apply for permanent residence through the Permanent Residence (Skilled Regional) Visa (Subclass 191), if eligible. The Subclass 191 Visa allows successful applicants to permanently live, work and study anywhere in Australia, enroll for the public healthcare scheme, sponsor eligible relatives for permanent residence, and eventually apply for citizenship by fulfilling basic requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the introduction of the Subclass 494 Skilled Employer Sponsored Regional Visa, the DHA is on track to achieve its goal of admitting 25,000 new immigrants to regional Australia in 2019-20. This visa will provide an extremely lucrative opportunity for foreign nationals to economically establish themselves in Australia&rsquo;s charming and well-developed regional areas.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '338820565_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTA0', 1, '2023-12-27 05:18:06'),
(105, 130, 'Australia Skilled Nominated (Subclass 190) Visa Points System', '<div>\r\n<p>This is a permanent residence permit. It enables the visa holders to reside inside the territorial limits of Australia for an unlimited period of time. Skilled - Nominated (Subclass 190) Visa, the visa in question, also enables the involved persons to travel to, and gain entry into the country, for countless times, for a period of 5 years, from the time the said permit is offered to them.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe end of the validity of the permit in question does not at all, in any manner, impact the permanent residency status of the candidates provided they happen to be inside the territorial jurisdictions of Australia. But, those applicants who could be keen to carry on entering and leaving the nation making use of their prized permanent resident status in the wake of expiry of the initial permit are directed to get a <strong>Resident Return Visa </strong>(RRV). The eligibility, or otherwise, of the aspirants, for this visa, will depend on the actual time period for which they may have resided inside the country.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe applicants should garner not less than 60 points, which is the pass marks, to be qualified to file an application for this visa.To be able to apply for this visa you need to have your occupation on their updated list of occupations based upon which they shall nominate you for permanent residency in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A contender can secure points based on getting points in these strictures and become eligible for Skilled Immigration via the Australia Skilled Nominated (Subclass 190) Visa Points System.&nbsp; This system was introduced with the aim to select skilled migrants who would add the best in connection to economic progress and advancement in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Australia Skilled - Nominated (subclass 190) Visa Points Factors</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here below is given the sub-heads under which points can be garnered and are even factors based on which you can be awarded points in a maximum or minimum way depending upon your profile.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Age</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The candidates may get a maximum of 30 points on the basis of their age. The age count begins from the day they were duly sent invites to submit their petitions.. You need to be of a specific age in order to qualify for the Skilled 190 visa. As an applicant you need to below 45 years of age to be able to apply for this category. The lesser your age the more points you can garner on the Australia points system increasing your chances to be nominated by a specific state territory agency of Australia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>English Language Skills</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The applicants may get as many as 20 points on the basis of their English language skills. Those keen to get points for expert or higher ability, would do well to conclude a test for English language even as the same is normally the test for the <strong>International English Language Testing System (IELTS)</strong>.For the applicant to be eligible there needs to be a submission of your International English Language Testing System (IELTS) score. Getting 7 or above in each bank of Speaking, writing, Listening and reading helps an increase in the points when it comes to Subclass 190 as points test is an important requirement besides skills assessment and having your occupation on the skilled updated list.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Trained Employment</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As many as 20 points are up for grabs for enjoying a grouping of out-of-the-country and Australian skilled employment during the course of the past decade at the time the applicants are suitably invited to file their visa petitions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn order to pocket these points, the aspirants would do well to have been employed for not less than 20 hours of fully paid work every week in their designated skilled vocation, or a closely associated vocation even as the job should have been done inside and/or outside the territorial jurisdictions of the Down Under.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Educational Skills</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As many as 20 points are up for grabs under this category. This is based on the candidates&rsquo; educational qualifications at the time they were sent invites to duly apply.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt needs to be mentioned here that test points may be suitably given for just one of the recognized qualifications of the aspirants. For instance, in case they have concluded a Bachelor Degree, and a Doctorate Degree, they may get test points for the latter only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith a view to getting test points for a Masters Degree, the applicants should also possess a Bachelor Degree, or else the former should be regarded as at least at par with Bachelor level at the national levels.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe assessing authority which runs the skills evaluation has the power to decide if any skills pocketed outside the geographical limits of Australia are of a level which is at par with the applicable national level.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>National Study Prerequisites</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As many as 5 points are up for grabs under this category provided the aspirants fulfill the study prerequisites of the nation. It means the aspirants have been offered with one or extra Degrees, diplomas or trade credentials, via a subject or subjects pursued at an educational organization of Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Credentialed Society Language</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The applicants may get 5 test points for this when they are duly sent invites to submit their visa petitions. If an applicant holds National Accreditation Authority for Translators and Interpreters (NAATI) Certification or a letter showcasing the fact that they are accredited by NAATI, at the paraprofessional level or more for interpretation as well as&nbsp; translation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The NAATI certification not only evaluates whether the applicant is knowledgeable to take the designation of an interpreter or translator, but also get an extra 5 points under the Credentialed community language credentials, which as a result improves their points tally on the Australia points system which can be of a huge advantage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about <strong>immigrating to Australia</strong> you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '990349747_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTA1', 1, '2023-12-27 05:23:27'),
(106, 131, 'Australia Skilled Nominated Subclass 190 Visa: Basic Requirements', '<div>\r\n<p>The Australian <strong>Skilled Nominated Subclass 190 Visa</strong> substitutes both the offshore Skilled - Sponsored Subclass 176 permit and the onshore Subclass 886 permit. Australia&nbsp;Skilled Nominated Subclass 190 visa is a permanent permit even as it necessitates nomination by a territory or state government of Australia. It&rsquo;s a points-based visa and the holders may state and do a job on a permanent basis anywhere across Down Under. Some members of the applicant&rsquo;s family may be included in the visa-petition.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith a view to filing a valid petition for this permit the applicants require, to begin with, presenting an <strong>Expression of Interest (EOI)</strong>, via SkillSelect. It&rsquo;s an online facility which makes it possible for the qualified workers keen to shift base to the Kangaroo Land to get their details duly registered to be given consideration for a trained permit, via an EOI.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe interested candidates may be found and offered with nomination for skilled permits by the Australian firms/ recruiters or territory or state administrations, or they may be sent invites by <strong>Immigration Australia</strong> to submit a visa petition. The good thing is that the applicants can do this from both inside or outside the territorial jurisdictions of the nation. The aspirants who get nomination from an Australian territory or state and who fulfill the primary requirements for the said permit will afterwards get an EOI.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Primary Prerequisites</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Some primary requirements need to be catered to successfully file a petition for this permit. The aspirants should:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have an invite to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Be below 50 years at the time of receiving an invite.</li>\r\n	<li>Nominate a vocation which matches their qualifications and expertise and which finds mention on the applicable Skilled Occupation List (SOL). The present SOL (schedule 1) applies to every fresh points-based qualified migration petitions. This includes the candidates entitled for provisional arrangements, provided they desire to utilize the same.</li>\r\n	<li>Have their qualifications suitably evaluated by the pertinent evaluating authority as appropriate for their designated vocation.</li>\r\n	<li>Garner not less than 60 test points.</li>\r\n	<li>Have reasonably good command over the English language.</li>\r\n	<li>Fulfill the prerequisites related to character &amp; physical condition.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about <strong>immigrating to Australia</strong> you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>', '', '525722590_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTA2', 1, '2023-12-27 05:27:58'),
(107, 132, 'How to Apply for Australia Sub Class 190 Visa', '<div>\r\n<p>Those who get an invites to file a petition for Skilled Nominated Subclass 190 Visa, will have two months or 60 days at their disposals for submitting their online petitions. Their petition letter will thoroughly give details on the procedure of the lodgment that they must go after. The visa-candidates could be inside or outside the territorial jurisdictions of Australia when they file their petitions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nInvites are based on the claims made in their Expression of Interests (EOIs) at the time the aspirants are sent invites to submit their applications. The petition should mirror the particulars given in their EOIs, and must also be duly beefed-up by applicable proof. In a situation wherein post getting 2 invites to submit petitions for permits the applicants fail to file visa petitions, their EOIs will be taken out from SkillSelect.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>File the petition</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The applicants must submit their petitions online, via SkillSelect. They must pay the original application fee, via credit card at the said time even as a second fee which covers just those dependants who happen to be 18 years or above and the names of whom are mentioned on the petition of the aspirants and who are not very good at English language having less than practical skills in this is to be paid, prior to a permit may be offered.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs a part of the filing of the petitions of the aspirants, the candidates must suitably corroborate that they fully concur with the Australian Values Statement and that they also have gone through, or had duly paraphrased to them the book titled &lsquo;the Life in Australia&rsquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Furnish applicable papers</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It is crucial to proffer the papers which demonstrate the claims made in the EOI even as these are suitably identified and paraphrased in what is called the Document Checklist. The said checklist also offers details on extra requirements, and if there are any requirements of furnishing the original papers or duly certified photocopies.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAny deed or paper in a language other than English should duly go with a translation in English carried out by a recognized translator. All supporting papers/deeds must be thoroughly scanned and uploaded with the petition of the applicant. In case of any requirements of additional details and/or certification, the aspirants will be duly informed by the Department of Immigration and Citizenship Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Include family members</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The visa aspirants may include these kinds of family members in their petitions: spouses, actual partners, same-sex mates; dependent children; other dependent members of the family, such as parents, who live with the candidates and who are reliant, money-wise.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAlthough it is within reach to include mates and dependent children, post the filing of the petition, it is advisable to include the names of other dependent members of the family right at the time of the filing of the petition for the Skilled Nominated Subclass 190 Visa.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEven if you seek&nbsp;more information about Australia skilled nominated subclass 190 visa, you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '562966798_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTA3', 1, '2023-12-27 05:30:46'),
(108, 133, 'Employer Nomination Scheme Subclass 186 Visa', '<div>\r\n<p>A rather important component of the permanent Employer Sponsored visa scheme of Australia, <strong>Employer Nomination Scheme</strong> or the ENS (Subcategory 186) for Australia is fundamentally meant for those trained employees based in a foreign country, or those qualified temporary residents, who could, at the time of applying, be staying and professionally involved with a job, since a specified time, in Down Under.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe ENS Visa is one of the employer sponsored visa subcategories. It means the aspirants have to discover an organization, eager to put in the significant effort, time, &amp; money to them (the candidates) over to the shores of Down Under. The applicants may apply for the permit only post they have been proffered nomination from an Australia based recruiter/company.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Australia Employer Nomination Scheme (Subclass 186) Categories</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The well-liked and widely accepted ENS has three different streams out of which, as per some experts, the third one, i.e., the Direct Entry Class is the most appealing since the same provides the applicants the prized and the much sought after Permanent Residency (PR) right away.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Temporary Residence Transition Stream</strong>: This category is basically for those subclass 457 visa holders who have been professionally engaged in Oz for two years even as their recruiters want to engage them on a permanent basis.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Direct Entry Stream</strong>: This category is basically for those people who have, by no means, or just for a short period of time, been associated with Australia&rsquo;s labor market even as they have the support of a firm/recruiter based in the country who is prepared to offer nomination to them.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Agreement Stream</strong>: This category is for those candidates who are armed with sponsorship from a company, through a labor or regional migration agreement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Australia Employer Nomination Scheme (Subclass 186): Major Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Among others, the aspirants:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Should have nomination from a duly approved job-provider from the country;</li>\r\n	<li>Ought to less than 50 years of age;</li>\r\n	<li>Ought to successfully satisfy the requirements involving proficiency, qualifications, &amp; the English language; and</li>\r\n	<li>Should file a petition through the category for which they were duly nominated.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nIt requires to be duly mentioned here that some freedoms related to age, capability, and language skills are given to some candidates. Still, these mainly depend on the selected line-of-work, wages, besides the applicants &lsquo;previous employment experience. Those who lack a manager to offer nomination may present an EOI through Skill Select. The concerned recruiters/firms and territory and state administrations will later on check their particulars before they take a decision on extending nomination for skilled migration purposes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Important</strong>: Those who owe the nation&rsquo;s regime some money will not have the authority to claim a permit until and unless they appropriately settle the amount overdue.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEven if you seek&nbsp;more information about Australia Employer Nomination Scheme Subclass 186 Visa, you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '126267262_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTA4', 1, '2023-12-27 05:33:01');
INSERT INTO `cms` (`id`, `menu_id`, `title`, `description`, `video`, `image`, `url`, `status`, `created_at`) VALUES
(109, 87, 'Australia Business Visa Process, Requirements and Eligibility', '<div>\r\n<p>Australia is one of the most beautiful and wealthiest countries, backed by a robust economic and social structure. It&#39;s a developed and multicultural nation with plenty of opportunities for skilled workers and business investors seeking a high quality of life, financial freedom, world-class education for their children, and significant civil liberties and political rights protection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australian Business Visa is an ideal option for anyone looking to establish or buy an existing business in Australia. There are different Australian business visas for eligible applicants depending on their investment needs and the purpose of immigration. The Australia business visa is a perfect pathway to conduct business activities in Australia and live an accomplished life in Down Under.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Australia Business Visa Process and Requirements:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Following are some of the most famous investor visa Australia categories for prospective foreign entrepreneurs planning to expand their Australian business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) visa (subclass 188)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) visa (subclass 188) has five streams available. Out of five, four streams require applicants to be nominated by the state or territory government. They are described below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Business Innovation Stream (Subclass 188) -&nbsp;</strong>It&#39;s a provisional visa for candidates with commendable business skills looking to establish a new business or buy an existing business in Australia. A state or a territory government must nominate you to have this visa.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) Visa (Subclass 188) Investor Stream-&nbsp;</strong>A provisional visa for high net worth individuals capable of making a designated investment of at least AUD 1.5 million in any Australian state and conduct business activities in Australia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Significant Investor Stream- </strong>Designed for people willing to invest at least AUD 5 million into complying with substantial investments in Australia and maintaining the business in the country. &nbsp;The applicant must be nominated by an Australian State or Territory government agency or Austrade for an Australia PR visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entrepreneur Stream- </strong>For business individuals who have secured a minimum of AUD 200000 from a designated funding body to facilitate Australia&#39;s investment activities. You must be nominated by a state or territory government.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Business Talent (Permanent) visa (subclass 132)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Significant Business History Stream-&nbsp;</strong>for high-caliber business owners who want to do business in Australia. The visa category requires you to get a nomination from a state or territory government.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Venture Capital Entrepreneur Stream-&nbsp;</strong>A permanent visa stream for individuals who have secured venture capital funding from one of the designated members of AVCAL to start their business in Australia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Australia Business Visa Eligibility Criteria:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for a business visa Australia, you must be:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Below 55 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>You must score at least 65 on the Department of Home Affairs&#39; points test in SkillSelect.</li>\r\n	<li>You must have a Vocational level of English (or equivalent).</li>\r\n	<li>Have a minimum of three years&#39; experience in managing the eligible business or the qualified investment</li>\r\n	<li>Able to present a successful track-record of qualifying business activity or management of an eligible investment.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Genuinely interested in owning and maintaining a typical management role in the business located in Australia.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to apply for an Australia business visa from India?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>All eligible applicants must apply for a state nomination before making any formal application for the business visa. Applying for a state nomination is a three-step process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: </strong>Lodge an Expression of Interest to the Department of Home Affairs Australia through SkillSelect and select your preferred Australian state for the nomination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2: </strong>Submit an official application for the state or territory nomination. You must register as a user first and then complete the application process. You will need to submit the following documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) visa (subclass 188) Business Innovation stream Nomination Conditions form</li>\r\n	<li>Appointment of an Agent/Representative form (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>If you propose to undertake export or eCommerce activity</li>\r\n	<li>Evidence of your relevant academic qualification/s</li>\r\n	<li>Evidence of your business experience</li>\r\n	<li>Evidence of your English language competency</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Lodge a formal visa application if nominated by your chosen state. In this stage, an automatic invitation will be sent to your email ID by SkillSelect, requesting you to submit an official application for the visa. You must respond to the request within 60 days of receiving the nomination.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>How Do I Get A Business Visa For Australia?</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The application process for an Australia business visa can be completed online or offline. Nevertheless, there are a few factors that need to be examined. You must possess a valid passport and any additional documentation required by the embassy. The visa application process is comprised of the following steps:</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Online Procedure:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sign up for IMMI at https://online.immi.gov.au/lusc/login</li>\r\n	<li>Start by filling out the Subclass 600 Australia business visa application form.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that you provide the accurate and necessary information</li>\r\n	<li>Provide a recent photo of yourself that adheres to the given photo requirements.</li>\r\n	<li>Attach the required documents with the form.</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the fees for the visa online.</li>\r\n	<li>Fill out the application online.</li>\r\n	<li>When submitting the application, you will be required to furnish biometrics to the embassy.</li>\r\n	<li>Organize a health test per the embassy&#39;s instructions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Offline Procedure:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Download the application form for a business visa at https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/form-listing/forms/1415.pdf.</li>\r\n	<li>Fill in the required fields on the form.</li>\r\n	<li>Attach the documents, original for some</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the application to the embassy.</li>\r\n	<li>Pay the visa fees at the moment the application is submitted.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide the biometrics</li>\r\n	<li>Organize a health examination if the embassy requests one.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>Whether you are completing the form offline or online, you must ensure that the information you provide is accurate and verifiable. If any fraudulent information is provided and the form is not filled out according to the instructions, your visa may be denied. You should be aware that this visa denial may affect your future visa applications. It may even occur between expedited applications.</div>\r\n\r\n<p>The team at Orange Global Consultancy has extensive knowledge of all aspects of Australia immigration, from skilled to business visas. Orange Global Consultancy Immigration Services can guide you through creating a robust business plan while ensuring a smooth visa process from start to end.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To know more information, you can connect with us on 8336933522 or drop an email at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in. We will provide your evaluation results and chart out the best Australian business immigration pathway for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', '', '995075226_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTA5', 1, '2023-12-27 05:39:27'),
(110, 88, 'BUSINESS INNOVATION AND INVESTMENT (PERMANENT) VISA- SUBCLASS 888', '<p>The Business Innovation and Investment (Permanent) subclass 888 is a state-nominated permanent residency visa designed for foreign entrepreneurs and investors who wish to carry out business activities in Australia. Subclass 888 is the second stage of the Business Innovation and Investment subclass 188 visa, which is a 5-year temporary visa for people who want to own and manage a new or existing business in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once a business is successfully established in Australia, the holder of a subclass 188 visa can apply for a permanent residency visa through the Business Innovation and Investment (Permanent) subclass 888.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The subclass 888 visa has two streams:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Business Innovation Stream, and</li>\r\n	<li>The Investor Stream</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who can apply for this visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>To be eligible for the subclass 888 visa, you must be a holder of one of the following visas:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A Subclass 188 visa,</li>\r\n	<li>A special category Subclass 444 visa, or</li>\r\n	<li>A business long-stay Subclass 457 visa (in limited circumstances).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The following types of individuals are eligible for subclass 888 visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Business innovators</li>\r\n	<li>Significant investors</li>\r\n	<li>Premium Investors</li>\r\n	<li>Entrepreneurs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Apart from this, they must:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hold a current Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) visa (subclass 188) or a Special Category visa (subclass 444).</li>\r\n	<li>Have fulfilled the eligibility requirements of your provisional visa</li>\r\n	<li>Have been nominated by a state or territory government.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Investor Stream-888 visa</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must produce evidence of a designated investment of at least AUD$ 1.5 million for 4 years.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide a performance report of your business or a summary of activities undertaken in Australia in the last two years. The report must also include your plans regarding the business.</li>\r\n	<li>You must have resided in Australia as a subclass 188 holder under the Investor Stream for 2 years in the 4 years before lodging your 888 visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Business Innovation and Investment (Permanent) subclass 888- Processing Time</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The exact time taken to process an application under the subclass 888 visa depends on the stream you&rsquo;ve applied for and how well you meet the eligibility requirements. The business innovation stream applicants may expect their application to process in 10-11 months. Whereas, applications under the significant investment stream tend to take 7-9 months. Please keep checking the Department of Home Affairs website for any changes in the processing times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nEven if you seek&nbsp;more information about Business investment&nbsp;to Australia, you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '173827362_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTEw', 1, '2023-12-27 05:46:06'),
(111, 89, 'Australia Business Talent Permanent -Subclass 132 Visa', '<div>\r\n<p>Australia Business Talent Subcategory 132&nbsp;Permit is a Permanent Residence&nbsp;Visa; it&rsquo;s basically not an investment&nbsp;visa. It is a specialist permit tailored for high net worth people, below the age of 55, with an excellent commercial background. It is vital that the candidates aim to settle in a particular Australian state or territory and set-up a business, which gives &lsquo;exceptional&rsquo; economic advantage to the state/territory. The visa can be gained only in case you get an invite even as it&rsquo;s an important component of the well-known Australian Business Innovation and Investment Scheme.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPrior to gaining an invite to submit a submission, it is expected of the applicants to present an Expression of Interest (EOI), through the online visa and immigration facility, Skill Select. It is vital that the EOI clearly states if the candidates are motivated with either of the two Australia Business Talent Permanent Subcategory 132 Visa categories, namely, the Venture Capital Entrepreneur Stream, and the Significant Business History stream. It is also essential that the candidates indicate if they are motivated with only one or every territory &amp; state of Down Under. Significantly, the candidates do not have to furnish any supporting certificates/papers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Australia Business Talent Permanent Subclass 132 Visa Streams</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As mentioned just a short will ago, the permit category has two sub categories the Significant Business History Stream, and the Venture Capital Entrepreneur Stream. The first one is meant for the prosperous owners or part owners of a firm who are eager to get hold of a key management role in a completely new or existing business enterprise in Oz. The number two is meant for those who have received at least AUD1 million in funding from an Australian venture capital group.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As stated previously, submission can be made only if you have gained an invite for the purpose.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>For the Significant Business History Category the Aspirants Ought to:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submit an EOI;</li>\r\n	<li>Have nomination from an Australian territory or state administration;</li>\r\n	<li>Be below 55 years of age;</li>\r\n	<li>Possess business &amp;personal resources worth AUD1.5 million;</li>\r\n	<li>AUD400 000 should be net assets in the business; and</li>\r\n	<li>Possess an overall business turnover of AUD3 million.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nFor the Venture Capital Entrepreneur Category, the aspirants should: have obtained not less than AUD1 million in funding from a venture capital firm of Oz, for business concept with a fairly high value.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Business Talent Visa Subclass 132: Some Major Benefits</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The widely accepted visa allows you to do several things and gain several things. It enables you to set-up a new or build-up an existing group/firm in Down Under. It&rsquo;s a permanent residence visa. It enables you along with family members (those who have the permit) to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Reside in Australia for an indefinite period.</li>\r\n	<li>Do a job and pursue studies in the country.</li>\r\n	<li>Register for Medicare the nation&rsquo;s popular program for health-associated care &amp; expenses.</li>\r\n	<li>File a petition for Australian citizenship (of course, in case you are qualified).</li>\r\n	<li>Offer sponsorship to entitled family members for permanent residence.</li>\r\n	<li>Take a trip to and from the nation for a period of 5 years from the date the permit is offered (post the said time, you will require a Resident Return Visa (RRV) or a new permit to come back to Oz).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Post Petition Submission</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>After you submit your immigration application and documents, you will be contacted by the relevant body which will inform you it has gained the particulars; your will be allocated a case official, a decision will be taken on your petition, you will be asked to appear for an interview (of course if it is necessary), more data will be sought (again if the same is needed) before a decision is taken.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn case you want to present a submission for the&nbsp;Autralia Business Subclass 132 Immigration Permit, please feel free to mail at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in. Do not forget to specify your city and phone contacts along with a brief business profile. It should include business turnover during each of the previous five years. You will soon be contacted by Orange Global Consultancy to take move the assessment and filing procedure for the Subclass 132 Immigration Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', '', '280229664_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTEx', 1, '2023-12-27 05:49:56'),
(112, 90, 'What is Australia Business Innovation and Investment Subclass 188 Visa', '<p>If there is an innovative idea which is investible and unique as well then the business innovation visa Australia 188 is definitely a table topper. With this visa you can own and manage as well as carry out any business investment activities when you plan for your Australia Immigration.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Business Innovation stream</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Business Innovation stream that helps you eventually secure an Australia PR visa as this is a provisional visa which allows you to stay for up to 5 years, wherein you need to new or existing business in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can apply for permanent Business Innovation and Investment (Permanent) visa (subclass 888) in the Business Innovation stream to how to immigrate to Australia as a permanent resident. For this visa, you should be nominated by an Australian State or Territory government agency to know how to immigrate to Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Business Investment stream</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The business investment visa Australia is the type of visa which requires a minimum investment in Australian investments which meet some of the important requirements and as an applicant of this investment visa Australia maintain their business or even investment activity in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other streams for this visa are Significant Investor stream, Business Innovation Extension stream, Significant Investor Extension stream, Premium Investor stream as well as Entrepreneur stream among some of the streams of this visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Top Benefits of 188 visa Australia</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You can temporarily stay with a possibility to apply for the permanent visa.</li>\r\n	<li>Can as an applicant bring along your family members.</li>\r\n	<li>You can extend your stay for 4 years or more with this 188 visa Australia</li>\r\n	<li>Also, you can do a job as well as pursue other courses in Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>As an applicant you can sponsor other qualified members of family for permanent residence.</li>\r\n	<li>You can travel to and from Australia in the time span of 5 years or as long as the visa is valid</li>\r\n	<li>Enrolment in Medicare and save colossal health costs as well as gain access to the all-inclusive Medicare health coverage with affordable health cover.</li>\r\n	<li>Help via Higher Educations Loans Programs (HELP) once you get permanent residence</li>\r\n	<li>You can with this kind of provisional visa even live, work and study in a designated regional area of Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>After 3 years you shall even be eligible to apply for permanent residence from the time of granting of your visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>188 visa Australia requirements for eligibility</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To apply for this visa you shall be required to submit an Expression of Interest in SkillSelect</li>\r\n	<li>Also, the applicant should be Nominated by a State or Territory government agency or Austrade &nbsp;and should not withdraw the nomination or else your visa shall not be granted.</li>\r\n	<li>Ultimately you should be invited to apply for this visa.</li>\r\n	<li>For 2 out of 4 fiscal years just prior to you getting an ITA you must have an ownership stake in 1 or 2 businesses which has either has a AUD500, 000 turnover in each of those 2 years if you were invited to apply before 1 July 2021 or a turnover of AUD750, 000 in each of those 2 years if you were invited to apply on or after 1 July 2021.</li>\r\n	<li>Even if you have either 1 or 2 businesses you should be owning a minimum of 51%, of the total worth of the business if the business accrues a turnover of less than AUD400, 000 per year, 30%, of the total cost of the business if the business has a revenue of AUD400, 000 or more per year, or 10%, of the total worth of the business if the business is functioned by a publicly listed company.</li>\r\n	<li>Once invited for the visa, you, your partner or both of you together should have a total minimum net business and personal assets of a minimum of a minimum of a AUD1.25 million if you receive the invitation on or after 1 July 2021 or AUD800,000 if you got the invitation to apply prior to 1 July 2021. These funds should be made available to move to Australia within 2 years of us issuance of this visa.</li>\r\n	<li>Score a minimum of 65 based on the factors of age, English language expertise, credentials, business experience, net personal and business assets, business turnover, innovation as well as special endorsement</li>\r\n	<li>Have a business career which has been fruitful as well as a genuine intention to consistently own and manage in Australian business for you to know how to immigrate to Australia through this route.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that you are under 55 years of age if you want to get an invitation to apply for this visa. In case you are older which is above 55 you can be invited by State or Territory if you have a business which brings about an exceptional economic advantage.</li>\r\n	<li>You should as a business investment visa Australia applicant be involved in suspicious or illegal business or investment activities considered unacceptable by Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant for this kind of visa should have functional English and if you don&rsquo;t then you shall be asked to make a payment of the second instalment of the visa application charge. The Department accepts test scores from approved providers like Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL iBT), IELTS, One Skill Retake (OSR)*, PTE, Cambridge English (CAE) called as&nbsp; C1 Advanced, and Occupational English Test (OET) which is mainly for health professionals.</li>\r\n	<li>Meet health and character requirements. Can be asked for family members as well who are coming or not coming as well.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that you sign the Australian values statement if you or your family members who have applied are above 18 years during the time of submission of application confirming that you shall respect the Australian manner of life and obey their laws and have read or explained to you the Life in Australia tool.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that you or your family members have no money owed to the Australian government or show it has been paid back</li>\r\n	<li>See to that your any previous visa has been cancelled or denied while you were in Australia and check if this cancellation affects your eligibility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>What is the step by step procedure to get an Australian business visa?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1-</strong> The first step is to submit an Expression of Interest and be nominated by State or Territory, for you to be invited to apply for Australia immigration through this subclass 188 visa Australia route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong> - Assimilate all the necessary documents as well as those of your proposed investment. Also documents related to your family members need to be applied.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong> - You can apply for the visa via online by creating an ImmiAccount for which firstly you need to be invited to apply. For all the documents which are uploaded from 13 November 2021, candidates must upload supporting documentation to ImmiAccount when submitting a subclass 188 Business Innovation and Investment visa application in all streams. Uploading ensures that the processing is effectual and aids in reducing the processing time on these applications. While uploading these supporting documents make sure that you use naming conventions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong> - The Home Affairs of Australia will let you know once they have received your application along with the documents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong> - The visa outcome shall be known to you in written. If the visa is granted we shall inform you about your visa grant number, the starting date of your visa and conditions of your visa. Keep a copy of all this while you are in Australia.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If visa is refused the reason for refusal shall be mentioned and whether or not you have the right to access the decision.&nbsp; No application charge shall be refunded on refusal of the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Processing time and fees for 188 visa Australia</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For business innovation visa Australia the processing time for 25% of applications is 15 Months, 50% of applications is 18 Months, 75% of applications is 33 Months and 90% of applications is 36 Months. On the other hand when it comes to investment visa Australia the processing time of 25% of applications takes 22 Months, for 50% of applications it is 38 Months, for 75% of applications it is 41 Months and for 90% of applications it is 42 Months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fees for business innovation visa Australia and also business investment visa Australia starts from AUD6, 270. There is fee for every family member who applies for this provisional Australia PR visa pathway. For family members over 18 years the fee is AUD3, 135, and below 18 years the fee is AUD1, 565. The second instalment charges for the primary applicant is AUD9, 795 and for family member it is AUD4, 890.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case you are keen to present a submission for the Sub-class 188 Immigration Permit, please feel free send across a mail to info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522. It should comprise your business turnover in every of the previous 5 years. A higher-ranking executive will contact you to take forward the appraisal and filing course of action for the <strong>Australia Business Innovation and Investment (Provisional) (subcategory 188) Visa</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '835866791_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTEy', 1, '2023-12-27 05:56:43'),
(113, 91, 'Australia\'s New Skilled Occupation List', '<div>\r\n<p>The Skilled Occupation List Australia is a list of occupation which highlights the most in-demand occupations across various states and regions of Australia. Used as a part of points-based system for <a href=\"https://www.abhinav.com/australia-immigration.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Australia immigration</a>, skilled workers who want to live and work in Australia are required to choose or nominate an occupation that must align with the skills and experience of the candidate from the Consolidated Sponsored Occupation List (CSOL).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Skilled Occupation List- What&rsquo;s in It</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anyone who is applying for Australia PR visa under General Skilled Migration, and they are not nominated by any of the Australian state or territory, then they must choose an occupation from the SOL List Australia. Every year, the Australian Department of Home Affairs updates its skilled occupation list as per the latest labor market demands of the country. The purpose to update the list is to ensure that the entry of skilled immigrants is purely based on Australia&rsquo;s current workforce needs and economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Skilled Occupations List (SOL) is generally applicable for Skilled Independent Subclass 189 Visa, Skilled Work Regional Provisional Visa Subclass 491, Skilled Nominated Subclass 190 Visa, and Subclass 485 (Graduate Temporary Visa) visa applications.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>If you already have a skilled visa, you will not be affected by the removal of these jobs until your circumstances change and you need to submit a new nomination application. In that event, you may be affected. If you are changing your occupation or employer and your occupation is no longer on the combined list of qualifying skilled occupations, this consequence may occur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information, feel free to get in touch with us at 8336933522&nbsp;or mail us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '692678600_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTEz', 1, '2023-12-27 06:07:23'),
(114, 92, 'Australia\'s New Skilled Occupation List', '<div>\r\n<p>The Skilled Occupation List Australia is a list of occupation which highlights the most in-demand occupations across various states and regions of Australia. Used as a part of points-based system for Australia immigration, skilled workers who want to live and work in Australia are required to choose or nominate an occupation that must align with the skills and experience of the candidate from the Consolidated Sponsored Occupation List (CSOL).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Skilled Occupation List- What&rsquo;s in It</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anyone who is applying for Australia PR visa under General Skilled Migration, and they are not nominated by any of the Australian state or territory, then they must choose an occupation from the SOL List Australia. Every year, the Australian Department of Home Affairs updates its skilled occupation list as per the latest labor market demands of the country. The purpose to update the list is to ensure that the entry of skilled immigrants is purely based on Australia&rsquo;s current workforce needs and economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Skilled Occupations List (SOL) is generally applicable for Skilled Independent Subclass 189 Visa, Skilled Work Regional Provisional Visa Subclass 491, Skilled Nominated Subclass 190 Visa, and Subclass 485 (Graduate Temporary Visa) visa applications.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Farmers</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Due to the pandemic, Australia faces a severe shortage in the farming and irrigation. Mostly, consists of labors from overseas as the Australian residents are fewer in this industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Agriculture Technicians &amp; Workers</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Agriculture industry is one of the booming industries in Australia. Therefore, more technical professionals are needed in this industry. December 1, 2021 will mark the resumption of international workers travel to the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Marketing Professionals</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every business needs a dedicated marketing team to generate business. And, marketing professionals are demanded in the country. Digital Marketing is now becoming useful medium for the businesses to promote their products and offerings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Marketing Professionals</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every business needs a dedicated marketing team to generate business. And, marketing professionals are demanded in the country. Digital Marketing is now becoming useful medium for the businesses to promote their products and offerings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sports Professionals</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the recent occupations addition, Australia has added sports professionals (riders and turf managers). It is a unique occupations which has less competition with maximum opportunities for the professionals who are associated with sports and management.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Short-term Skilled Occupation List (STSOL) Contains 253 Occupations</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Short-term Skilled Occupation List (STSOL) is reviewed every six months and contains a list of skilled occupations determined by the Department of Employment (DoE) and the Department of Home Affairs (formerly DIBP).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you already have a skilled visa, you will not be affected by the removal of these jobs until your circumstances change and you need to submit a new nomination application. In that event, you may be affected. If you are changing your occupation or employer and your occupation is no longer on the combined list of qualifying skilled occupations, this consequence may occur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information, feel free to get in touch with us at 8336933522&nbsp;or mail us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '175970867_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTE0', 1, '2023-12-28 03:59:39'),
(115, 93, 'Australian Capital Territory (ACT) Occupation List 2023', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>An Overview Australian Capital Territory Occupation List</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Australia Capital Territory (ACT) Skilled Occupation List&nbsp;encompasses the occupations that have demand in Canberra to suffice the labour market needs. The occupation list predominantly grants the opportunity for the subclass 190 and subclass 489 candidates who want to apply for ACT state nomination. Eligibility for ACT can be checked for both skilled visas and employer nomination scheme. Australia Capital Territory (ACT) nomination gives the provision for the skilled workforce and business professionals to migrate to Canberra. Below are the pathways for the state nomination:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Skilled Visas</strong> &ndash; Consisting of the ACT nomination of a skilled nominated subclass 190 visa which is a permanent visa that allows an individual to live and work in Canberra.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Employer Nomination</strong> &ndash; Prospective Employer take the support of Regional Certifying Body to nominate skilled workers under the Regional Sponsored Migration Scheme.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '', '788059835_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTE1', 1, '2023-12-28 04:02:54'),
(116, 94, 'New South Wales 190 Priority Skilled Occupation List - 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>New South Wales has begun the intake for skilled immigration program for Financial Year 2018-19. The NSW 190 invitation round is expected to receive qualified immigrants with high scores in the occupations summarized on NSW 190 occupation list 2018. In order to gain more highly&nbsp; skilled immigrants under subclass 190, the state is open throughout the year for selection of candidates under the New South Wales Nomination Program (190).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCandidates whose profile is in high demand in NSW, can match up with the skills required in NSW as shown in the New South Wales Occupation List (190), would receive the invite from the state for nomination under the subclass 190 (skilled nominated visa).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNew South Wales has a selection-based invitation process, where the state elects and invites suitable immigrants from Skill Select to apply for state nominations under the NSW Occupation List - 190 to ensure right allocation of resources is done according to the need of the state economy.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', '', '904576948_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTE2', 1, '2023-12-28 04:13:22');
