(123, 72, 'Australia Family, Partner and Spouse Visas - Sponsored Visa', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>Reunite with Your Loved Ones with Australia Family Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia is a country which has always encouraged family migration to Australia and integration of multiple ethnicities to improve nation&rsquo;s economic and social fabric. It&rsquo;s a way to provide families opportunities to establish their roots in the country and prosper together. Keeping this in mind, the Department of Home Affairs in Australia offers a range of family visas to help Australian citizens and permanent residents to bring their dependent family members, parents, partners, and children in Australia on a temporarily or permanent basis. These visas are specifically sponsored by the Australian citizens or permanent residents, and eligible New Zealand citizens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Various Family Visa Categories</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following are the different categories of family visas that the sponsoring person may choose from to bring their family members/dependents to Australia:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Partner visa</li>\r\n	<li>Prospective marriage visa</li>\r\n	<li>Parent visa</li>\r\n	<li>Child</li>\r\n	<li>Other family visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nLet&rsquo;s discuss all categories of Family visa Australia in detail:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Partner Visa-</strong> <strong>Temporary and Permanent Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also known as Subclass 801, the Partner Visa for Australia allows the spouse or de facto partner of an Australian citizen or permanent resident to migrate to Australia. The visa is applicable for married partners, same sex partners, and or a fianc&eacute;e/fianc&eacute; of an Australian citizen, or an eligible New Zealand citizen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your application for Partner Visa to Australia must be lodged or sponsored by your partner already living in Australia for a period of two years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Basic Requirements for Partner Visa Australia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are eligible to apply for the partner visa Australia if you meet the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Both partners must be 18 years of age or above;</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant must be spouse/fianc&eacute;/ de facto partner of the person residing in Australia.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Your spouse must be able to sponsor you for at least two years.</li>\r\n	<li>For married couples, it is important to prove your relationship for more than 12 months as well as legit under the Australian Law.</li>\r\n	<li>For de facto partners, they must demonstrate the length of your relationship for at least 12 months.</li>\r\n	<li>Must provide sufficient proofs to establish the credibility of your<strong> </strong>relationship.</li>\r\n	<li>Must satisfy health and character requirements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prospective Marriage Visa (Subclass 300)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The prospective marriage visa for Australia is created for people who want to get married to an Australia permanent resident&nbsp;or citizen or an eligible New Zealand citizen. The visa is valid for 9 months only, during which you must marry your prospective partner. The holder of Subclass 300 is eligible to apply for a full-time job or study in this 9-month period at your own expense. Once you are married, you may then go ahead to apply for a partner visa which will ultimately lead to your Australia permanent resident status.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility Criteria for Prospective Marriage Visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for a Prospective Marriage Visa, you must satisfy the below-mentioned criteria:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Both partners must be 18 years or above</li>\r\n	<li>You must be engaged to an Australian permanent resident, or a citizen, or an eligible citizen of New Zealand.</li>\r\n	<li>Your visa application must be sponsored by your prospective spouse/partner.</li>\r\n	<li>You must be intended to marry each other within 9-months&rsquo; period</li>\r\n	<li>Meet necessary health and character requirements</li>\r\n	<li>Must clear all your debts to the Australia government, in case you have any. &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salient Features of Prospective Marriage Visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The intended marriage must be recognized or legal under Australian law</li>\r\n	<li>You must have met your partner in person during the course of your relationship</li>\r\n	<li>You must not be married to anyone else while lodging the application</li>\r\n	<li>You are genuine in your intentions to live together as husband and wife</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parent Visa (Subclass 103)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a permanent resident visa that permits the eligible parents of Australian citizens or permanent residents to reunite with their children in Australia. Under Australia parent visa, you&rsquo;ll be sponsored by your child settled in the country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The parent visa for Australia can be further divided into three categories:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parent Category- </strong>The visa category allows Australian citizens or permanent residents to sponsor their parents or family to join them in Australia either temporary or permanently.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Contributory Parent- </strong>The contributory parent visa comprises a number of visa pathways or migration programs. By applying for this visa, you may stay in Australia as a permanent resident. However, in order to qualify for this visa, you must meet the balance-of-family test, which means half of your children must be living as lawful Australian residents or citizens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, you must submit an Assurance of Support for a permanent visa in the aforementioned category. The same is not mandatory for people applying for the Retirement Pathway.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sponsored Parent</strong>- It&rsquo;s a temporary visa category introduced in March 2019 to help parents or grandparents to join their children in Australia. The visa pathway allows a parent to live in Australia for a period of five years without much limitations, however, the said parent must be outside for at least 90 days before reapplying for this visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Aged Parent Visa-</strong> The visa is granted for older parents who wish to live in Australia with their children, who are already Australian residents or citizens. The prospective parents must be sponsored by their children before applying for this visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Parent Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for Australia Parent visa, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>be sponsored by an eligible child, who is already settled in Australia as resident or citizen.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents who are applying as a retiree do not need any sponsor for this visa</li>\r\n	<li>Meet the balance-of-family test, which means half of your children must be lawfully living in Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>Be able to obtain an assurance of support</li>\r\n	<li>Meet the health and character requirements</li>\r\n	<li>Have cleared all your debts with the government of Australia, in case you have</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia parent visa cost may go up to AUD6,415, and no additional fee will be charged for each family member who applies with you.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Child Visa (Subclass 101)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A child born outside Australia to an Australian citizen or permanent resident, do not become a citizen by default, unlike those getting born in Australia. In such scenario, the parent must apply for a Child Visa that comes under subclass 101.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Child Visa is granted for up to 25 years of age. And, the prospective child must remain outside Australia till the time his/her visa application is under process.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Categories of Child Visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are basically three categories of Child Visa:<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Adoption (Subclass 102)- </strong>This is a permanent resident visa for a child who is born outside Australia, and is below 18 years of age, and has been adopted earlier or in the process of being adopted by an Australian citizen or permanent resident, or an eligible New Zealand citizen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Orphan Relative Visa (Subclass 117/ Subclass 837)- </strong>The Orphan Relative is a visa category that allows an Orphan child overseas (below 18 years) to live with his/her relatives in Australia. To apply for this visa, the parents of the child must be dead, incapacitated or unable to found.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dependent Child Visa (Subclass 445)- </strong>The stream is applicable for children whose parents are the holders of temporary partner visa, and in the process of obtaining the permanent visa in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Basic Requirements of Child Visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible for child visa Australia, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be dependent on sponsored parents who are Australian permanent residents or citizens, or eligible New Zealand citizen.</li>\r\n	<li>The child must be over 18 years of age or under 25 years.</li>\r\n	<li>Be not married to anyone or in a de facto relationship</li>\r\n	<li>Must meet health and character requirements along with parents applying for this visa</li>\r\n	<li>be either a biological/adopted /step-child of the parent who holds temporary partner visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Other Family Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other family visa pathways are created for dependent relatives, caregivers, and other relatives of residents and citizens of Australia and New Zealand. The visa permits the eligible relatives to migrate to Australia permanently, upon meeting the following requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The prospective applicant must be sponsored by a relative who is an Australian citizen, permanent resident or eligible New Zealand citizen</li>\r\n	<li>The applicant must demonstrate sufficient evidence to prove their connection in Australia.</li>\r\n	<li>Must provide an assurance of support.</li>\r\n	<li>Meet health and character requirements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What Is The Application Process?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This visa application can be submitted from outside Australia. If your temporary visa allows you to apply for another visa while you are in Australia, you can also apply in Australia. When the visa is issued, you must be physically located outside of Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salient Features of Other Family Visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The holder of this visa can work and study in Australia without any restrictions.</li>\r\n	<li>Take the benefit of health care facilities along with social security</li>\r\n	<li>May apply for Australian citizenship after a certain period</li>\r\n	<li>Sponsor other people for permanent residence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Contact Orange Global Consultancy Immigration for Quick Process</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our team of dedicated experts assess your profile carefully and suggest relevant options accordingly. Get in touch with us today to know the steps and procedures to follow under Australia family immigration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processing &amp; Services by Orange Global Consultancy Immigration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We at Orange Global Consultancy are committed to offer unbeatable services when it comes to assessing documents for your family visa application. As one of leading immigration consultants in India, we strive to provide a comprehensive range of immigration and advisory services to families, individuals, and investors who wish to move to Australia and kick-start a new life in world&rsquo;s most developed economy.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '449251367_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTIz', 1, '2023-12-28 05:06:35'),
(124, 73, 'Australia Global Talent Visa Program Eligibility Requirements', '<div>\r\n<p>Australian Global Talent Visa program is introduced under the Global Businesses and Talent Attraction Taskforce to attract high-value businesses and highly skilled professionals to Australia. The administration has identified ten future-focused sectors to select the experienced professionals who will drive innovation, transfer skills, and the country&#39;s economy. The selected applicants can work and live permanently with the Australia PR Visa<strong>.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the year 2020-2021, the administration allowed 15,000 applications under the program, which significantly increased from the 5000 applications allocated last year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the Global Talent Independent (GTI) Program?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The purpose of the GTI program is to attract talented migrants at the top of particular critical industries to Australia. It runs on top of an existing visa - the Global Talent (Subclass 858) visa (discussed further below).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The GTI program entails the Department embarking on a more proactive role by employing &quot;Global Talent Officers&quot; (GTO) in important international locations to invite targeted candidates to apply for an Australian visa. GTOs will collaborate with nations in their respective regions and participate in significant events/expos to promote this initiative.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be invited to apply for this visa, those interested in this program must submit an Expression of Interest (EOI) to the Department of Home Affairs (Department). A successful applicant would be provided with a unique identity and invited to apply for a Global Talent visa. Their visa application would be processed expeditiously (around 3 months). In order that:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2019/20 migration program year - 5,000 spots were available;</li>\r\n	<li>During the 2020/21 migration program year, 15,000 spots were allocated;</li>\r\n	<li>During the 2021/22 migration program year, 15,000 spots were offered;</li>\r\n	<li>There will be 5,000 spots during the 2022/23 migration program year (reduced further down from 8,448).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Particularly, the Department intends to target persons with profiles pertinent to the 10 sectors listed in Directive 89.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Department also seeks to target select student cohorts with internationally recognized and industry-relevant research, especially those who have recently (within the last three years) finished their PhD.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the targeted sectors under Australia Global Talent Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applicants can apply for the Global Talent Independent Program (GTIP) if they are within the following fields:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Resources</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Engineering</li>\r\n	<li>Geology</li>\r\n	<li>Metallurgy</li>\r\n	<li>Waste management</li>\r\n	<li>Energy saving technology</li>\r\n	<li>Extraction and processing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Agri-food and AgTech</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seed technology</li>\r\n	<li>Nanomaterials</li>\r\n	<li>Biofuels</li>\r\n	<li>Supply chain and packaging</li>\r\n	<li>Wearable technologies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Energy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Clean energy</li>\r\n	<li>Resource robotics</li>\r\n	<li>Computational metallurgy</li>\r\n	<li>Geostatistics</li>\r\n	<li>Benefication</li>\r\n	<li>Battery/energy storage</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Health Industries</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Medical and biomedical technology</li>\r\n	<li>Pharmaceutical and vaccine research and development</li>\r\n	<li>IT biochemistry</li>\r\n	<li>Digital health</li>\r\n	<li>Implantables and wearable devices</li>\r\n	<li>Genomics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Defence, Advanced Manufacturing and Space</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Astrodynamics</li>\r\n	<li>Satellite systems</li>\r\n	<li>Rocket and avionics systems</li>\r\n	<li>Urban mobility</li>\r\n	<li>Military equipment acquisition and sustainment</li>\r\n	<li>Automation and robotics</li>\r\n	<li>Nano-manufacturing</li>\r\n	<li>Sustainable manufacturing and life-cycle engineering</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Circular Economy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bioenergy</li>\r\n	<li>Sustainable production</li>\r\n	<li>Recycling</li>\r\n	<li>Waste treatment</li>\r\n	<li>Waste to energy technology</li>\r\n	<li>Emissions technology</li>\r\n	<li>Ecologically sustainable manufacturing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DigiTech</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Quantum computing</li>\r\n	<li>Cyber sciences</li>\r\n	<li>Cyber security</li>\r\n	<li>Artificial intelligence</li>\r\n	<li>Blockchain, IoT</li>\r\n	<li>Big data</li>\r\n	<li>Disruptive technology</li>\r\n	<li>Smart cities</li>\r\n	<li>Machine learning</li>\r\n	<li>Network engineering</li>\r\n	<li>Cloud computing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Infrastructure and Tourism</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Travel and tourism infrastructure</li>\r\n	<li>Water infrastructure</li>\r\n	<li>Energy infrastructure</li>\r\n	<li>Regional development</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Financial Services and FinTech</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Neobanking</li>\r\n	<li>Payment systems</li>\r\n	<li>Wealth and regtech</li>\r\n	<li>Blockchain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Education</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cutting edge skills in emerging fields of the industry</li>\r\n	<li>Developing advanced educational systems and curricula</li>\r\n	<li>Improving the education infrastructure in Australia</li>\r\n	<li>Digital data and eResearch platforms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The government believes that skilled workers from these sectors will play a significant role in post-pandemic economic recovery and development. Therefore, the department is also looking for research students relevant to those industries, including Ph.D. students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Global Talent Independent Program Benefits</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Global Talent Independent Program (GTIP) offers the following benefits:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Priority processing signifies that these Global Talent visas have the highest priority of all Australian immigration programs. The process is streamlined and incredibly efficient, with visas granted in as little as one month after application submission.</li>\r\n	<li>This visa is for independent applicants, does not require sponsorship by an employer, and is not based on a points system.</li>\r\n	<li>The visa is given without restrictions or limits for employment.</li>\r\n	<li>A permanent resident is eligible to apply for Australian citizenship.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the eligibility requirements under Australia Global Talent Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Applicants must be from the industries mentioned above with relevant knowledge</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants must prove they are internationally recognized with evidence of outstanding achievements such as senior roles, patents, professional awards, and international publications and memberships.</li>\r\n	<li>Must have the ability to attract an annual salary of minimum of AUD 158,600 (INR 86.9 Lac) according to the Fair Work High Income</li>\r\n	<li>Must be exceptional in their field of expertise and provide evidence that they would be an asset to Australia</li>\r\n	<li>Attain nomination as a global talent from a recognized organization or individual in Australia in the same field as the applicant</li>\r\n	<li>Must have no difficulty in getting employment in Australia or becoming established in their field</li>\r\n	<li>Ph.D. graduates and Ph.D. students can also apply to demonstrate their exceptional talent and international recognition in a target sector.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to apply for Australia Global Talent Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply the following stages that you need to follow:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>First Stage &ndash; Get nominated by an eligible Individual or organization in Australia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>As a part of the application process, candidates must acquire nominations from the individual or an organization with a national reputation.</li>\r\n	<li>The nominating individual or organization will endorse your achievements and skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Second Stage &ndash; Expression of Interest</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submit an expression of interest using Global Talent Contact Form</li>\r\n	<li>If you meet the program requirements, you will receive the unique Invitation reference identifier and Invitation code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Third Stage &ndash; Apply for the Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>After receiving the Invitation reference identifier and Invitation code, apply for visa application in Immiaccount (Official portal)</li>\r\n	<li>Apply for the Global Talent (Subclass 858) Visa for your Australia Permanent Residency Visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The applications under the Australia Global Talent Visa program will get priority processing of 3 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Long Does The Processing Take?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the Department&#39;s stated processing times as of the time of writing, 75% of visa applications for the Global Talent visa under the:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pathway for Distinguished Talent are processed in 18 months; and</li>\r\n	<li>Global Talent route processing times are 65 days (around 2 months).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This is in part because the Global Talent track is a &quot;priority&quot; program and the Distinguished Talent pathway has a limited number of openings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why choose Orange Global Consultancy for Australia Global Talent Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Orange Global Consultancy</strong> is the most trusted and globally renowned Immigration enterprise with more than 28&nbsp;years of dedicated industry experience in processing immigration applications (permanent residency visas, Student Visas, Global Talent Visas, and business visas). We provide comprehensive solutions on Australia Global Talent Visa applications with the strength of our dedicated documentation division, Immigration Specialists, business associates &ndash; specializing in Australia Immigration. Our comprehensive services include application assessment for Applications, IELTS Coaching support, market analysis, industry identification, documentation, legal consulting methods, and post-landing services.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '283111903_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTI0', 1, '2023-12-28 05:10:01'),
(125, 74, 'How Indians can apply job in Australia from India in 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>India is the land where many job seekers wish to apply for Australia Immigration so that they can land a quality life and a safe, secure living for themselves as well as their families. But looking for jobs in Australia for Indians.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia has one of the strongest economies globally with skilled workers coming from here all over the world as one of the strongest economies all over the world with people from all over the world coming here to seek a well suited and paid job and secure an advanced standard of living.&nbsp; Many Indians have landed up jobs in Australia with Indians being one of the largest communities in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Be it teaching at universities, being medical practitioners, being in charge of information technology in top companies, cooking up some of delectable cuisines at world class restaurants or being owners of micro, macro or large businesses Indians have made their impact in securing best jobs in Australia for Indians.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Australia envisioned to attract 160,000 migrants by the end of 2022, and in case you are curious to know on how to get job in Australia from India but for that you need to be able to clear the visa processes and complete the eligibility requirements for the type of Australia PR visa immigration pathway you are applying for as a candidate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, the Australia immigration is a points based system granting them on a list of factors of age, education qualifications, work experience, specialist education credential, Australian study requirement, Professional Year in Australia, Credentialed community language, Study in regional Australia as well as Partner skills as well as being nominated if your job falls on Australia skilled occupation list of the specific Australian state or territory agency.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to apply for jobs in Australia from India?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a candidate to apply for jobs in Australia for Indians under Subclass 189 or skilled Independent visa the following requirements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The applicant should hold a previous work experience in a job listed on the Australia skilled occupation list.</li>\r\n	<li>Skill assessment report made by an appointed authority for that job type.</li>\r\n	<li>Submission of an Expression of Interest (EOI) through Skill Select which can be applied either from outside or even from within Australia.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For an EOI the applicant needs to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Be 45 years</li>\r\n	<li>Attain a minimum of 65 points on the Skills Assessment test</li>\r\n	<li>Hold a health as well as character certification</li>\r\n	<li>On receiving the invite for application, need to apply within 60 days</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For a candidate on how to apply for jobs in Australia from India under Subclass 190 or skilled nominated visa the following requirements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must be a nominee from an Australian state or territory</li>\r\n	<li>Previously held work experience in a nominated occupation present on job listed on the Australia skilled occupation list.</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum of 60 points or more points</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum of 6 in all bands of IELTS English language test</li>\r\n	<li>EOI submission to an immigration authority of Australia</li>\r\n	<li>No previous criminal record as well as health and fitness report</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Family Sponsorship Program the following requirements on how to apply for jobs in Australia from India are:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your husband or wife, parent, brother or sister, or any other relative should agree to sponsor for your Australia PR visa.</li>\r\n	<li>If the applicant is a dependant they need to have a partner in the form of Australia permanent resident or citizen of Australia.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>High Demand Jobs in Australia for Indians in 2023</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the high demand in jobs in Australia for Indian Fresher&rsquo;s are from fields of</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Health Care and Social Assistance (252,600 jobs)</li>\r\n	<li>Professional, Scientific &amp; Technical Services (172,400 jobs)</li>\r\n	<li>Education and Training (113,700 jobs)</li>\r\n	<li>Construction (118,800 jobs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are the top 25 High Demand Jobs in Australia for Indians in 2023:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Registered Nurses</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary School Teachers</li>\r\n	<li>Software and Applications Programmers</li>\r\n	<li>Electricians</li>\r\n	<li>Construction Managers</li>\r\n	<li>Carpenters and Joiners</li>\r\n	<li>Metal Fitters and Machinists</li>\r\n	<li>Plumbers</li>\r\n	<li>Motor Mechanics</li>\r\n	<li>University Lecturers and Tutors</li>\r\n	<li>Structural Steel and Welding Trades Workers</li>\r\n	<li>Solicitors</li>\r\n	<li>Management consultants</li>\r\n	<li>General Practitioners and Resident Medical officers</li>\r\n	<li>Other Specialist Managers</li>\r\n	<li>Civil Engineering Professionals</li>\r\n	<li>Early Childhood (Pre-primary School) Teachers</li>\r\n	<li>Painting Trades Workers</li>\r\n	<li>Industrial, Mechanical and Production Engineers</li>\r\n	<li>Database and Systems Administrators &amp; ICT Security Specialists</li>\r\n	<li>ICT Business and Systems Analysts</li>\r\n	<li>Chefs</li>\r\n	<li>Computer Network Professionals</li>\r\n	<li>Electronics Trades Workers</li>\r\n	<li>Social Workers</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>What would be the average salary in Australia in 2023?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As per the exchange rates of April 2023 the average salary in Australia for the year of 2023 amounts to 7,570 Australian dollars (AUD) per month. The average yearly salary in Australia has been calculated to 90,800 AUD which is equivalent to USD 60,355.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What is more remarkable is what we know as the average salary in Australia per month is much lesser than in the United States which is USD 7,900 per month and the United Kingdom which is mainly USD 7,347 per month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The average income Australia depends on some of the chief parameters like median salary in Australia for 2023 which is 6,650 AUD (USD 4,420) per month which means the middle value of all the salaries taken in to account which means half the Australian earns an income of 6,650 AUD per month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Average salary range is another factor in determining average salary in Australia that can range somewhere from 1,917 AUD (USD 1,274) per month up to 33,750 AUD (USD 22,433) per month. Other parameter to evaluate average income Australia is minimum hourly wage which is estimated at AUD 21.38 (USD 14.21) for part time and full-time workers as per the Australian Bureau of Statistics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The employees in Australia get an average salary increase of 8% every 16 months and annually means every 12 months. Some of the industry sectors which have received salary increments are from energy, healthcare, construction, banking, information technology, travel, as well as education</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the best possible way to apply for jobs in Australia from India?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1 &ndash; </strong>Do proper research as there are over 40 Australian immigrant Visas and choose the best option or pathway suited to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2 &ndash; </strong>Validate your visa as well examine the application as visas need sponsor, a citizen family member, or a specific amount of money for payment to a business or precise employment abilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3 - </strong>Submit an Australia immigration application once you have made sure the finalization of the right visa by following all necessities of the particular Australia PR visa route.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4 &ndash; </strong>wait for the conclusion or result of your application that can take some days or even weeks. Success of your Australia PR visa depends on the timing that can range from 6 to 8 months for completion of the entire process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5 &ndash; </strong>Success for Australia PR visa under which immigrant visa is issued allowing you to permanently live and work in Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can even apply for jobs in Australia from India via job search portals such as Indeed, Linkedin, GrabJobs, Adzuna, APS Jobs, Snaphunt, SEEK, JobServe, AllJobs Australia, GumTree and Gradconnection as well are some of the top job portals which lists some of the most in demand designations for jobs in Australia for Indians. Work on your CV as well as well as cover letter highlighting all your strengths, awards, extracurricular activities etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the part time jobs and pay in Australia?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the part time jobs and their pay in Australia whose Average pay per hour is AUD 35 (INR 1,961), Delivery driver pay is AUD 20.33 (INR 1,136), Personal tutor pay per hour is AUD 20.33 (INR 1,136), for Sales representative it is AUD 30 (INR 1,681), Customer Service is AUD 26 (INR 1,457), for Secretary it is AUD 25 (INR 1,401), Oral Hygienist it is AUD 32 (INR 1,793), for Waiter it is AUD 24 with tip (INR 1,345) per hour, Personal trainer the pay is AUD 25 (INR 1,401) and Admin Executive the average pay per hour is AUD 30 (INR 1,681).</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>How Orange Global Consultancy can help you?</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>If we speak of quality, credible, and reliable immigration services, then we cannot miss the name of Orange Global Consultancy Immigration Services and how their dedication and efficiency has impacted the immigration journeys of clients all over the world right since 1994.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We deal in an array of immigration visas like Permanent residency, student, business, as well as job seeker visas. From world-class consultation to immaculate documentation services and touching 50k application submissions makes us a leading name in the immigration industry for over years. For more queries connect with us by calling on 8336933522&nbsp;or mail us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '456675466_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTI1', 1, '2023-12-28 05:14:05'),
(126, 96, 'UK Immigration Consultants in Delhi - Highly Skilled Immigration Visa Program', '<p>One of the most influential and preferred destinations across the globe, from immigration perspectives, the United Kingdom encompassing Great Britain (England, Wales, and Scotland) &amp; Northern Ireland is 200% of the geographical size of the New York State. It enjoys an important place in the world, thanks to its buoyant economy and the quality of life that it offers to those who immigrate to it, for residence and business purposes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis is the country wherein the sun did not set once even as it ruled over more than half of the world, courtesy its unmatched economic might and military powers. Great Britain was the first industrialized country in the world. It was also an amazing power with unmatched political, economic, military, cultural, &amp; scientific influence the world over.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThough those days may have been vanished, and new players merged on the world map, the island nation still continues to enjoy widespread popularity and influence across the globe.&nbsp;Immigration is one of the most important things which has come in to the fore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UK is an epicentre of immigrants wherein people from diverse communities come and settle here along with their families either on Work visa, study visa as these provide a direct route to permanent residency in UK. It is important for us to learn how UK Immigration has shifted and there are no better people to explain than the UK Immigration Consultants in Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This highly developed western nation boasts of a robust economy, proffers superior lifestyle, vast business opportunities, a plethora of employment opportunities, unique infrastructure &amp; public transportations, not-too-high personal taxation, impressive law &amp; order, apart from an array of public welfare schemes. These combined together make the country one of the most preferred immigration destinations across the globe.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSkilled workers from across the globe find the country the best place to exhibit their expertise, acquire widespread name &amp; fame even as they enjoy a peaceful &amp; prosperous life therein. For the world immigrants, the <strong>UK immigration program</strong> is the best choice for study, business, employment, and/or settlement purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Population &amp; Geography</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The beautiful island nation is home to over 62.74 million people (2011 census) even while it is renowned and famous for its multicultural social living worldwide.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIts capital, London, is a famed world cosmopolitan city and holds the maximum number of the nation&rsquo;s people. The mega city is said to be one of the best place on the earth, for residence purposes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe nation&rsquo;s total land area is 243,160 square kilometers even while the UK is the 6th biggest economy in the world &amp; the third biggest in Europe, measured by the GDP. The Island nation is a permanent member of the UN Security Council. It is also a key member of the European Union (EU), the Commonwealth of Nations, NATO, G20, G8, OECD, World Trade Organization (WTO), and the Council of Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>UK Culture &amp; Lifestyle</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The overall quality of life and the living standard of the nationals of the UK is regarded one of the best in the world. London is celebrated for its high fashion culture, stock market, &amp; commerce goings-on. A large number of migrants from all across the globe wish to make London their home, for obvious purposes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEvery key living aspect, like home, work, safety, society, law, education, entertainment, &amp; healthcare are at its best and most appealing in the country. The nation&rsquo;s Permanent Residents are proffered essential public healthcare that too absolutely free. Many of the globe&rsquo;s well-known sport shows are organized in the country with the BPL Football season, Cricket, Golf, Tennis (Wimbledon), Rugby being just some of them. The migrants to the country get every possible facilities, luxuries, and things for which they immigrate to the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>UK Economy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The national economy is said to be one of the most powerful in the whole world (even today) even as the same is based on the partly regulated market economy. The nation&rsquo;s economy has direct &amp; significant influence on the global economy &amp; stock markets. Being the 6th biggest global economy, the UK economy generates employment to accommodate and reduce joblessness on the global stage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the factors of the UK economy which we cannot ignore is the flocking of innovative and talented overseas individuals who are interested in making UK their home. When it comes to finance and business services you will be glad to know that London which is the capital of the UK is regarded as the financial centre of the world with many big brands and companies ready to invest here.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFurther, industrialization &amp; manufacturing is the main source of the nation&rsquo;s economy &amp; employment. Automotive industry is the chief manufacturing sector with &pound;52.5 billion of turnover, and recruiting over 180,000 workers, besides accounting for &pound;26.6 billion.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Aerospace segment accounts for a turnover of &pound;20 billion. It is succeeded by the pharmaceutical industry with the reason being the same is the third biggest share of world R&amp;D expenditures in the pharmaceutical.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSignificantly post the world economic meltdown the UK is beginning to see positive results with business activities picking-up, firms continuing to employ fresh workers &amp; the end-users beginning to splurge yet again. A chain of studies made available reveal that the UK is back on the path to recovery even as the experts expect the national economy to develop by 1% this year and by 2% during 2014.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn short, the UK&rsquo; economy is the best playground for investors and/or business aliens, besides entrepreneur-migrants to exhibit their skills and lead a flourishing business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Employment &amp; Working Conditions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>UK Work Visas </strong>are usually much sought after by the world migrants keen to shift to an overseas country through the skilled <strong> UK&nbsp;Immigration Programs</strong>. London safeguards the right of its workers, via slapping strict employment rules &amp; salary criteria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is a mandatory rest period for workers which is up to 4 hours of work every day and a minimum of one day of rest per week. Also there is an additional pay for overtime work and laws speak of full-time workers to get minimum of 4 weeks paid vacation each year.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNearly every employee enjoys the right to not less than 4 weeks of fully paid leave per annum, illness pay, &amp; maternity or paternity leave. It&rsquo;s the duty of the recruiters/firms to take care of its workers&rsquo; health &amp; safety. The UK job and income conditions are regarded to be one of the best in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>UK Immigration Programs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>During the past couple of years, the nation has brought-in several fresh UK immigration classes. The points based skilled immigration category the <strong>Highly Skilled Migrant Programme</strong> which earlier had proved to be very successful &amp; fruitful has been substituted with the Tier 1 (General). It&rsquo;s a component of the nation&rsquo;s latest five-tier points based system even as the same includes highly skilled migrants, Sponsored Skilled Workers, Temporary workers, global students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about immigrating to united kingdom&nbsp;&nbsp;you can write an email on&nbsp;&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>', '', '900505792_UK-scaled2.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTI2', 1, '2023-12-28 05:20:15');
