(127, 97, 'High Demand jobs in UK for Indians in 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>Indians are one of the most efficient and hardworking immigrants that UK will ever find which is why there is no dearth of jobs in UK for Indians. The UK is regarded as one of the top 5 nations where Indians look to immigrate because of the cultural diversity and inclusion as well as well-paid employment opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The search jobs in UK for Indian fresher&rsquo;s comes with a wish to settle here along with their families in the long term as UK visa in the form of work permit offers them a path to even permanently settle in the nation which is even known as Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR) with which you can work, live as well as study anywhere in the UK. But to gain as an Indian you need to look for job vacancy in UK for Indian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UK Skilled worker visa is one pathway via which Indians come to UK for work and then eventually apply for jobs but to apply for one as an Indian you should have a confirmed job offer prior to this in the form of certificate of sponsorship&rsquo; from a UK employer with information regarding the position you have been offered for job in UK and be paid a minimum salary. Also, your job should be present in the list of eligible occupations for jobs in UK for Indian freshers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How do I get a job in the UK from India?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To get a job in UK from India you confirmed job offer as well as be eligible for the job vacancy in UK for Indian. The work life balance in UK is impressive with age not being a deciding aspect in terms of seniority position.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To even get a secure a jobs in UK for Indian graduates they need to attract the employers with a perfectly drafted CV, cover letter and mentioning achievements and awards which are relevant to the job profile they are applying for. Also, there are job portals like Naukri.com, Monster, Indeed or Linkedin for job openings which suit your profile and match your qualifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your cover letter creates an impression in front of your employers and can be summed up in one or two paragraphs where you briefly explain what your contribution shall be to the company whereas a CV shall introduce them to your personal information, qualifications, references and work experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having a work permit of UK makes it easier when you wonder on how to immigrate to UK but the best way to is to get a job and then apply for UK skilled worker visa as it increases your chances to live and work there and further apply for ILR or permanent residency in UK after residing for a minimum of 5 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Is IELTS required for a job in the UK?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, you are required to sit for your IELTS to prove your fluency in English language and secure a minimum of 7 in each band of Reading, writing, speaking and listening. You need to as someone applying for UK immigration should know how to read, write, speak and understand English to at minimum level B1 on the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR) scale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can be done by passing a Secure English Language Test (SELT) from an approved provider for you to even apply for UK visa as a skilled worker or holding a GCSE, A level, Scottish National Qualification level 4 or 5, Scottish Higher or Advanced Higher in English, added via study at a UK school that you started when you were below 18. Your English proficiency can even be proved if you show a degree-level academic requirement that was imparted in English - if you studied overseas, you&rsquo;ll need to apply via Ecctis (formerly UK NARIC) for confirmation that your degree is equal to a UK bachelor&rsquo;s degree, master&rsquo;s degree or even PhD.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Approved providers of the SELT test if you are applying from outside UK as an Indian are Pearson, PSI Services (UK) Ltd, IELTS SELT Consortium and LanguageCert, which means that IELTS is one of the approved language test providers as is required when you apply for a job in the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For your results to be even accepted you require acceptance of providers present on list of approved English language tests and have been sat at an approved test location. Ensure that the IELTS test you book is the one which is approved by the SELT.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the average salary in UK?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2023, the average salary in UK and what jobs in UK for Indians comes to is &pound;29,600 per year which means &pound;1,950 per month. Dentist, Engineer, Pharmacist, and Nursing professionals among other receive some of the highest average salary in UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In March 2023, the employees in UK were earning an average of 2,200 British pounds per month. There has been a rise and a difference since COVID pandemic had hit the world had salaries were on all time low with ensuing cuts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In November 2022, the current average salary in the UK is &pound;27,756, which is a 6.8% rise from 20. The median annual earnings for full time employees was 33,000 British pounds per year and for part time it is &pound;12,247 &nbsp;per year which is inclusive of gig economy workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;But more importantly they varied from region to region from 41,866 pounds in London to 29,521 pounds in the North East. But much of the salaries when you know <a href=\"https://www.abhinav.com/uk-immigration/how-to-immigrate-to-uk-from-india.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">how to immigrate to UK</a> for job depends upon factors such as industries, jobs and geographical locations as well as your age and level of educational qualification.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What are the highest paying jobs in UK?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2020 according to Office for National Statistics (ONS), the mean average salary across the entire of the UK was &pound;38,600 for full-time employees and &pound;13,803 for part-time. The average salary in England was &pound;39,452 for working full-time, and &pound;13,845 for part-time workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the highest paying jobs in UK are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\"><strong>Occupation</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\"><strong>National Average Salary</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Lawyer </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;51,237 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Chief Executive Officer </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;61,805 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Actuary </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;64,362 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Marketing Director </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;69,049 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Managing Director </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;74,450 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>IT Director </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;77,446 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Director of Engineering </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;78,368 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Tax Director</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;89,619 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Dermatologist </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;86,734 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:289px\">\r\n			<p><strong>Plastic Surgeon </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:288px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&pound;90,531 per year</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>What jobs in the UK will be the best paid in the future?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jobs in London for Indians which shall be the best in future are from IT and tech industry in roles of software engineer, data scientist, or web designer. In creative field in the role of film editor, graphic designer, as well as healthcare sector in the position of Doctors, paediatrician, nurse, veterinarian, and not to forget secondary education sector as math or even mandarin teachers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical Director, Neurosurgeon, Anaesthetist, Plastic Surgeon, Psychiatrist, Cardiologist, Director of Nursing as well as Clinical Director are some of the best paid jobs in the future when it comes to the medical field. When it comes to Scientists roles such as Environmental Scientist, Senior Biologist, Research Scientist, data Scientist shall have advantage in terms of high salaries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In engineering positions like Nuclear Engineer, Data Engineer, Software Engineer, Robotics Engineer, Mechanical Engineers, Chemical Engineer and Aeronautical Engineer are among the favoured jobs for the future. Let us not forget IT professional roles like Project Manager, Web Design Professionals, Programmers, and Software development professionals, IT Business Analyst, SEO Manager and Graphic Designers as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What are the most in-demand jobs in UK for Indians?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the most high demand jobs in UK are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Programmers and Software Developers</li>\r\n	<li>Cyber Security Specialists</li>\r\n	<li>Health Services and Residential Care</li>\r\n	<li>Architects</li>\r\n	<li>Graphic Designers</li>\r\n	<li>Physical Scientists</li>\r\n	<li>Sales Assistant</li>\r\n	<li>Operations Manager</li>\r\n	<li>Business Analyst</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>How Orange Global Consultancy can help you?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At Orange Global Consultancy Immigration Services we stand for Trust, Credibility and Commitment and are torchbearers of high quality immigration services for over years. We pledge to bring you seamless immigration experiences with sound consultation, spotless documentation and secure submission practices. To know more about jobs in UK for Indians, feel free to connect with us on 8336933522&nbsp;or mail us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '568465425_Indian-students-Studing-in-abroad.jpg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTI3', 1, '2023-12-28 05:31:16'),
(128, 98, 'UK Tier 1 Investor Visa Eligibility Requirements and Process', '<div>\r\n<p>Are you looking for a residency visa in the UK? One brilliant way is to apply for the Tier 1 Investment UK Visa, which allows you to do so. To apply for this visa, the individual needs to make a substantial financial commitment to the UK. This visa category is specially made for high net worth individuals who are willing and able to make a sizeable amount of investment in the UK to gain residency. The holders of this kind of UK Investor visa are allowed to work, study and conduct business activities in the UK. They can be also be joined by their dependants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UK is a great destination when it comes to investment and is considered by many as the financial capital of the world which is why many choose to invest in business here and the best way to go about the same is to apply for the UK Tier 1 Investor Visa. With this visa you can settle in the UK for a longer term via the route of investment which can eventually lead to citizenship.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This route of the UK Tier 1 Investor Visa is now closed to new applicants except those people who have an entry clearance leave to enter or continue as a Tier 1 Investor Migrant may apply to prolong their residence or for indefinite leave to remain. The applications for the further leave to remain as a Tier 1 Investor can be done till the duration of 17 February 2026.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not only does UK have the lowest corporation tax rates in the G20, but is a very competitive nation when it comes investment. Even an array of tax reliefs are provides to many national as well as overseas companies who want to invest in doing business here as it is a nation which is open and hospitable to newcomers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility Requirements for Tier 1 UK Investor Visa </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minimum of &pound;2,000,000 or more investment funds in the UK</li>\r\n	<li>Be 18 or over to be able to apply for his visa</li>\r\n	<li>Be qualified enough to prove that the funds belong to you, either your spouse, unmarried or same-sex partner.</li>\r\n	<li>Also, you need to open an account at a UK regulated bank to use for your funds</li>\r\n	<li>These funds should be held on one or more regulated financial institutions</li>\r\n	<li>Also, these funds should be free of wands in the UK. This money can be in the UK or overseas when you apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Unlike UK Skilled Worker Visa, you can even apply for the Tier 1 Investor visa if you are a Tier 4 visa holder student.</li>\r\n	<li>For this, you should have an unconditional agreement in writing from your financial sponsor. It must state whether to re-enter or reside in the UK if the government or a scholarship agency paid your living expenses or course fees.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required for UK Skilled visa </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You must have a current passport or any other valid travel identification</li>\r\n	<li>Also, you should carry with you tuberculosis (TB) test results if you plan to come to the UK for more than six months. Also, it is necessary to take this test if you belong to a country from where you need to take the test. A chest X-ray will be given as a test result for TB.</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal record certificate from any of the countries you have resided in for a total of 12 months over the past ten years.</li>\r\n	<li>Blank page in the passport of your visa</li>\r\n	<li>Give a certified translation of any of the submitted documents that are not either English or Welsh.</li>\r\n	<li>Remember to showcase the evidence backing the fact that you have the required investment funds for UK Visa.</li>\r\n	<li>If it is your money that you are investing, you need to show the amount of money you hold and where it is being contained</li>\r\n	<li>Show the source of these funds if you have had the money for less than two years if money passed by a relative.</li>\r\n	<li>Also, this money should be transferred to the UK and converted into the local currency.</li>\r\n	<li>If your partner possesses the money, you must present a certificate of marriage or civil partnership. If you are single or in a same-sex relation, then a proof that you have been in a long-term relationship for at least two years.</li>\r\n	<li>In the case of a partner, they should provide a statement confirming that they permit you to be in charge of the funds in the UK and a letter from a legal advisor stating that it is a valid declaration.</li>\r\n	<li>Lastly, you should produce a letter confirming that you have a UK bank regulated for using the investment funds. The letter should be issued by an authorized official and be dated within three months of your application.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;This letter should also be on the official headed paper belonging to the bank with your name and account number. There should be a confirmation letter that you have opened an account with this bank for the investment of &pound;2,000,000.</li>\r\n	<li>The letter should confirm that the Financial Conduct Authority regulates the bank and ensure checks on whether money laundering has been carried out.</li>\r\n	<li>Depending upon your circumstances, you should be ready to provide additional documents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cost of Applying for Tier 1 UK Investor Visa </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to immigrate to UK from India? </strong>For applying for this visa, you need to pay an application fee of &pound;1,623. In addition to this, you will be required to pay the healthcare surcharge as part of your application. If you want a priority service while extending or switching visas, you can make an extra payment of &pound;500 and get a decision within five working days of application submission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How can Orange Global Consultancy Help you with UK Investor Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our team of expert immigration specialists helps you in your UK immigration journey with world-class consultation as well as flawless documentation services. In the immigration industry for over years, Orange Global Consultancy Immigration Services is a pioneering, trusted, and valued name for quality immigration services. For more queries, you can ring us at 8336933522&nbsp;or connect with us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</p>\r\n</div>', '', '393137653_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTI4', 1, '2023-12-28 05:36:37'),
(129, 99, 'United Kingdoms Immigration New Exceptional Talent Visa Program', '<div>\r\n<p>The category is limited to providing 1000 places. The new category is meant for exceptionally talented people having performed remarkable work in the arena of science, arts and humanities with intention to work and settle in the UK in the later stages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to be exceptional or outstanding in the field which you have chosen to apply under when you move to the UK.&nbsp;You can work under this visa if you are eligible and are endorsed by either a renowned leader (exceptional talent) or an emergent leader (exceptional promise) as a matter of fact.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe prospective applicant must be globally recognized, or are likely to become global leaders in their niche area. Our immigration experts at Orange Global Consultancy would assist our prospective applicants in filing applications under the New Exceptional Talent Program for UK category, provided they qualify. Below mentioned are the pre-requisites to qualify under the UK Immigration New Exceptional Talent Visa Program.</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Process to apply for the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa Program</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The first stage begins with Tier 1 (Exceptional Talent) visa wherein you first need to apply to the Home Office for endorsement in the role of a leader or an emergent leader in your specific line of Interest. This is for those who have proved time and again about their exceptional talent in their own field to be considered for an endorsement like a proven record of successive successes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>When it comes to Exceptional Promise it speaks about the category of individuals who already are proven leaders in their respective field. These might have been the early birds, but have achieved tremendous success in their respective endeavours. The theme of progress is crucial when you file an application for the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa.</li>\r\n	<li>This first stage of endorsement must be applied for via online means as your application which has been submitted shall be analysed by an organisation who is in connection with your turf and can also be referred to as the&nbsp; &rsquo;Designated Competent Body&rsquo;. Some of the examples one can site are the Royal Society which is for science and medicine, The British Academy catering to humanities, Tech Nation complies to digital technology), Arts Council England is specially for art and architecture and not to forget the Royal Academy of Engineering.</li>\r\n	<li>In case you are an architect or are in to architecture, fashion or film and television, the Arts Council shall put your application forward to the Royal Institute of British Architects, British Fashion Council, as well as Producers Alliance for Cinema and Television when it comes to their designated bodies.</li>\r\n	<li>The new Tech Nation Visa Scheme of the government permits the body to authority endorse applications for the exceptional talent visa of the UK.&nbsp;This is due to the fact that the government wants to increase the number of talented immigrants to be able to help build the economic health of the UK.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>It takes a period of 8 weeks to get a decision as once you have succeeded once you get an email from the Home Office along with a copy of an endorsement letter.</li>\r\n	<li>The second stage of the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa process involves you applying for the actual visa. But if there is a dismissal of your visa you can even ask for a re-assessment of your endorsement.</li>\r\n	<li>Just keep in mind that just because you have the endorsement letter does not mean that you are guaranteed a visa. Reviews for the eligibility of your visa shall be made apart and on their very own grounds and reasons which are submitted for the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Entry requirement&nbsp;the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. It is essential to be endorsed by a designated Competent Body.<br />\r\n2. Not mandatory to have any English level requirement<br />\r\n3. General Grounds for Refusal would be applicable.<br />\r\n4. You should be outside from the European Union or Switzerland&nbsp;<br />\r\n5. You should submit the copy of the endorsement letter emailed to you at the first stage itself<br />\r\n6. If you are staying in the UK already ensure that you apply for the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa prior to the ending of your existence of your current leave to remain which is best described as a month prior to its end.<br />\r\n7. Make it a point to apply 3 months prior to you receiving your endorsement letter as this can lead to a refusal of your application.&nbsp;<br />\r\n8. In case you are applying from out of UK you should be submitting the test results of Tuberculosis if you come from a nation wherein it is mandatory to take the test.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>Fees to be submitted at the First and second stage of the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>The first stage of the entire process for the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa comes to &pound;456. Whereas when it comes to the second stage of the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa it generally costs &pound;152 but only &pound;97 if you belong to either Turkey or Macedonia. The cost of the application for the UK New Exceptional Talent Visa for dependants can come to a total of &pound;608.</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Extension</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>It is mandatory for the applicant to be economically active in their niche.</li>\r\n	<li>Intermediate English level.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Grants of leave </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Initial grant of 3 years and 4 months</li>\r\n	<li>2 years extension (after fulfilling the pre-requisites)<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Settlement </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>It is mandatory for the applicant to be economically active in their niche</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledge of life test is applicable</li>\r\n	<li>May qualify for ILR after a span of 5 years.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dependents </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Granted leave in line with main applicant.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about UK Immigration New Exceptional Talent Visa Program you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '507312745_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTI5', 1, '2023-12-28 05:40:04'),
(130, 100, 'How to Immigrate UK from India', '<div>\r\n<p><strong>Life in United Kingdom? Why to Migrate from India</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>United Kingdom has become the next hot-spot destination among many skilled workers and students from India. Every year, people in high numbers are migrating to the UK for work, study, and visit purposes. The country offers promising opportunities in terms of job, lifestyle, pollution-free environment, safety, and more. Lately, most of the people chose UK migration due to better employment prospects. The labor market and economy are two most important factors encouraging migration from all over world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, UK is a hub of some of the world&rsquo;s best colleges and universities. In fact, many people who migrate to the UK for study, find jobs and stay back here forever. Also, the fact the English is the first language in the country, most people find it easy to settle here permanently.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The United Kingdom also boasts a very strong and vibrant economy, backed by lower employment rates. Many large companies also prefer to invest in the UK due to its favorable labor laws, and thus create more jobs for its citizens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why Indians Migrate to UK from India? Solid Reasons!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another strong reason for Indians to migrate to UK is studying in some of the world class universities as well as globally ranked colleges that help you get some of the best jobs as you can study and work and then later apply for the work permit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even despite the global pandemic crisis since 2020, Indians were the ones who were issued majority of the sponsored skilled-worker visas which is more than any of the countries in the world. This speaks about the strong ties between India and UK with immigrants from India being in positions that pay very handsome salaries.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Healthcare is one of the pivotal sectors which have boomed and have managed to attract many Indian migrants since there is a dire need of skilled healthcare and medical personnel in the UK. You will be surprised to know that amongst all Indians largest overseas class who is working in the National Health Services (NHS), only coming in after the British nationals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another sector to be spoken about is the Information technology sector wherein near to three out of the five visas are issued to Indians since they are more skilled and talented in working in overseas markets like the UK. The nation is in requirement of workers and professionals in the fields of hospitality, veterinarians, doctors, scientists, architects, artists as well as others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Different Ways to Migrate to UK?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many different types of visa options available for people seeking immigration to UK from India. The type of visa suitable for you depends entirely on what you want to do in the UK and how long you plan to stay in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, to put broadly, UK visa&nbsp;can be classified into Tier 1 and Tier 2 Visas. The eligibilities for both visas are assessed through a point-based system. So, let&rsquo;s discuss them in detail:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tier 1 (Entrepreneur) Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a high net-worth entrepreneur dreaming of investing in the UK, then this visa is for you. The UK Innovator Visa&nbsp;allows investors to set up a company or buy an existing business in the country. The Visa category may also be divided into- Start-up Visa and Innovator Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can apply for a Start-up Visa if:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You wish to establish a new business in the UK;</li>\r\n	<li>You are from outside the European Economic Area (EEA) and Switzerland</li>\r\n	<li>You satisfy the other eligibility requirements for the visa.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Who is Eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The applicant must be at least 18 years old or more</li>\r\n	<li>Meet the English language requirement</li>\r\n	<li>Be able to demonstrate enough source of funds or personal savings to support themselves during initial days in the UK.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Processing Time</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Innovator Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As per the UK immigration rules, you are eligible to apply for the Innovator Visa if:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>you want to set up a new business or buy an already existing business in the UK. And, you have your business or business idea endorsed by an approved body</li>\r\n	<li>You must be able to invest at least &pound;50,000 if you want to set up a new business.</li>\r\n	<li>you&rsquo;re from outside the European Economic Area (EEA) and Switzerland</li>\r\n	<li>you meet the other eligibility requirements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Who is Eligible?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Candidates who are from outside the European Economic Area (EEA) and Switzerland</li>\r\n	<li>Applicants who are 18 years of age or above at the time of application.</li>\r\n	<li>be able to demonstrate enough source of funds or personal savings to support themselves during initial days in the UK.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Tier 2- General Work Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This UK visa category is designed for skilled workers who wish to migrate to the UK permanently and address the labor skill shortage needs of the country. Candidates under the Tier 2 visa are selected through the point-based system, and is only issued to highly skilled individuals who have been offered a job in the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be eligible, you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have a valid job offer or a job in the occupation list.</li>\r\n	<li>You&rsquo;re from outside the European Economic Area (EEA) and Switzerland</li>\r\n	<li>You also need to get sponsored from a legitimate UK employer before you apply to live permanently in UK.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Processing Time for UK Tier 2 Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>All candidates are advised to apply for the tier 2 visa 3 months before the day you&rsquo;re due to start work in the UK. Your profile will be processed within 3 weeks in case you are applying from outside the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>What is Highly Skilled Migrant Program (HSMP UK)?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Introduced in January 2002, the Highly Skilled Migrant Program was designed to cope with the demand for skilled labors in the UK. The visa category is designed for skilled workers who can come to live and work in the UK. The program was a huge success at the time of its launch; however, it was later replaced by General Tier 1 skilled migration visa, which includes all work, study, and training immigration routes into the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>What Documents you need to apply for UK Migration?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every visa is different, therefore has unique requirements in terms of document submission. Prospective candidates must carefully analyze each requirement before making the final submission. Below is just a general list of documents that you must have while filing the application for UK immigration:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A copy certificate of sponsorship reference number (in case of Tier 1 General Visa).</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of English language proficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of bank statement to demonstrate that you have sufficient funds or personal savings to support yourselves in UK.</li>\r\n	<li>a current passport or travel document to prove you can travel - you need a blank page in your passport for your visa</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of expired passports or travel related documents to show your travel history.</li>\r\n	<li>Medical test results, especially tuberculosis, in case you come from a listed country</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of criminal record certificates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about How to Immigrate to UK you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '320772933_Immi.jpg', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTMw', 1, '2023-12-28 05:43:27'),
(131, 101, 'How to apply UK Skilled Worker Visa in 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>Being at the center stage of economic and financial development, the UK has an incredibly high quality of life and diverse and unique employment opportunities for the skilled professional who wants to Migrate to the UK to live, work, and settle with their families long term. The UK economy has a high demand for skilled workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Not only this, the nation has a multicultural community making it easier to transition. The country is exceptional in healthcare and education, providing its citizens free of cost or at subsidized rates. Not only is it a great place to settle, but with its relaxed immigration policies, a good place to work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The UK skilled worker visa allows you to come as well as stay in the UK to a job which is qualified by an approved employer and has been substituted by the Tier 2 (General) work visa. The aim of this visa is to call in highly talented overseas individuals who come to UK for the purpose of being able to apply to permanent residence in the UK that accrues many benefits that are long tern for the person who applies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Skilled Worker for the UK Skilled Worker Visa are selected based on the points they have scored and whether or not their occupation is present on the updated list of shortage occupations. This makes them eligible to get an offer letter without having the need to give the labour test and being able to reside in the UK as a skilled worker for a period of up till 5 years.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>New Developments of the UK Skilled Worker Visa</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The UK Skilled worker visa is the best route for non EU nationals who want to reside as well as get a full-time employment in UK. Immigration has been rising in the UK in 2022 and shall continue being so in the coming years.&nbsp; In 2021 a total of 239,987 work-related visas were issued which is a 110% surge from last year and a 25% rise from 2019.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What more the overseas students who have moved to UK to study can switch to applying for UK Skilled worker visa even prior to completing their college degree. This is a great option for those who wish to work in UK and find it difficult to apply for work visas in the UK.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This change in rule and move by the UK government has been to make the UK Skilled Worker visa more accessible to a wider spectrum of persons who wish to work and stay in the UK for the longer term. This shall allow them to share and give their skills and experience to the UK economy for the upcoming future. This is a bid by the UK to rope in overseas global talent as it keeps the fire of innovation and growth burning in the economic hearth of UK.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Eligibility Requirements for UK Skilled Worker Program </strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You are required to work for a UK employer who the Home Office has approved</li>\r\n	<li>You should have with you a &#39;certificate of sponsorship&#39; from your employer who has the requisite information about the kind of job designation you would be hired for in the UK.</li>\r\n	<li>For UK immigration, as a skilled worker, you will need to do a job that is mentioned on the list of eligible occupations</li>\r\n	<li>Payment of a minimum salary threshold. It will also depend on your nature of work</li>\r\n	<li>However, the specific eligibility depends on the kind of job that you have applied for.</li>\r\n	<li>Before applying for your UK visa for a skilled worker, you must have a confirmed job offer.</li>\r\n	<li>Also, you should be able to speak, read, write and understand English. You will need to prove your fluency and command of the language.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Documents required for UK Skilled visa </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Certificate&nbsp; of the sponsorship reference number</li>\r\n	<li>Test results stating your proficiency in the English language</li>\r\n	<li>Any valid passport or any other document that gives proof of your identity as well as nationality.</li>\r\n	<li>Job title as well as your annual salary</li>\r\n	<li>The occupation code for the job you have applied for in the UK</li>\r\n	<li>Also, the employer&#39;s name and sponsor license number will be on their certificate of sponsorship.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that your certificate of sponsorship is updated as it was assigned to you before the Tier 2 (General) work; the Skilled Worker visa replaced the visa.</li>\r\n	<li>Personal savings that are enough to support yourself as well as your family in the UK, for example, bank statements, unless and until your certificate of sponsorship states support from your employer</li>\r\n	<li>Relationship proof with your partner/spouse or children when they have applied along with you.</li>\r\n	<li>If you belong to a listed country, then your tuberculosis test results</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal record certificate in case of some particular jobs when in UK immigration</li>\r\n	<li>UK Ph.D. certificate, your unique Ecctis reference number (formerly unique UK NARIC reference number) that is if you are applying from outside the UK, you will be required to apply via the Ecctis.</li>\r\n	<li>Also, you are required to have a blank page in your passport if you are from outside the EU, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland, or Liechtenstein.</li>\r\n	<li>And lastly, if your documents are not in English or Welsh, you will need to give a certified translation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Cost of Applying for UK Skilled worker visa </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For applying for a UK visa for skilled workers, you need to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Make a payment of the application fee. The standard price falls between 610 to &pound;1,408, depending on your circumstances.</li>\r\n	<li>Along with this, you need to pay the healthcare surcharge, which is usually &pound;624 per year.</li>\r\n	<li>To support yourself in the UK, you will need to have a minimum amount of &pound;1,270.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How can Orange Global Consultancy Help you?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Our team of expert immigration consultants helps you in your UK immigration journey with world-class consultation as well as flawless documentation services. For over years, Orange Global Consultancy Services is a pioneering, trusted, and valued name for quality immigration services in the immigration industry. For more queries, you can call us on 8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '854893784_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTMx', 1, '2023-12-28 05:47:06'),
(132, 102, 'United Kingdoms Innovator Visa for Investors and Entrepreneurs', '<div>\r\n<p>A new business visa category has been created for investors and entrepreneurs to set up their business as well as settle along with their families in the UK. This visa came in to the picture on April, 2019 and came in place of Tier 1 Entrepreneur Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If innovative new ideas are sprouting in your mind and you want to give them a voice, UK provides you with a platform which is a breeding ground for Investors and Entrepreneurs who want to do business in the diverse and economically rich UK.&nbsp;Your idea should have a patent and uniqueness to it and have a value and viability attached for it to thrive and be successful when you apply for the UK innovator visa.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experienced businesspersons can use this visa to establish or set up their business in the UK. You can even settle in the UK with the pathway of this visa as it is a way you are adding value to the economy of UK.&nbsp; This visa can lead to indefinite leave to remain in the UK at the end of the duration.&nbsp; As an person applying the Innovator visa you can even bring along your spouse/partner or children under the age of 18 to the UK.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two categories you can apply, as if it is a fresh one and first time you shall need to apply under the new business&rsquo; requirement as per the Immigration Rules and if it is an existing business for expansion then you need to apply under the &lsquo;same business&rsquo; criteria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be a part of the business and innovator category you are not required to be ole founder of the proposed business. In the upcoming time, the Innovator who has the leave to remain who puts an application for a stay extension in the UK shall need to apply under the &lsquo;same business&rsquo; criteria if the business remains the same as mentioned in the endorsement letter that was submitted firstly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefits of UK Innovator Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You can live in the UK for a period of 5 years 4 months with your family</li>\r\n	<li>Once you complete this duration you are permitted by the UK government for permanent settlement (Indefinite Leave to Remain)</li>\r\n	<li>There is investment as low as &pound;50,000</li>\r\n	<li>You can live along with your family members in the UK for 3 years</li>\r\n	<li>Also, you can even get a visa extension for a period of 2 years</li>\r\n	<li>As a permanent resident of UK you will have access to perks which are related to education in the UK as well as your healthcare will be covered by the government of UK which will save you from incurring major costs of medical related expenses.</li>\r\n	<li>What is best about UK Immigration Visa is that it requires an easy and quick processing.</li>\r\n	<li>Not only is the visa innovative and scalable, but it is also viable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>UK Innovator Visa Eligibility</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are looking forward to start a business in the UK you will be required to meet the following eligibility requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For innovation visa UK eligibility you must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The prospective applicant must be from outside the EEA and Switzerland</li>\r\n	<li>The candidate should be a minimum of 18 years of age</li>\r\n	<li>Unlike the UK Skilled Worker Visa, you should be willing to make a minimum investment of &pound;50,000 in case they want to set up a new business in the UK.</li>\r\n	<li>Must have their business idea endorsed by an approved body. (This endorsement should not have been withdrawn before the Home Minister even puts the application under his consideration)</li>\r\n	<li>Should have proficiency and fluency in the English language</li>\r\n	<li>They must also be able to support themselves as well as their families, due to which they need to meet certain financial requirements.</li>\r\n	<li>You need to mention the source of your funding.</li>\r\n	<li>You will not require any investment funds if pour business is already established and has been endorsed for an earlier visa or you have changed your business and have already agreed it with your endorsing body.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Long Does it Take to Process an Innovator Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the Innovator visa UK Process to even start it will require the applicant to prove their identity as well as furnish the required supporting documents. To do this you will be required to have extra time if you require an appointment to get this done. Once you have applied for online, proven your identity as well as submitted all your documents you will usually get a decision within 3 weeks if you are outside the UK and 8 weeks if you are in UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the Innovator Visa Requirements?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your business proposal will be required to meet certain Innovator visa UK requirements to be able to be functional in UK:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Innovation:</strong> The prospective applicant will need to showcase that they have a genuine and unique as well as original business plan which meets a new or existing market requirement, and will thus prove to be profitable to the British economy as well as their overall workforce. Just keep in mind that the candidate cannot join or invest in a business which is already in to trading.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Being Viable: </strong>The applicants needs to showcase that they possess the required skills, knowledge and the know-how of the market to be able to run a business successfully in to which he has put his mind in to.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Scalability: </strong>One very important Innovator visa UK requirements is for the applicant to ensure the UK government that their model of business or projected business will have the ability to generate employment as well as add to the economic growth, development and progress of the UK economy on a whole.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about UK Innovator Visa you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '846382453_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTMy', 1, '2023-12-28 05:50:12');
