(133, 103, 'Global Talent Visa-Live and Work in the UK', '<div>\r\n<p>The UK Global Talent Visa program is an immigration pathway for highly skilled and talented foreign workers working in specific sectors seeking to immigrate to the UK. The visa category replaced the Tier 1 (Exceptional Talent) visa in February 2020. The pathway is available for creative practitioners, artists, academic researchers, and international experts outside the European Economic Area (EEA) to settle and work in the UK and make valuable contributions with their cutting-edge expertise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a promising individual seeking&nbsp;UK immigration&nbsp;and wishing to live and work in the UK&rsquo;s digital technology sector, the Global Talent Visa is for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the Global Talent Visa pathway, if you are a &lsquo;leader or a potential leader in the fields of science and technology, arts, financial technology (fintech), cybersecurity, gaming, artificial intelligence, medicine, or academic research, you may be eligible to apply for the visa. The visa stream allows you to work in the UK for up to five years without a sponsor or a job offer. In year six, one becomes entitled to indefinite leave (ILR), equivalent to permanent residence status. After ten years, one can apply for UK&nbsp; citizenship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon completing the settlement application and meeting the basic residency requirements in the UK, you become eligible to apply for British citizenship. Typically, this will happen ten years from the date of issuance of your first visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two routes available under the Global Talent Visa:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Exceptional Talent- Created for people already established as leading practitioners or recognized experts in their field.</li>\r\n	<li>Exceptional Promise- aimed at attracting people with the potential to become leading practitioners of recognized experts in their field</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>The applicant must receive a letter of endorsement from one of the designated endorsement bodies, including the Royal Society, the British Academy, the Royal Academy of Engineering, Arts Council England, and Tech Nation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Who is eligible for the UK Global Talent Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The primary UK global talent visa requirements are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your age must be a minimum of 18 to apply for this visa</li>\r\n	<li>You can use the global talent visa pathway if you are working in one of the following sectors:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Academia or research</li>\r\n		<li>Arts and culture</li>\r\n		<li>Digital technology</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must be endorsed by one of the approved endorsing bodies in the UK.</li>\r\n	<li>Be internationally recognized in your field as a world leader (Exceptional Talent) or have demonstrated exceptional Promise or have the potential to become a world leader in your area (Exceptional Promise).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key benefits of the Global Talent Visa</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The visa is based on your unique background, skills, and achievements.</li>\r\n	<li>The visa is granted for up to 5 years</li>\r\n	<li>One can easily extend it as many times as they want</li>\r\n	<li>Highly flexible. Not tied to any specific employer or company.</li>\r\n	<li>You can include family members in the application</li>\r\n	<li>Change jobs without telling the Home Office</li>\r\n	<li>Do volunteer work</li>\r\n	<li>Travel abroad and return to the UK</li>\r\n	<li>May lead to permanent residency in the UK</li>\r\n	<li>There are no language or minimum salary eligibility requirements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Do I apply for the UK Global Talent Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to immigrate to UK&nbsp;using the global talent visa?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Get the endorsement letter from a designated endorsement body. Your endorsement body depends on your field of expertise. The endorsement fee for stage one is &pound;456.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong>: If you are granted an endorsement, you must apply for your visa for leave to enter or remain. You must apply within three months upon receiving your acceptance. The endorsement fee for stage two is &pound;152.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you include your partner or children in your application, they&rsquo;ll each need to pay &pound;608.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What documents do I need for UK Global Talent Visa?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for the Global Talent UK Visa, you will need to submit the following documents</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Copy of a valid passport or other document showing your identity and nationality</li>\r\n	<li>Your tuberculosis test results if you belong to a country that requires you to take the test</li>\r\n	<li>Your endorsement letter</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of immigration health surcharge fee and the application fee</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processing Time</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The processing for endorsement usually takes up to 28 days to complete. The visa application process can carry a maximum of three weeks if you apply from outside the UK and a maximum of eight weeks if you apply within the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Can We Help?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The global talent visa for the UK is a highly competitive and complicated visa category, requiring an in-depth understanding of the process. At Orange Global Consultancy Services, we have a proven track record of guiding applicants wishing to enter the UK. We provide professional, practical, and expert immigration advice on immigration to help individuals realize their dream of obtaining a British passport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We can assist in the overall process of the Global Talent Visa Application, including required coordination with endorsement agencies.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about <strong>Global Talent Visa UK</strong> you can write an email on info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experience immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '651936262_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTMz', 1, '2023-12-28 05:53:18'),
(134, 104, 'The UK scale-up visa route for talented foreign immigrants', '<div>\r\n<p>The government of the United Kingdom unleashed a new visa route last week, known as the Scale-up Worker Visa Route. The Scale-Up worker visa permits talented and highly-qualified overseas workers to come to the United Kingdom to work in an eligible job recruited by a UK Scale-up Sponsor. Successful applicants can work for fast-growing UK businesses, called scale-up businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The UK Home Office launched a new pathway to welcome skilled professionals across the globe, including India. The latest statistics by the British government also unveiled that Indians dominated the UK immigration under skilled visa streams with excellent numbers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Launched recently from August 2022, the UK scale-up visa route is a way in which you can work in a qualified job for a swiftly growing business in the UK. This should happen for a minimum duration of 6 months and this route allows the UK businesses undergoing fast growth to recruit highly skilled overseas workers and they be the best ones.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The holders of the UK scale-up visa route can leave their role of being sponsored after 6 months and move or transfer to an unsponsored role. In order to get UK scale-up visa you should have your occupation present on the list of qualified occupations which are in demand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In that case your employer should be able to provide 4-digit occupation code for your role. This can be used to check as in whether or not your selected job is qualified. This visa route is to attract top class talent. This in turn pumps up the innovation gene in to the UK business stream. Only the very highly skilled&rdquo; and &ldquo;academically elite&rdquo; have the qualification for this visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest Scale-up Visa is directed at high-growth businesses to recruit the best and the brightest talent. The visa will benefit many Indians by allowing UK companies to leverage the vast pool of talented Indian professionals.&nbsp;The Scale-Up visa leads to settlement in the UK. Applicants can include their partner and dependent children in the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Potential applicants will need a sponsor to be eligible for the scale-up visa. Your employer must fulfill the basic eligibility before sponsoring you for the visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Requirements for a Scale-up Visa &ndash; Sponsored Application </strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Have a confirmed job offer from the UK with a validity of at least six months.</li>\r\n	<li>Have a valid Certificate of Sponsorship issued by the UK-based Sponsor for the job you intend to do. The certificate must also contain information regarding the job role you have been offered.</li>\r\n	<li>Your salary must be equal to or exceed both &pound;33,000 per year, &pound;10.58 per hour, and the &#39;going rate for the job;</li>\r\n	<li>Your Certificate of Sponsorship must have been issued no more than three months before your&nbsp;Scale-up Visa&nbsp;Sponsored Application date.</li>\r\n	<li>Show English language proficiency of at least CEFR Level B1.</li>\r\n	<li>Have sufficient funds to manage your expenses in the UK.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Your certificate of sponsorship must contain the below information:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your name, job position, and salary;</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmation that you will work for your Sponsor for at least six months;</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmation that the Certificate of Sponsorship:\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li>&nbsp;Has not been used in a previous application that was either issued or refused;</li>\r\n		<li>&nbsp;Has not been withdrawn either by the Sponsor or denied by the Home Office.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Eligibility requirements for approved UK employers 2022</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Employers must meet the following eligibility requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To be called a Scale-up business, the company must demonstrate growth of 20% or more in either employment or turnover year-on-year for at least three years;</li>\r\n	<li>Employed a minimum of 10 people at the start of the three years</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Financial Funds for Scale-up Visa</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The applicant must have &pound;1,270 or more in their bank account and must have held these funds for at least 28 consecutive days before applying. Applicants already residing in the UK for one or more years are exempt from this requirement.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Scale Up Visa- Sponsored and Unsponsored Route</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>One thing that makes the Scale-Up a standout pathway is its ability to give flexibility to applicants to work under any employer after six months in the UK. The applicant is not obliged to work under the employer who sponsored them initially and can switch jobs after the initial six-month period. If you are wondering how to immigrate to UK, the scale-up visa is the pathway for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This kind of provision offers considerable flexibility to visa holders as most employers in the UK do not hold sponsor licenses. Thus, it opens a wide range of employment opportunities for the applicant.&nbsp;You can even become self-employed after a period of 6 months and those who change their job or employer post 6 months need not apply for a new visa. But despite this, you shall need to meet the requirements of salary when you think of applying for visa extension.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those who switch jobs after six months&#39; completion need not apply for a new visa. However, they must satisfy the minimum wage requirement while applying for a visa extension.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, suppose you want to change your job&nbsp;within the first six months&nbsp;after the approval of your scale-up visa. In that case, you will need to inform the Home Office by submitting an online application regarding your scale-up visa status update. Please note that your new employer must be a scale-up employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How Can Orange Global Consultancy Immigration Services Help?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Our team of talented and experienced immigration agents are expert at handling applications related to the new scale-up visa. Our range of services include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Evaluating the needs of your the new Scale-Up visa</li>\r\n	<li>Advise suitable visa options as per your needs</li>\r\n	<li>Checking whether your sponsor meets the scale-up business license criteria</li>\r\n	<li>Applying for a Scale-Up visa</li>\r\n	<li>Follow-ups&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Even if you seek&nbsp;more information about UK Scale Up Worker Visa&nbsp;you can write an email to info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;and one of the most experienced immigration consultants will get in touch with you to help you out with your questions and concerns or you can also choose to call us on +91-8336933522.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '510609730_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTM0', 1, '2023-12-28 05:57:11'),
(135, 105, 'Europe Visa', '<h2>How to Apply for a Visa and Travel to Europe from India</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Are you dreaming of Europe immigration, visiting its famous landmarks, or working in one of its diverse and dynamic countries? If so, you may be wondering what are the visa requirements and processes for Indian citizens who want to travel to Europe. In this post, we will give you an overview of the different types of visas you may need, depending on your purpose and duration of stay.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Types of visas for Europe</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Europe is not a single country, but a continent that consists of many countries, each with its own laws and regulations. However, some European countries have agreed to form a common area of free movement, known as the Schengen Area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Schengen visa is a short-stay visa that allows you to visit any of the 26 countries that are part of the Schengen Area for up to 90 days within a 180-day period. The Schengen Area includes most of the European Union countries, except for Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, Ireland, and Romania, as well as Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway, and Switzerland. With a Schengen visa, you can travel freely within the Schengen Area without going through border checks at each country.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Applying for a Schengen Visa from India &ndash; Steps </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visiting Europe for tourism, business, family visits, or other short-term purposes requires a Schengen visa for Indian citizens. This is also known as a tourist visa for Europe from India. To apply for this visa, you need to contact the embassy or consulate of the country where you plan to spend most of your time in Europe, or where you will enter first if you plan to visit multiple countries. Alternatively, you can apply through a visa application center (VAC) authorized by the embassy or consulate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for a Schengen Europe visa from India, you need to follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check the visa requirements and eligibility criteria for the country you want to visit. You can find this information on the official websites of the embassies or consulates or on this website.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare the essential documents for your visa application. These may include your passport, application form, photos, flight reservation, hotel booking, travel insurance, proof of financial means, purpose of travel, and other supporting documents depending on your visa type.</li>\r\n	<li>Make an appointment online or by phone with the embassy or consulate or the VAC where you want to submit your application.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to your appointment and submit your application along with the Europe visa cost and biometric data (fingerprints and photo). The standard visa fee is &euro;80 (about Rs. 7,200) for adults and &euro;40 (about Rs. 3,600) for children between 6 and 12 years old. Some categories of applicants are exempt from paying the fee or pay a reduced fee.</li>\r\n	<li>Wait for your visa decision. The processing time for the Europe Visa may vary depending on the country and the season, but it usually takes around 15 days. In some instances, the time frame maybe 30 or 60 days. You can track the status of your application online or by contacting the embassy or consulate or the VAC.</li>\r\n	<li>Collect your passport with your visa sticker or have it delivered to you by courier. Check the validity and accuracy of your visa and make sure it matches your travel plans.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> You can apply for a tourist visa to Germany from India if you want to visit Germany for a short stay (up to 90 days in a 180-day period). This visa is also known as a Schengen visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are Other Types of Visas for Europe?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to visit a European country that is not part of the Schengen Area, such as the United Kingdom (UK), Ireland, Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, or Romania, you will need a separate visa for that country. These visas are issued by each individual country according to their own rules and regulations. Some of the most common types of visas for Europe are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>National (D) Visa:</strong> This is a long-stay visa that allows you to stay in one specific country for more than 90 days. It may also allow you to travel within the Schengen Area for up to 90 days in a 180-day period. You need to apply for this visa at the embassy or consulate of the country where you want to stay.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>EU Blue Card:</strong> This is a Europe work permit that allows highly skilled workers from non-EU countries to live and work in any EU country except Denmark and Ireland. It is valid for up to four years and can be renewed. You need to have a valid job offer or contract from an employer in an EU country before applying for this card.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Student Visa:</strong> This is a type of national (D) visa that allows you to study at an accredited educational institution in an EU country. It may also allow you to work part-time or full-time depending on the country and course. You need to have an acceptance letter from a school or university before applying for this visa.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Family Reunion Visa:</strong> This is a type of national (D) visa that allows you to join your spouse, partner, parent, child, or other relative who is an EU citizen or resident in an EU country. You need to prove your family relationship and meet certain Europe visa requirements such as income, health insurance, and integration before applying for this visa.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If you are looking for a great country to relocate to, you might want to consider the Netherlands. You can apply for a Netherlands Schengen visa, which will allow you to enter and stay in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to Apply for Other Types of Visas for Europe from India?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Europe visa process for other types of visas for Europe from India is similar to the Schengen visa process, but with some differences. You need to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check the visa requirements and eligibility criteria for the country and visa type you want to apply for. You can find this information on the official websites of the embassies or consulates or on this website.</li>\r\n	<li>Gather the required documents for your visa application. These may include your passport, application form, photos, proof of purpose, proof of financial means, proof of accommodation, health insurance, language proficiency, and other supporting documents depending on your visa type.</li>\r\n	<li>Make an appointment online or by phone with the embassy or consulate where you want to submit your application.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to your appointment and submit your application along with the visa fee and biometric data (fingerprints and photo). The visa fee may vary depending on the country and visa type.</li>\r\n	<li>Wait for your visa decision. The processing time may vary depending on the country and visa type, but it usually takes longer than a Schengen visa. You can track the status of your application online or by contacting the embassy or consulate.</li>\r\n	<li>Collect your passport with your visa sticker or have it delivered to you by courier. Check the validity and accuracy of your visa and make sure it matches your travel plans.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you need a Europe tourist visa or a work visa, we are here to help you with your Europe visa process. Please contact us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in&nbsp;or call 8336933522&nbsp;if you have any questions.</p>', '', '329507098_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTM1', 1, '2023-12-28 23:25:29'),
(136, 106, 'Austria Job Seeker Visa from India in 2023', '<div>\r\n<p>If there is a European nation which has all the right elements when it comes to living a life of comfort and getting access to some of the best jobs then you cannot miss the name of Austria which has excellent standards of living for 8.3 million people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, you should know that Vienna was also ranked as best city to live on the global scale for the 10th consecutive year. Also a member of the European Union this city has a German speaking population housing some of the largest number of immigrants making it a diverse nation to apply for the <strong>Austria Job Seeker visa</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Austria Job Seeker visa is actually a work permit spanning across 6 months and are provided to highly qualified applicants to come and seek job opportunities in Austria. This UK visa is based on a points based system wherein a person who scores 70 out of 100 points is considered to be highly qualified. It also goes by the name of Austria Red-White-Red Card (RWR Card).</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Austria job seeker visa from India</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As an Indian looking to settle in the beautiful country of Vienna you can apply for the Austria job seeker visa from India (category D visa) by yourself at the capable Austrian representation (embassy or consulate) in your home country or the nation from where you belong. You can access this UK visa application forms at the Austrian representative authority.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under the Red-White-Red Card Scheme you are allowed to search for work in Austria for a 6 months and keep in mind when you apply for Austria job seeker visa from India that it provides entry to only &lsquo;Very Highly Qualified Workers&rsquo;. As an applicant if you fail to look for a job within the 6 month period then you have to go back to India. If not this visa the <strong>Sweden Job Seeker visa</strong> is also a good and viable option.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Points of the Austria Job Seeker visa are given based on the factors of age, Educational qualification applicable Work Experience, English Language as well as Studies in Austria. This UK visa helps you search for a suitable job in Austria. Once you get an offer letter from an Austrian employer you can transform the visa to a Red-White-Red (RWR) card.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Austria job seeker visa requirements</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are the following Austria job seeker visa requirements:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Education qualifications such as a course record book and related examination certificates or a document which shows completion of a program of studies in Austria. Also, a Post-doctoral qualification or PhD</li>\r\n	<li>Recognised awards or prizes</li>\r\n	<li>Gross salary of previous year earned in a senior management position with a company listed on the stock exchange or a company for which the Austrian foreign trade office have given a positive report regarding their business activities.</li>\r\n	<li>Patent publication in the form of Patent applications and publications</li>\r\n	<li>University qualifications for a minimum period of 4 years and should be in connection with the nominated occupation.</li>\r\n	<li>Have sufficient funds to be able to manage staying in Austria which is needed at the time of submission of the application.</li>\r\n	<li>To get points you need experience or qualification which is in relation the role of Senior Manager.</li>\r\n	<li>To claim points the candidate should be between the age of 18 to 45 years;</li>\r\n	<li>Have basic skills of language which is German (A2) or English (intensified elementary use) to be even be able to work in the nominated occupation.</li>\r\n	<li>Your recent medical report</li>\r\n	<li>Police clearance certificate showing that you have no previous criminal record</li>\r\n	<li>Other supporting documents</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Austria job seeker visa processing time</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The processing of the Austria job seeker visa if it is processed by the regional settlement authority in Austria it can take up to a time period of a minimum of 3 &nbsp;to 5 months. In other words it can also take up to 8 weeks. But to get the Red-White-Red Card you need an employment offer which should match your qualification and should pay you well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Scientists and senior level managers are the kind of people who are chosen for this UK visa as it is for highly skilled professionals. Migrants have a critical role when it comes to the development of the Austrian economy and also there is an increasing demand for immigrants due to low rates in population.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Austria job seeker visa cost</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The cost of applying for the Austria job seeker visa comes to &euro; 150. In case you need to submit the Austrian Red-White-Red Card (work permit visa) application form, you shall need to pay a total amount of 120 EUR (132 USD).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The granting of the visa cost is &euro; 20 and the cost of personalisation which means the fingerprints, scan of photography and signature comes to a total of &euro; 20. After 21 months of living on the RWR card and working for an employer you can apply for a Red-White-Red (RWR) Card Plus which permits you to work for any employer in Austria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the most important reasons to apply for this UK visa is the excellent healthcare system of Austria which is regarded as one of the best. This visa is your ticket to finding a residence and the work of your liking in Austria</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Austria job seeker visa consultants</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Knowing about the procedure for this <strong>UK visa</strong> is not enough, which is why you need the assistance and guidance of Austria job seeker visa consultants who have the knowhow, skill and experience for you to steer clear of the intricate procedures of how to apply and cracking the Austria Job Seeker visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One such immigration consultancy is Orange Global Consaultancy Immigration Services who with over 28 years of experience in the immigration industry help you navigate on how to successfully apply for the Austria Job Seeker visa. Our team of consultants guide you in every possible manner on how to face minimum obstacles while applying for this job seeker visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What is an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>An Austria job seeker visa is a temporary residence permit that allows you to live in Austria for up to 6 months while you search for a job. You do not need to have a job offer in order to apply for this visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Who is eligible for an Austrian job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for an Austrian job seeker visa, you must meet be a Non- EU citizen, have a higher education degree recognized by the Austrian government, possess sufficient funds to support your stay in Austria, attain health insurance and must be able to speak and understand basic German.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What are the documents required for an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The documents required for an Austria job seeker visa vary depending on your nationality. However, some of the common documents that you will are valid passport, completed application form, copy of your higher education degree, bank statement, health insurance policy and a letter of motivation explaining your intentions in Austria.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>How long does it take to process an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Austria job seeker visa processing time can vary depending on the backlog of the Austrian Immigration Office. However, it typically takes around 1 to 3 months to process a job seeker visa application.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Can I bring along my family on an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>No, you cannot bring your family with you on an Austria job seeker visa. However, if you find a job in Austria and are granted a work permit, you can then apply for your family to join you.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Can I work while I am on an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>No, you cannot work while you are on an Austria job seeker visa. However, if you find a job in Austria and are granted a work permit, you can then start working.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>How much does it cost to apply for an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The application fee for an Austria job seeker visa is EUR 150.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Where can I apply for an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can apply for an Austria job seeker visa at the Austrian embassy or consulate in your home country.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What are the chances of getting an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The chances of getting an Austria job seeker visa are good if you meet the eligibility requirements and have a strong application. However, it is important to note that the Austrian Immigration Office may refuse your application if they do not believe that you have a realistic chance of finding a job in Austria.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What are the next steps after I get an Austria job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have been granted an Austria job seeker visa, you will need to find a job in Austria. You can start your job search by contacting Austrian employers directly or by using online job boards. If you find a job, you will need to apply for a work permit.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Only trusted and reliable&nbsp;visa consultants help you find the road to Austria without being misled. Looking to apply for fantastic and best visa options like Sweden Job Seeker visa? Get in touch with our certified immigration consultants by ringing us at <strong>8336933522</strong> or mail us at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '', '546202133_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTM2', 1, '2023-12-28 23:32:06'),
(137, 107, 'Sweden job seeker visa 2023- No Job offer requirement', '<p>Sweden is a fantastic place to live, study, and work with the best benefits in the world. Working and living in Sweden gives you countless benefits ranging from outstanding public services, relaxed everyday life, free education, excellent corporate culture, and an exceptional work-life balance. It is no surprise that many foreign nationals, especially Indians, prefer to move to Sweden, the largest country in the Scandinavia region, to enjoy everything this country offers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For many people, Sweden is synonymous with technical innovation, telecommunications, forestry, iron, and steel. It&rsquo;d surprise you that Sweden spends 3% of its GDP on research and development.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Innovation is a value which Sweden realty appreciates and encourages, which is why some of the top most and breaking barrier companies that rule the global tech scene belong to Sweden. Advanced social policies, reachable occupation, relaxed immigration policies, publicly funded medical facilities and teaching, are some of the reasons people choose Sweden as their place of employment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Working in Sweden</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You need a work permit if you are a non-EU national and want to work in Sweden. Sweden is the fourth European country that has launched a Job Seeker visa to address labour shortages. It means you can now go to Sweden without an offer of employment before arrival.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sweden unveiled the job seeker visa in April 2022, and in addition, it also determined the process for prospective immigrants seeking to move to Sweden without a job offer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With this new accomplishment, Sweden joins Germany, Austria, and Portugal among the European countries that launched the job seeker visa due to the massive shortage of workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to apply in Sweden then a work permit or a Job seeker visa is the simplest route in case you are a non EU overseas national who is interested in working here. You can do this via online as applications which are submitted online are send straight to the Swedish Migration Agency and have the facility of a priority processing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many work opportunities in many cities in Sweden which are Stockholm, Gothenburg and Malm&ouml;. Knowing about the official language can be a great incentive when you are working in Sweden as it can help you land a job.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On weekends you can go and move around 30 national parks or reside overnight in the global original Icehotel, situated in the village of Jukkasj&auml;rvi. Most of the Sweden relies mostly on overseas trade and is known for their excellent working conditions and has the most resilient job markets in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Sweden Job Seeker Visa- Why is it Important?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Sweden has a shortage of workers with specific skills across many sectors. There is a lack of well-trained nurses, doctors, engineers, teachers, carpenters, electricians, mechanics, and more. The shortage is expected to exist over the next five to ten years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Job agencies in Sweden have urged Swedish employers to consider recruiting workers with limited skills to fill rising job vacancies, as recent reports show a constant labour shortage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sweden was experiencing a shortage even before the pandemic hit the world. The country desperately needs qualified chefs, system developers, assistants, healthcare professionals, etc. The need intensified as the market started up again.&nbsp;The nation is looking for innovative and talented working professionals which is why they have launched with the Sweden Job Seeker visa.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many employers are struggling to hire workers for entry-level positions, such as restaurant waiting staff. The primary reason is that restaurant workers got laid off amid the pandemic. Many of them have found jobs in different sectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Job Seeker visa is valid for a period of 3 months but can be extended till 9 months also. Those who are qualified in jobs are issued the Sweden Job Seeker visa. Which is why when you need to apply for this visa you need an advanced degree.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Swedish Migration Agency directly sends your documents so that your level of education can be evaluated with the authorities. The agency cannot ask questions prior to making your application in case of Sweden Job Seeker visa.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the increasing demand for skilled professionals in Sweden, the job seeker visa is an excellent opportunity for non-EU citizens who do not wish to immigrate to Sweden through education or business investment. You can migrate for a specific duration, search for jobs, or start a business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What are the eligibility criteria?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To qualify for a job seeker visa for Sweden, you need the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must have completed studies equivalent to an advanced level degree.</li>\r\n	<li>Be able to include a Letter of Consent that gives the Swedish Council for Higher Education the right to contact higher educational authorities in your home country to verify your documents.</li>\r\n	<li>You must have sufficient funds to manage your expenses during the period you are applying for a permit.</li>\r\n	<li>You must demonstrate a well-defined plan to seek employment or explore business opportunities in Sweden.</li>\r\n	<li>You must have health insurance valid for care in Sweden.</li>\r\n	<li>It would help if you were currently living outside of Sweden.</li>\r\n	<li>You must have a valid passport.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Duration</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you apply, the Swedish Migration Agency will review your documents and decide your case. If all documents are satisfactory, you will be granted a permit for at least three months for no more than nine months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the permit is issued for over three months, you will receive a residence permit card. The card is evidence that your stay is valid in Sweden and features your fingerprint, photo, and other relevant information related to your visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What if I have secured a job offer in Sweden or started a business?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you land a job in Sweden during your stay, you can apply for a work permit. Please note that you cannot start working immediately in Sweden before applying to the Swedish Migration Agency for a valid work permit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to launch a business, then a residence permit under a self-employed person is the visa you should apply for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What do you mean by a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Sweden job seeker visa is a temporary residence visa permit that enables you to live and seek employment in Sweden for up to 9 months. You do not need a job offer to apply for this visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Who can apply for a job seeker visa of Sweden?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for a job seeker visa of Sweden, you must have a higher education degree that is recognized by the Swedish government. You must have sufficient funds to support yourself financially during your stay in Sweden. You must apply for health insurance that covers your stay in Sweden.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What are the documents required for a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The documents required for a Sweden job seeker visa vary depending on your nationality. However, the common documents you must provide are a valid passport, duly filed application form, higher education degree, bank statement, health insurance policy, and a letter of motivation explaining your intentions in Sweden.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>How long does it take to process a Swedish job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The processing time for a Swedish job seeker visa can vary depending on the backlog of the Swedish Migration Agency. However, processing a visa application typically takes 1 to 3 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Can I bring my family with me on a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>No, you cannot bring your family with you on a Sweden job seeker visa. However, if you find a job in Sweden, you can apply for a Sweden&rsquo;s work visa permit which allows you to bring your family to Sweden.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Can I work while I am on a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>No, you cannot work while you are on a Sweden job seeker visa. However, you can seek employment and attend interviews in Sweden. Once you find a job, you can apply for a Swedish work permit and start working for the employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>How much does it cost to apply for a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The application fee for a Swedish job seeker visa is SEK 1,500.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Where can I apply for a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can apply for a Swedish job seeker visa at the Swedish embassy or consulate in your home country by submitting your documents.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What are the chances of getting a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The chances of getting a Sweden job seeker visa are good if you meet the eligibility requirements and have a strong application. However, it is important to note that the Swedish Migration Agency may refuse your application if they do not believe that you have a realistic chance of finding a job in Sweden.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>What are the next steps after I get a Sweden job seeker visa?</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have been granted a Sweden job seeker visa, you will need to find a job in Sweden. You can start your job search by contacting Swedish employers directly or by using online job boards. If you find a job, you will need to apply for a work permit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to work in Sweden? If so, contact our migration agents today on 8336933522 or mail at info@orangeglobalconsultancy.in</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n</ol>', '', '900098297_org_img1.png', 'https://orangeglobalconsultancy.in/cms.php?type=MTM3', 1, '2023-12-28 23:35:42');
